title: fudgy brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.

title: adobo manook at baboy
directions: Combine the pork (baboy), vinegar, pepper, garlic and bay leaf.
Add the water.
Cover the pot and simmer for about 1 hour. Put the chicken (manook) in the pot and cook until tender.
Remove all meat pieces from the pot and drain them.
Brown the meat in grease or oil and then return it to the pot.
Add the coconut milk and simmer for 5 to 6 minutes before serving.

title: cream corn bread
directions: In an 8 x 8 dish, melt butter (must be butter).
Mix in bowl the baking mix, egg and creamed corn.
Pour mixture over butter; do not mix into butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool slightly and cut into squares to serve.

title: german chocolate sheet cake
directions: Pour this over cake mixture.
Bake in a 325° oven for 45 minutes, depending on oven.

title: meatballs in cherry sauce(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Meatballs:
Mix all ingredients.
Shape into balls about the size of a walnut.
Brown in an ungreased skillet on medium-low heat.
Drain and add the following sauce.
Serve over rice or with potatoes.

title: cheesy chicken
directions: Melt butter in baking dish.
Dip chicken in flour and place, skin side down, in baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 425° for 30 minutes.
Turn chicken and bake 15 more minutes.

title: coon balls
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Add no liquid.
Roll into balls about the size of a quarter.
Bake at 300 degrees for 15 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: orange beets
directions: Combine sugar, orange juice, peel, cornstarch, salt and pepper.
Bring to boil.
Cook until thickened.
Add beets and enjoy!

title: squash casserole
directions: Bake at 350° until brown.
Serves 4.

title: wedding punch
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 9 cups water, boil, stir and set aside. Bring sugar and 4 cups water to a rolling boil.
Combine all ingredients, except ginger ale.
Pour into two (1-gallon) jugs. Freeze.

title: upside-down pizza
directions: Brown sausage and drain; add remaining ingredients and put in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Lay 8 ounces thinly sliced Mozzarella cheese over meat mixture.

title: ed's incredible chicken
directions: In a large bowl, crush 4 to 5 cloves of garlic so that the juice from the garlic stays in the bowl as well as the garlic. Stir in onion salt, Lawry's seasoned salt, black pepper, soy sauce, teriyaki marinade sauce and Dale's steak sauce.
Stir well, making sure to cover the chicken with plenty of marinating juices. Cover your bowl with Saran Wrap and place in the refrigerator for 2 to 4 hours.
Stir chicken about once every hour to be sure you have your chicken well saturated.
You may cook your chicken on the grill, or in the oven on 450° for approximately 45 minutes. But, however you decide to cook your chicken, remember to baste it with the extra sauce.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Blend all ingredients thoroughly.
Roll dough 1/8 to 1/4-inch thick.
Cut with a round cookie cutter the size you like or have. (Chill the dough 2 to 3 hours, or overnight before rolling if it is difficult to handle.)
Place 1 to 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Place cookies on racks to cool.
Sprinkle with sugar or as desired.

title: carrot-coconut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, sift together first 6 ingredients.
Combine separately and add the next 3 ingredients. Stir just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Stir in last 3 ingredients.
Turn into 4 well-greased and floured 16 ounce fruit or vegetable cans or 2 (9-inch) bread pans.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes.
Remove from cans and cool thoroughly.
Wrap and refrigerate overnight or until used.

title: chinese almond cookies
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Add egg and almond extract and mix thoroughly.
Stir flour, salt and soda together. Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture.
Mix thoroughly.
Roll dough into small balls.
Press almond into top of ball.
Bake at 350° for approximately 20 minutes; cookies should be set and not browned.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour, corn meal and salt.
Add butter, lemon rind, lemon juice and milk; mix well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well with a wire whisk after each addition.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: cynthia's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix brown sugar, sugar and eggs in bowl at medium speed; add shortening.
Mix well.
Add flour, salt and baking soda.
Mix in water at low speed.
Add chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Bake for 11 minutes at 350°.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream margarine, cream and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating 30 seconds after each addition.
Combine flour, baking powder, salt and vanilla and add milk, beating well.
Can add 1/2 cup cocoa, if you wish.
Pour batter into well-greased pan and bake at 325° for 2 hours.

title: peanut butter chewies
directions: Bring to a slow boil the sugar, white syrup, peanut butter and butter.
Stir constantly until boils.
Add cornflakes.
Drop on wax paper and cool.

title: monster balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drop spoonful of mixture on child's plate and let them form into a monster ball.
Have fun.

title: golden potato salad
directions: Heat 1-inch salted water (1/2 teaspoon salt to 1 cup water) to boiling.
Add potatoes.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat.
Cover and cook until tender, 30 to 35 minutes.
Drain and cool.
Cut potatoes into cubes.
Stir in onion, Italian dressing and salt and pepper.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Just before serving, toss with mayo and stir in other ingredients.

title: easy coconut macaroons
directions: Slice bread into quarters; place on toaster oven tray.
Pour milk over bread and sprinkle with coconut.
Bake until brown.

title: gourmet acorn squash
directions: Cut squash in halves and remove seeds and membranes.
Arrange on buttered baking sheet.
Fry bacon until crisp and drain on paper towels. Crumble and reserve.
In bacon fat, saute onion, celery and green pepper until tender.
Stir in tomato sauce. Sprinkle squash halves with salt and dot with butter.
Put a tablespoon of vegetable mixture in each cavity and sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until tender when pierced with a fork.
Sprinkle bacon on top before serving.

title: cocktail wieners
directions: Mix the prepared mustard and red currant jelly together and heat over hot water. Add little smokies and heat through. Serve hot from a chafing dish, electric frying pan or shallow saucepan. Spear with toothpicks to eat. Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: cajun carrots
directions: Peel and cut carrots into 2-inch strips.
Cook until tender. Drain and put in a 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Mix mayonnaise, horseradish, onions, salt and pepper together; then add carrots. Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 300° for 15 minutes.

title: ham-broccoli casserole
directions: In a large
bowl blend soup, Cheez Whiz and milk.
Cook onion in	butter	until
tender.	Cook
broccoli	until almost tender; drain
and	add onion, broccoli, ham and uncooked rice to soup mixture.
This
makes
1/2 quart casserole.
Bake, covered, 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients; mix well. Shape into ball. Refrigerate overnight.
Roll in chopped pecans.

title: raisin sponge pie
directions: Put raisin mixture in bottom of crust; add batter and put crumbs on top.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes, then turn to 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: dip for bread and veggies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: summer garden medley
directions: Saute onion in butter in a Dutch oven.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook over medium heat for 15 minutes, or until vegetables are tender.
Serves 8.

title: chocolate syrup brownies
directions: Boil about 2 minutes and add 1/2 cup chocolate chips. Spread over cooled brownies.

title: vanilla egg pie
directions: Separate eggs; save whites for meringue.
Mix egg yolks, sugar and flour well.
May have to use a little of milk to mix well. Add rest of milk, vanilla and margarine.
Cook on top of stove on medium heat, stirring often.
Cook until thick.
Cool.
Pour in unbaked pie shell and bake until shell browns at 325°.

title: marshmallow treats
directions: Melt margarine in large saucepan; heat over low heat.
Add marshmallows and cook, stirring constantly, until marshmallows are melted and mixture is syrupy.
Remove from heat; add Rice Krispies. Stir until well coated.
Pour into buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Press evenly and firmly into pan.
Let cool.
Yield:
24 squares (2 x 2-inch).

title: cabbage and hamburger casserole
directions: Saut onion in butter. Add ground beef. Heat through, but not browning; drain. Add salt and pepper. Spread in a 2-quart baking dish 3 cups of shredded cabbage. Cover with meat mixture. Add layer of cut cabbage. Pour tomato soup over all. Bake covered at 350° for 1 hour.

title: garlic grits
directions: Bring water to boil.
Add salt; stir in grits.
Cook, covered, on low heat until done (about 20 minutes).
Stir in cheese (cut into cubes), butter, eggs, milk and hot sauce.

title: potato casserole
directions: Parboil potatoes, drain, cool and grate.
Add butter, cheese, onions, salt and pepper.
Stir in sour cream.
Put mixture in a greased casserole dish. Dot with butter and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serves 10.

title: old time buttermilk pie(makes 1 deep dish (9-inch) pie or 2 (9-inch) shallow pies)
directions: Melt butter.
Add sugar, flour and eggs.
Mix well.
Stir in buttermilk and vanilla.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Pecans can be added to the mix or put on pie crust before you pour in mix. Bake for 45 to 50 minutes at 350° or until brown.
The pecans will rise to the top while baking.
Allow to cool completely before serving.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix lemon juice and milk.
Add prepared Dream Whip topping and pineapple.
Mix well.
Pour into 2 graham cracker crusts; chill at least 2 hours before serving.

title: pizza lover's lasagna
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Cook lasagna noodles according to package directions.
Rinse and drain.

title: milky way cake
directions: Melt bars and 1/2 cup butter in saucepan over low heat.
Beat remaining 1/2 cup butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well.
Add flour and baking soda alternately with buttermilk.
Mix until smooth.
Add melted bars.
Mix well.
Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Slice potatoes into 1/4-inch thick slices and boil.
Cut up onion and cook in microwave oven for about 2 minutes.
Mix potatoes, onion, soup, sour cream, 1/2 stick of butter (melted) and cheese.
Pour into buttered 9 x 11-inch casserole dish.
Top with corn flake crumbs and 1/2 stick of melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix
all
ingredients well;
fold in Cool Whip and pour into shallow dish.
Chill and serve.

title: barb's sour cream potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Thaw hash browns.
Mix together potatoes, sour cream, soups, onion and cheese.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with corn flake crumbs and butter which have been mixed together.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: honey baked chicken
directions: Wash and dry chicken pieces; skins can be removed.
Melt margarine in a shallow baking pan.
Add remaining ingredients. Roll chicken pieces in the mixture, then arrange in a single layer in the same pan.
Bake at 375°, basting occasionally for 40 minutes, 30 minutes for boneless breasts.

title: lemon lush
directions: Blend first 3 ingredients together and pat into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Remove and cool.
Blend cream cheese, confectioners sugar and 1 cup whipped cream together and put onto crust.
Mix pudding and milk together and put on top of cheese mixture.
Top all with 1 pint of whipped cream.

title: perdenales river chili
directions: Put meat, onion and garlic in a large heavy skillet.
Sear until light colored.
Add oregano, cumin, chili powder, Ro-Tel and hot water.
Bring to a boil, lower heat and simmer about 1 hour; as fat cooks out, skim.
This can be served as a dip, alone or over rice, or add chili beans for a chili con carne.

title: lazy cherry cobbler
directions: Pour pie filling in a baking dish; sprinkle cake mix over top. Drizzle melted margarine over all.
Add nuts.
Bake in a 350° oven until brown on top (about 30 minutes).

title: sweet and sour pork(crock-pot)
directions: Sprinkle pork pieces with paprika.
Heat shortening in skillet.
Saute pork and discard fat.
Place meat in crock-pot. Add onion and pepper.
Combine the next 4 ingredients in bowl, then add vinegar, soy sauce, Worcestershire sauce and 2/3 cup pineapple liquid.
(If juice does not make this much, add water.) Pour entire mixture into crock-pot.
Cook on low 8 to 9 hours, or on high 4 to 5 hours.
During last 1 to 2 hours, add pineapple. Serves 4 to 6.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix all the ingredients.
Serve with fresh vegetables.

title: green rice
directions: Stir together.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease square 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan. Place apple slices in pan.
Mix all other ingredients together. Sprinkle over apples.
Bake 30 minutes or until apples are tender and topping is golden brown.
Serve warm.

title: candy bacon
directions: Cut a strip of bacon into thirds.
Drench in brown sugar and pleat onto a toothpick.
Bake in a medium oven for 10 to 15 minutes.
It should be crisp but not burned.
Let it cool for a few minutes before serving.
The hot sugar can be very painful to the mouth.

title: the best dip
directions: Cook sausage and hamburger; drain. Add all other ingredients in crock-pot and slowly simmer until cheese is melted.
Use your choice of chips for dipping.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Cook macaroni.
Brown meat and onion.
Add salt and pepper. Mix hamburger, macaroni, pizza sauce, tomato sauce, tomato paste, and sugar.
Add spices to suit your taste.
Place half the mixture in casserole.
Add a layer of cheese, then another layer of each. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes

title: sweet potato souffl
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Mix first 5 ingredients. Butter dish and pour into a bowl. Mix remaining ingredients and crumble on top. Cook for 25 minutes, then top with marshmallows and cook until brown.

title: mexican lime chicken
directions: Mix marinade ingredients in a medium bowl.
Add the chicken and chill for 2 hours. Preheat oven to high broil.
Cut the chicken into strips for faster cooking under broiler; cook until done.
When done, arrange the chicken in a baking pan.
Spread a layer
of Mexi-ranch dressing on each portion of chicken, followed by 1/4 c. of the shredded cheese.
Broil for 2 to 3 minutes, or just until the cheese has melted.
To serve, spread a bed of tortilla strips on each of 4 plates.
Slide a chicken portion onto the chips and serve with your favorite rice or other Mexican dish. Serves 4.

title: custard pie
directions: Mix ingredients together except pie crust.
Pour mixture into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes, then bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
An inserted knife will come out clean when custard is done.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Line a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish with crust; cut chicken in bite size pieces.
Put a layer of chicken, then a layer of English peas, then a layer of diced potatoes, then add chopped onion, salt and pepper to taste.
Cover the top with crust.
Pour enough chicken broth over the pie until crust is covered.
Bake in a 325° oven until crust is golden brown.

title: quick rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Spoon into greased muffin tin.
Let rise 1/2 to 1 hour.
Bake at 350° until brown.
Will keep 2 weeks in refrigerator in covered bowl.

title: ambrosia
directions: Peel and remove seeds from oranges.
Divide sections and cut into thirds.
Toss with coconut, pineapple and sugar.

title: fried squash
directions: If you like you can fry fat back meat and use grease to season or use vegetable oil.
Wash and chop squash (I use yellow squash). Put in frying pan with about 1 1/2 cups water or more.
Cook squash until beginning to get soft.
Add chopped onion and fat back meat grease or vegetable oil.
Season with sugar, salt and pepper.
Squash will be done just before they come all to pieces.

title: tasty toss-up salad
directions: Prepare Creamettes according to directions.
In small bowl blend dressing and seasonings.
Add to salad mixture to coat. Cover and chill.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil
potatoes	until just slightly hard; drain.
Cover with cold water and drain again.
Refrigerate until cool.
Cut up potatoes
into
bite
size pieces and add chopped eggs and onion. Blend in mayo and salt and pepper.	Refrigerate.

title: vidalia onion casserole
directions: Saute onions in butter until tender.
Mix broth with onions. Layer 1/2 onions, 1/2 cheese and 1/2 crushed crackers.
Repeat layers.

title: cherry cheese dessert
directions: Mix and pat down.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool thoroughly.

title: blueberry cream pie
directions: Beat cream cheese and sugar together.
Stir in Cool Whip. Pour into graham cracker crust.
Add pie filling on top and chill.

title: one dish meal or ground meat-vegetable casserole
directions: Brown meat; drain in colander.
Add salt, pepper and other seasonings desired.
Put in casserole dish.
Slice or chop vegetables.
Layer potatoes, onions, carrots and bell pepper. Dash a little salt on vegetables.
Pour mushroom soup over vegetables.
Spread Ro-Tel tomatoes over soup.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until vegetables are done.
Very tasty!

title: coconut cookies
directions: Cream butter
and sugar together.
Add eggs and vanilla and beat.
Add dry ingredients and beat.
Add coconut, oatmeal and nuts.
Form
into
balls
and flatten on cookie sheet with glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° until light brown.

title: oven baked baby back spareribs
directions: After cleaning ribs, season with seasoning salt.
In large baking dish, mix lemon juice and liquid smoke.
Spread over ribs. Cover with plastic wrap and marinate 3 hours or overnight in refrigerator.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except shredded cheese.
In baking dish, layer meat mixture and cheese, ending with cheese on top.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 minutes.
Serve with crusty warm rolls.

title: hermann sour cream chocolate cake
directions: Sift together all dry ingredients; add to cream.
Beat in mixer two to three minutes.
Add whole eggs, one at a time, and beat well.
Pour batter into two 9-inch layer pans plus an 11 x 7 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch pan or two 13 x 9 x 2 1/2-inch pans.
Bake at 375° for about 30 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Ice as soon as cool.

title: sweet pumpkin bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease an 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch loaf pan. Beat sugar with oil until blended using mixer at medium speed.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Continue until light and fluffy, then beat in pumpkin.
Combine remaining ingredients; beat in flour mixture using mixer on low speed.
Pour into pan.
Bake 60 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean. Cool 10 minutes; remove from pan.
Finish cooling.

title: mom's meat loaf
directions: Pre-heat oven to 350°. Mix ingredients. Press into greased pan and bake for 1 1/2 hours.
Makes 2 small loaves or 1 9x13 loaf.

title: amaretto cheesecake
directions: Delicious and calorie rich.

title: volcano punch
directions: In punch bowl, combine pineapple juice and limeade concentrate.
Just before serving, stir in ginger ale and add scoops of sherbet.
Garnish with fresh fruit.
Makes about 6 quarts.

title: french dressing
directions: Place in quart jar; shake well.

title: pea salad
directions: Mix all together and garnish with crisp cooked crumbled bacon.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients and place in a 9 x 13 baking dish.
Top with 2 cups crushed cornflakes mixed with 2 tablespoon melted margarine.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: nellie's soup-stew
directions: Put kettle with setting or large pot on high.
Put in butter and brown beef cubes on both sides.
Add diced shallots, celery, carrots and potatoes in that order.
Stir.

title: shortbread cookies
directions: Mix by hand. Roll into small round rolls and chill. Slice and bake 20 to 25 minutes at 300°. Cookies will be light in color.

title: oriental chicken
directions: Use any amount of ingredients.
Stir-fry chicken breast strips in 2 to 3 tablespoons of oil.
Add strips of bell pepper and saute a few minutes.
Add onion, cut up, mushrooms and water chestnuts. Saute until tender.
Add 1 can cream of broccoli soup.
Cook on low heat until bubbly.
Add 2 cans water, soy sauce to taste, salt and pepper.
Serve over rice.

title: zucchini rice casserole(serves 15)
directions: Cook zucchini in boiling water until tender-crisp (3 to 5 minutes).
Drain well.
In greased 3-quart casserole, layer rice, 1 cup Sour Cream Sauce, turkey or chicken, cheese, zucchini, tomatoes, rest of Sour Cream Sauce and parsley.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Let stand a few minutes before serving.

title: italian cauliflower
directions: Cook onion and garlic in dressing for 2 to 3 minutes until tender.
Add cauliflower, water and salt.
Cook, covered, over low heat for 10 minutes or longer until cauliflower is tender.
Stir in basil and tomatoes.
Heat through.

title: ham and cheese chicken rolls
directions: Flatten chicken to even thickness, using the palm of your hand. Place ham slice on each breast.
Place cheese on top of ham.
Roll up each chicken breast; tuck in ham and cheese.
Secure with wooden toothpicks.
Heat oil in 10-inch skillet.
Cook chicken rolls for 10 minutes, or until browned.
Remove excess oil from pan.
Stir in soup, milk, thyme and onions.
Cover and cook for 10 minutes, until chicken is no longer pink.
Remove toothpicks to serve.
Spoon sauce over chicken.
Garnish with parsley.

title: olive stuffed meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Shape into a 4-inch diameter column on a baking sheet.
Cover with ketchup or tomato sauce and bake for 1 hour.
Remove to a warm platter.

title: company french toast
directions: In 9 x 13-inch pan melt butter, brown sugar and cinnamon.
Take 12 slices bread and layer on top of the melted butter mixture (6 slices on the bottom and 6 layed on those).
Next beat eggs and milk; pour over bread.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Cook for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: funnel cakes
directions: In medium bowl, beat egg with milk, flour, sugar, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Using funnel with about 3/8-inch diameter spout opening, hold finger over end of funnel spout.
Pour about 3 tablespoons batter into funnel if using round mini-fryer, heated to 375° or 4 tablespoons of batter for rectangular mini-fryer. Move finger as batter flows through spout.
Move funnel in a crisscrossing pattern above surface of hot oil until funnel is empty.
Fry about 1 minute, turn and fry another 1/2 minute. Remove from pan, drain on paper towel.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Makes 6 funnel cakes.

title: quick stroganoff
directions: You will need a 2-quart casserole dish.

title: popcorn cake
directions: Melt marshmallows, butter and oil.
Mix popcorn and M&M's. Add together and put in a Bundt pan.
Turn out on serving plate.

title: french beef stew
directions: Combine beef, onions, celery and carrots in 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Combine tomato juice, tapioca, sugar, salt, pepper and basil.
Pour over meat and vegetables.
Cover and bake in a 300° oven for 2 1/2 hours. Add potatoes and cook 1 hour longer. Stir occasionally.

title: chocolate drop cookies
directions: Mix thoroughly butter, sugar, egg, chocolate, buttermilk and vanilla.
Stir in flour, soda, salt and nuts.
Cover and chill 1 hour.
Heat oven to 400°.
Drop dough by rounded teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until almost no imprint remains when touched with finger. Immediately remove from baking sheet and cool.
Frost with chocolate icing.
Makes 4 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: cottage cheese dip
directions: Place milk in blender and cottage cheese; mix until cheese is smooth.
Add other ingredients.
Pour in bowl and chill.
Cover. Makes 1 3/4 cups.
Keep chilled.

title: persimmon pie
directions: Prepare topping.
Mix pulp, sugar and dry gelatin thoroughly. Add 1 cup topping and stir just enough to mix.
Pour into pie shell and chill about 2 hours to set.
Serve with whipped topping.

title: cornbread
directions: Combine all ingredients, using enough buttermilk to make a thin batter.
Bake in a greased pan for 15 to 20 minutes at 425°.

title: scalloped potatoes and ham
directions: Slice potatoes into a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Chop the onion in the pan. Salt to taste. Add chopped ham (optional).
Heat cream of celery soup and milk until blended and pour into baking pan. Cover and bake until done at 350°, approximately 1 hour.

title: smashed potatoes
directions: After baking, cut potatoes in half lengthwise.
Allow to cool for a few minutes.
In a medium bowl, place cheese, butter and a dash of salt and pepper.
Using a spoon, scoop out the potato half, leaving a thin layer around the inside of the skins.
Mix this with cheese mixture and fill potato skins, placing them in a dish that will keep them upright.
Return potatoes to oven for a few minutes.
Sprinkle with extra cheese, if desired.

title: mama robena's pork barbecue
directions: Season pork overnight with garlic salt, paprika and pepper. Bake on a rack in a 250° oven until skin is crisp (about 3 1/2 to 4 hours).
Make barbecue sauce with vinegar, catsup, sugar, salt and crushed red pepper.

Baste and cook over low flame for 10 minutes. When pork is done, remove and let stand until it is cool enough to chop in small pieces, including skin. When this is finished, pour remaining sauce over pork.
Serve on a warm bun with cole slaw.

title: pear bran bread
directions: Beat molasses, honey, and egg until well blended.
Stir in buttermilk and oil.
Combine flour, bran, brown sugar, salt and soda.
Add to buttermilk mixture.
Blend until smooth.
Fold in pears and nuts.
Pour into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 65 to 70 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center of loaf comes out clean.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix strawberry jello with 1 1/2 cups boiling water; dissolve well.
Stir in pineapple (drained) and pie filling; chill.

title: cornbread
directions: Mix ingredients together well. Pour into greased baking pan and bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix together.
Place in mold or 9-inch square pan.

title: congo squares
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Mix oil and sugar; beat in eggs one at a time.
Add dry ingredients, nuts and chocolate chips.
Mix thoroughly.
Spread 3/4-inch thick in a greased pan (10 1/2 x 15 1/2-inch).
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.
When almost cool, cut into squares.

title: people chow
directions: Melt margarine, peanut butter and chocolate morsels.
Put Crispix in Fix-N-Mix bowl and pour chocolate mixture over. Put seal on and shake well until all cereal is coated.

title: hot cheese appetizers
directions: Remove crusts from bread.
Mix remaining ingredients together until well blended.
Spread mixture on 3 slices of bread.
Stack, making 3 layers.
Repeat until bread and filling are used.
Cut through layers, making 8 triangles from each stack.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
These can be made ahead of time and frozen.
Do not cut before freezing.

title: stuffed manicotti
directions: Combine
water,
tomato
sauce, spaghetti sauce mix and ground beef; simmer for 6 minutes.
Blend half the Mozzarella with the Ricotta
and Parmesan.
Beat the eggs and blend with salt,	pepper and cheeses.
Fill manicotti shells with cheese mixture.
Put
1 cup sauce in bottom of casserole dish.
Layer with	manicotti shells,
sauce and the rest of the Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: hamburger potato casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Layer hamburger and potatoes in casserole.
Add salt & pepper.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over casserole.
Top with cheese slices.
Crushed potato chips or canned onion rings may be substituted for cheese.

title: apple crisp
directions: Slice apples in a Pam-sprayed 8 x 8-inch baking dish or cake pan.
Sprinkle about 1/2 to 3/4 cup sugar and some cinnamon over all.

title: dutch baby pancakes
directions: Preheat oven and put butter into a pan.
Mix eggs in blender. Add milk and then flour into eggs.
When the butter is melted, pour batter into hot pan.
When brown and fluffy, serve on table with maple syrup.

title: chicken dijon
directions: In a skillet, cook chicken in 1 tablespoon of hot margarine for 10 minutes or until browned. Remove from skillet.

title: divinity
directions: Cook and stir sugar, corn syrup, water and salt until mixture comes to boil.
Cook to 250° without stirring.
Remove from heat. Set aside.
Immediately beat egg whites until stiff.
Pour hot syrup slowly over egg whites, beating constantly at high speed, about 5 minutes.
Add vanilla and beat until mixture forms soft peaks and begins to lose gloss.
Add chopped nuts.
Drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients.
Roll into balls.
Bake at 350° on greased cookie sheet for 10 to 15 minutes.
Warm last 3 ingredients in saucepan until smooth.
Add cooked meatballs to sauce.
Heat 10 minutes.

title: mom blackburn's sugared nuts
directions: Beat egg white; add sugar and vanilla.
Beat well.
Place nuts in brown paper lined pan.
Pour melted margarine over nuts.
Stir in egg mixture and add dash of cinnamon.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring nuts every 15 minutes.

title: pumpkin cheese bread
directions: Combine sugar, cream cheese and margarine, mixing at medium speed until well blended.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each.
Blend in pumpkin.
Add combined dry ingredients, mixing just until moistened.
Fold in nuts.
Pour into two greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until wooden pick inserted comes out clean.
Cool 5 minutes. Remove from pans.

title: plum baby food cake
directions: Mix eggs and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients and beat well (add nuts last).
Pour into a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, then glaze cake while cake is still warm.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Boil 5 minutes.
Stir constantly.
Remove from fire; stir until it thickens.
Pour on buttered platter and cut.
Mrs. Tapp.

title: hello dolly bars
directions: Melt butter in 9-inch square pan.
Sprinkle in a layer each of the graham cracker crumbs, coconut, chocolate chips and nuts. Pour sweetened condensed milk over top.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Cool in pan and cut into bars.

title: artichoke spread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350° in glass pie pan.

title: jam strip cheesers
directions: Sift together flour and salt.
Cream butter and cream cheese thoroughly.
Blend in dry ingredients gradually; mix thoroughly. Roll out on floured pastry cloth or board to 1/2 inch thickness. Cut into 3 x 1-inch strips.
Make a deep groove lengthwise down the center of each cookie with handle of knife, keeping ends closed.
Place 1/2 teaspoon jam or jelly in each groove.
Place on ungreased baking sheet and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes until delicately browned.
Serve warm or cold.
Makes 2 dozen cookies.

title: mock chow mein
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Mix in next 6 ingredients.
Place all in a 3 quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cut up cooked chicken or other meat may be substituted for beef.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Mix margarine, flour and nuts together; pour into a square pan.
Bake until golden brown and let cool.
Mix the cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip together; spread over cooled crust. Dip strawberries out of juice and place on cream cheese mixture until covered.

title: quick fluffy frosting
directions: Pour milk into deep narrow bowl.
Add Dream Whip and pudding mix.
Beat until forms peaks.
Makes 3 cups.
Store frosted cake in refrigerator.

title: three day coconut cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package directions, making two 8 or 9-inch layers.
When cool, split layers in half.
While cake is cooling, combine sugar, sour cream and coconut, blending well. Chill.
Reserve 1 cup of this mixture.
Spread remainder between split layers of cake, making it 4 layers high.
Combine reserved sour cream mixture with thawed whipped topping.
Blend until smooth.
Spread on top and sides of cake.
Store in airtight container; refrigerate for 3 days before serving.

title: baked pork chops with dressing
directions: Season and flour chops; brown in butter.
Remove from pan; cook onion in drippings until done.
Combine corn, egg, bread crumbs, salt, pepper and onion; mix well.
Place chops in baking dish; cover each chop with dressing.
Add water; cover.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.
Uncover; bake for 15 minutes longer.
Yield: 4 to
6 servings.

title: kool-aid pie
directions: Soften gelatine in 1/4 cup cold water for 3 minutes.
Add hot water; stir until dissolved.
Add frozen milk and sugar; whip. Add Kool-Aid; whip until firm.

title: stir-fry
directions: In wok on medium-high heat, brown garlic in 2 tablespoons oil. Add beef (chicken, pork and shrimp); brown.
Add vegetables, then soy sauce, salt and pepper.
Cook for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: crab pecan delight
directions: Saute in butter celery, onion, 1 cup pecans and garlic.
Add salt and pepper.
Stir in crab and soup.
Slowly stir in milk and simmer 10 minutes.
Spoon into lightly greased 8-inch casserole. Top with crumbs, remaining pecans and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Melt butter in milk.
Add vanilla; pour in the powdered sugar. Stir until mix is smooth (if too thick, add a little milk, then add peanut butter and mix well).
Pour into buttered plate; let cool.
Cut into pieces.

title: stuffed chicken breasts
directions: Combine stuffing, Parmesan cheese and parsley.
Dip chicken breasts in butter; roll in crumb mixture.
Place slice of cheese and ham on top.
Roll from narrow end; secure with toothpick.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes or microwave on High for 10 minutes.

title: cranberry-raisin stuffing
directions: Toast bread cubes in 300° oven about 15 minutes.
Toss bread cubes with melted butter.
Add remaining ingredients.
Toss lightly until well mixed.
Place in neck and body cavity of 12 pound turkey and bake as directed for stuffed turkey.
Do not pack the stuffing.

title: fresh apple bread
directions: Sift together first 3 ingredients. Cream together butter, sugar and eggs. Add apples, nuts and vanilla to creamed ingredients. Stir in flour mixture. Pour into greased loaf pan. Sprinkle with topping. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pickled okra
directions: Wash okra and pack in 5 hot sterilized pint jars.
Put one clove of garlic in each jar.
Bring remaining ingredients to a boil.
Pour over okra and seal.
Keep several weeks before serving.

title: celery casserole
directions: Slice celery on diagonal; cover with water and cook until tender.
Drain.
Add water chestnuts, pimientos and soup.
Mix well.
Put into greased casserole.
Cover with crumbs, butter and almonds.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs and sugar.
Add other ingredients; mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes, or until brown.

title: low-fat cookie dough ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients, except ice cream, until well blended. Add more milk, if necessary.
Spoon mixture into softened ice cream, then gently fold in, being careful not to overmix.
Pour into freezer-safe container and freeze.
Yields 16 (4 ounce) servings, 1.3 g fat each.

title: apples and yams
directions: Remove skin from yams; arrange apples and yams in shallow casserole dish.
Combine brown sugar, cinnamon and melted butter and pour over casserole.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes, basting occasionally.

title: becky's fish and vegies
directions: Brown garlic in oil.
Add vegetables, chopped.
Add seasonings and 1 tomato, sliced or quartered (wine optional).
Cover and simmer until vegetables are almost ready.
Add in fish, stir and cover until fish is cooked.
Serve with bread or over pasta.

title: crescent rolls
directions: Add yeast to warm water, stirring to dissolve.
Stir in sugar, salt, eggs and shortening.
Add half of flour.
Add remaining flour and mix until smooth.
Scrape dough from sides of bowl and cover with damp cloth.
Let rise until double (about 1 1/2 hours).

title: fried ice cream
directions: Heat sugar and butter in saucepan until melted.
Add rest of ingredients (except ice cream).
Stir well.
Press half of mixture in 11 x 7-inch pan.
Spread with ice cream.
Top with rest of mixture.
Freeze.
Cut in squares and serve.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Drain liquid from salmon into measuring cup.
Add enough milk to make 3/4 cup.
Flake salmon, removing bones and skin.
Blend in egg.
Stir in rest of ingredients. Spoon lightly into greased loaf pan.
Bake for 45 minutes.

title: beef log(makes five 1 pound logs)
directions: Mix all together and put in refrigerator for 4 days.
Every day, be sure to mix it well.
On the 4th day, mold it into sausage size rolls and bake on rack in broiler pan for 8 hours at 200°.

title: chicken chow mein
directions: Melt margarine in large skillet with a lid.
Add chicken and stir-fry until lightly browned.
Add celery and onion; stir-fry for 2 to 3 minutes.
Add pepper and chicken broth; cover and cook until tender, about 15 minutes.
Drain Chinese vegetables; rinse and drain again.
Add to skillet; add undrained mushrooms and bring to a boil.

If more than 1 1/2 to 2 cups of liquid remain in skillet, cook over high heat to quickly evaporate excess liquid. In a cup, mix the cornstarch and soy sauce; stir until smooth. Add to skillet, stirring well to coat the vegetables and thicken liquid.
Add more water if sauce is too thick.
Serve over chow mein noodles.
Serves 4.

title: johnny mazetti
directions: Saute meat in heavy skillet.
Add vegetables and cook 10 minutes.
Add soup and simmer for 30 minutes.
Add cooked noodles.
Pour into a casserole dish and sprinkle with 1/2 cup grated cheese.
Serves 6.

title: pistachio pudding
directions: Combine pudding mix with whipped topping, stirring until the mixture turns green.
Fold in chopped walnuts and crushed pineapple, stirring until thoroughly combined.
Chill.

title: great cold cheese dip
directions: Blend with mixer or blender.
Serve with nachos.

title: guacamole salad
directions: Blend together and chill for one hour.
Serve with chips.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until tender.
Drain and mash.
Drain again.
Add butter, milk, salt and cheese. Pour this mixture into greased casserole dish.
Top with cracker crumbs.
Drizzle egg over top of this.
Bake at 350° about 25 to 30 minutes or until done.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Mix first 5 ingredients in a large bowl. Combine remaining ingredients. Pour in foil mini loaf pans or 2 regular loaf pans. Bake at 350° about 30 minutes or until nicely browned, depending on size of pans.

title: jazzabelle sauce
directions: Combine in blender; mix well.
Refrigerate.
Serve over cream cheese with crackers.
Good appetizer!

title: wash day hot dish
directions: Brown hamburger and onions.
Pour in bottom of casserole. Cover with layers of rice, celery, potatoes and beans.
Pour tomatoes over top and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until potatoes are done.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat all ingredients together.
Add 1 cup broken pecans.
Bake in unbaked pie shell at 250° for about 1 hour.

title: zucchini chocolate cake(extra moist)
directions: Mix margarine, oil, sugar and eggs; mix until smooth.
Add vanilla and sour cream.
Add zucchini.
Add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Bake in a tube pan or an 8 x 10-inch pan.
Bake in a 325° oven.

title: diabetic apple pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°. Put apples in pastry lined pan. Heat juice, cornstarch and spice (optional). Let it boil until clear. Pour over apples. Cover with top crust. Bake 50 to 60 minutes.

title: peach crinkle
directions: Spread peaches in lightly greased 8 x 12-inch baking dish. Sprinkle with lemon rind. Combine pie crust mix and brown sugar in bowl; mix well. Sprinkle over top; dot with margarine. Bake at 425° for 15 minutes. Serve with ice cream. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: holiday salad just for kids
directions: On individual plates make a bed of lettuce.
Place a slice of pineapple on the plate of lettuce.
Peel the banana and cut in half crosswise.
Place cut side down in the center of the pineapple.
Top with cherry holding with a toothpick.
When complete the salad will resemble a candle.
Kids can make one for each person.

title: pig picking cake
directions: Combine cake mix, oil, vanilla, eggs and mandarin oranges and then mix.
Bake in 4 layers at 325° for 15 minutes or until done. Layers will be thin.
Sprinkle pudding onto Cool Whip.
Fold in nuts and pineapple.
Frost cake (after layers are cool).
Store in a cool place.

title: party ham 'n cheese ball
directions: Drain ham; blend in cheese and mayonnaise.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Cover and refrigerate 8 to 12 hours. Shape into a ball or mold as
desired.
Roll in finely chopped pecans.
Let stand a little longer.
Serve with crackers or use as a filling for appetizers.

title: microwave seasoned potatoes
directions: Slice potatoes and put in flat microwave dish with a lid.
Add 1/2 stick butter and season with Lawry's seasoned salt. Microwave on High for 20 minutes, stirring potatoes every 5 minutes.

title: company potato casserole
directions: Defrost potatoes.
Combine with all remaining ingredients. Pour into buttered 3-quart casserole.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.
Early 70's.
Old recipe from newspaper.

title: peanut butter rice krispies treats
directions: Bring corn syrup and sugar to boil.
Take off heat and add peanut butter.
Stir until mixed completely.
Add rice cereal. Stir well.
Pour into 9 x 13 pan that has been sprayed with nonstick spray.

title: baked beans with ground beef topping
directions: In a large frying pan cook ground beef in its own fat.
Add green peppers, onions and celery; saute until beef is brown and vegetables are limp.
Stir in tomato sauce, water, vinegar, garlic, mustard, thyme, brown sugar and salt and pepper to taste. Simmer together for 5 minutes.
Turn pork and beans into a greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Spoon meat mixture over the top.
Bake in a moderately hot oven (375°) for 45 minutes.

title: pumpkin squares
directions: Cream sugar, oil, eggs and pumpkin together.
Add flour, salt, baking powder, baking soda and cinnamon.
Pour into greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Combine the sugar, cocoa, flour and salt.
Add boiling water and butter.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Add vanilla.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Mix all together and pour into 13x9-inch baking dish, greased and floured.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: easy "surprise" pickles
directions: Remove dill pickles, discard liquid and drain well. Wash pickles, then cut into lengthwise sections (usually quarters). Wash again.
Drain and cover with cold water; soak overnight. (Can be put back into same jar for the overnight period.)
Let come to a boil the mixture of vinegar, water and sugar.
Set aside until cool.
Drain the pickles and cover with cooled mixture in same jar.
Refrigerate and serve after allowing a few hours for mixture to soak in good.

title: chicken broccoli bake
directions: Butter 9 inch dish.
Layer broccoli, chicken, bread cubes, cheese.
Combine gravy, milk and pepper, pour over cheese.
Bake 375° for 40 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: cornmeal cookies
directions: Blend margarine and sugar in bowl.
Add egg and beat well. Add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Drop dough from teaspoon on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes about 3 dozen cookies.

title: hobo dinner
directions: Shape beef into patties on a large sheet of aluminum foil in a large baking pan.
Top with vegetables.
Season with butter and other seasonings.
Wrap foil over the top and crimp closed.
Cook at 375° for 1 hour.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix peanut butter and powdered sugar until crumbly.
Spread on bottom of pie shell, saving a little to spread on top of pie. Prepare pudding using 1 3/4 cups milk.
Pour into pie shell.
Top with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle remaining crumbs on top.
Chill. Pudding may also be prepared using 2 cups milk according to package directions.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Grease an oblong pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients, except the marshmallow cream and frosting.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes.
Spread marshmallow cream over hot cake, then spread on chocolate frosting.

title: chip dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate.
Serve with chips.

title: cecilia's flour tortilla
directions: Mix dry ingredients in a large bowl.
Using a pastry cutter or fork, cut in the shortening.
Add warm water a little at a time until dough is soft and sticky.
Knead the dough for a few minutes. Pull off pieces of the dough to form about 12 small balls.	Let them rest for about 10 minutes.
It is a good idea to dust each ball (as well as your working surface) with a little flour just before you roll them out.

title: marshmallow refrigerator loaf
directions: Cut marshmallows in quarters and pour water over them.
Add Eagle Brand, chopped nut meats, chopped dates and cracker crumbs. Blend thoroughly; form into roll or loaf about 6-inches long and 3-inches in diameter.
Wrap in wax paper.
Chill in refrigerator 12 hours or longer.
To serve, cut in slices.
May be garnished with whipped cream.
(Loaf will keep moist for several days.) Serves 10.

title: cornbread casserole
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine remaining ingredients in large bowl; add melted oleo.
Mix together.
Return mixture to buttered pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 60 minutes. Freezes well.

title: turkey crunch casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except chow mein noodles.
Pour into a buttered casserole dish.
Sprinkle noodles on top.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.
Great for using up holiday leftover turkey.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Boil squash and onions in unsalted water for 5 minutes.
Mix soup and sour cream together.
Drain squash and onions; stir into soup.
Add sour cream.
Add melted butter to stuffing; sprinkle over bottom of greased 12 x 7 x 2-inch pan.
Spoon on vegetable mixture.
Cover with remaining stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: arlene's old kentucky jam cake
directions: In a large mixing
bowl,
cream butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs; beat in blackberry jam and cherry preserves.

title: chili dip
directions: Chop pepper.
Mix with ground beef and brown.
Drain off grease. Add cream cheese, tomato paste, Chili-O mix and 1/2 cup water.
Cook slowly or put into a crock-pot.
Add more water, if necessary. Serve with taco chips.

title: coffee cake
directions: Mix together the first 4 ingredients. Spread in large pan sprayed with Pam. Mix the cream cheese, confectioners sugar and eggs and spread on top of cake batter. Spread the pecans on top. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: seven layer cookies
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 12-inch pan, then sprinkle crushed graham crackers.
Add coconut; sprinkle around.
Then sprinkle on butterscotch and milk chocolate chips.
Add Eagle Brand milk, then sprinkle 1 cup or more nuts on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: pasta with fresh vegetables
directions: Cook and stir vegetables, garlic and Italian seasoning in oil in large skillet over medium heat, 3 to 4 minutes or until crisp and tender.
Add linguine; toss.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Serve hot.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Rinse and drain mushrooms.
Remove stems from mushrooms and save the caps.
Chop the stems finely and saute with the garlic in 4 tablespoons butter.
Add the bread crumbs, cheese, salt and pepper.
Briefly saute the mushroom caps in 3 tablespoons butter.
Stuff the caps with the bread crumb mixture and place in a buttered shallow baking dish.
Drizzle 1 tablespoon melted butter over mushrooms.
Bake until very hot, approximately 15 minutes.

title: angel food delight
directions: Tear angel food cake into bite size pieces.
Mix milk with vanilla pudding according to box.
Mix in sour cream.
Pour over angel food pieces in large dish (oblong).
Sprinkle pecans and marshmallows over pudding mixture. Spoon pie filling over this and chill.

title: colonial nine bean soup
directions: *Cover beans with water and soak overnight. Drain. Add 2 quarts water** and ham, onion, garlic and salt. Cover and bring to a boil. Simmer until tender, about 1 1/2 hours. Add tomatoes and simmer 30 minutes.

title: stella d'oro puffs
directions: Prepare puffs by cutting in half.
Set aside.
Drain crushed pineapple leaving a little juice.
Mix Cool Whip and cream cheese together in bowl about one minute at medium speed.
Add crushed pineapple and blend at low speed for one minute.
Place filling with tablespoon onto bottom layer of puffs.
Replace tops. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Spread 1/2 of batter in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake 5 minutes at 350°.
Melt in another pan the caramels and 1/3 cup evaporated milk.
Pour over baked batter. Sprinkle the chopped pecans and chocolate chips over the caramel mixture.
Drop blotches of remaining batter on top.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.
Cut into squares.

title: d.u.m.m. breakfast pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease glass pie plate (10-inch).
Cook sausage and onion in a skillet; stir frequently until fully cooked and drain.
Mix sausage, potatoes and 1 cup of cheese in pie plate.

Beat remaining ingredients except 1/4 cup cheese with wire whisk or hand beater until smooth; pour over sausage mixture. Bake 40 minutes or until golden brown and knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Sprinkle 1/4 cup cheese on top; bake 2 minutes to melt cheese.

title: molasses oat bran cookies
directions: In a large bowl, cream the sugar, Butter Buds, molasses and Egg Beaters.
In another bowl, mix together the flour, oats, oat bran, baking soda, cinnamon, ginger and cloves.
Mix contents of both bowls into 1 large bowl.
Place in the refrigerator for about 30 minutes to chill.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Spray nonfat cooking spray on cookie sheet.
Dip the dough by tablespoon onto the cookie sheet.
Bake 7 to 10 minutes or until set and golden brown. Yields 8 dozen cookies.

title: martha's chicken
directions: Cook chicken breasts until fork-tender.
Cook stuffing according to directions.
Shred chicken.
Layer the rest of the ingredients in order in an oblong baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until bubbly.

title: picnic brownies
directions: Mix flour, baking soda, salt and margarine.
Add in sugar, eggs and vanilla; mix until well blended.
Add nuts and chocolate chips.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool and cut.

title: snack potatoes
directions: Cut red potatoes in 3/8-inch cubes.
Fill a 1-quart pot to 2/3 capacity.
Put black pepper until solid black.
Put red pepper until solid red.
Cook in oleo until done.
(I can't believe it!). Eat while watching T.V.

title: ribollita(servings:  8)
directions: Ribollita is a wonderful soup you can cook all day.
The longer you cook it, the better it tastes.
It keeps in the refrigerator for several days and may be frozen.
Use any vegetables you like in any amount and combination.
There are no measurements and you can't make a mistake.

title: old fashion molasses taffy pull
directions: Mix molasses, sugar and vinegar.
Cook at 270° or soft ball stage.
Stir occasionally to prevent burning.
Remove from heat and add butter, soda and salt.
Stir just enough to blend.
Pour into buttered pan.
When cool enough to handle, pull until light in color.

title: italian wedding cake frosting
directions: Cream sugar and Spry; add butter together and mix well.
Cook together flour and milk, then add to the creamed mixture, a spoonful at a time.
Beat at high speed; add salt.

title: chicken rockefeller
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients, stirring well; set aside. Combine breadcrumbs and Parmesan cheese; set aside. Place each chicken breast between 2 sheets of wax paper; flatten to 1/4-inch thickness using a meat mallet or rolling pin. Sprinkle with pepper. Place spinach mixture evenly in center of each chicken breast. Fold long sides of chicken over spinach mixture; fold ends over and secure with a wooden pick. Roll chicken in breadcrumb mixture and place in a lightly greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish. Sprinkle with remaining breadcrumb mixture and drizzle with butter. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes

title: tangy potato salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
After thoroughly mixed, place in a large bowl.
Smooth top of salad.
Garnish with sliced, hard-boiled eggs.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: microwave fish fillets almondine
directions: Toast almonds in microwave 5 to 7 minutes.
Melt butter and blend with salt and pepper.
Coat fillets in butter and arrange around a 2-quart glass dish.
Sprinkle with lemon juice and cover with wax paper.
Cook 6 to 8 minutes, rotating dish 1/4 turn halfway through cooking time.
Rest for 5 minutes.
Top with toasted almonds and serve with lemon slices.
Yields 6 servings.

title: egg casserole
directions: Brown the bacon.
Butter a rectangular Pyrex dish with butter. Layer bottom of dish with cheese. Beat eggs and milk together. Pour over cheese. Add 4 slices of crumbled bacon. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Crumble rest of the bacon on top.
Bake 10 more minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes, then slice.

title: carol's cocktail wieners
directions: Mix chili sauce, grape jelly and soup mix together in crock-pot.
Spray with Pam first.
Add wieners and stir until coated.
Cook on low for 4 to 6 hours.

title: creamy pineapple salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserve juice and add water to make 1 1/3 cups.
Bring to a boil.
Place jello in bowl and add boiling liquid.
Stir to dissolve.
Cool to thicken slightly.
Whip cream and add sugar.
Fold into gelatin mixture.
Stir in pineapple and cottage cheese.
Chill.

title: strawberries jubilee(easy and elegant -- good for after formal dinner)
directions: Drain washed strawberries on toweling; set aside.
In chafing dish, heat butter until bubbly.
Add sugar, water, lemon peel and liqueur.
Stir over high heat until sugar dissolves and mixture is syrupy (2 or 3 minutes).
Warm brandy; ignite and pour over syrup. When flame dies, stir in 1 scoop of the ice cream until melted. Add berries and poach one minute, continually spooning sauce over berries.
Spoon remaining ice cream into dessert dishes.
Top with berries and sauce.
Serve at once.
Serves 6.

title: pineapple sheet cake
directions: Mix sugar, flour, soda and salt.
Add eggs, oil and pineapple. Spread in greased and floured sheet pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Put first 3 ingredients in greased casserole.
Top with stuffing mix.
Pour 1/4 cup melted butter and 3/4 cup hot water over all.
Bake 20 minutes or until heated through.

title: shrimp de jonghe
directions: Melt butter; add garlic, parsley, paprika, pepper and wine. Mix together; stir in bread crumbs.
Place shrimp in a casserole. Spread butter mix over.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until crumbs brown.
Sprinkle with snipped parsley.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cheesecake ice cream
directions: Mix ingredients, then freeze.

title: graham cracker goodies
directions: Bring butter and brown sugar to boil, take off heat and add pecans.
Spread aluminum foil on cookie sheet; spray with Pam. Spread graham crackers over aluminum foil; pour mixture over crackers.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.

title: seafood salad
directions: Cut sea legs into pieces.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Great on crackers or pita pockets.

title: swedish apple pie
directions: Grease
well
one 9-inch deep pie pan.
Spread with pie mix. Sprinkle
with
cinnamon,
sugar and pecans.
Set aside. In mixing bowl, mix
oleo and eggs.
Add sugar, flour and salt which have been
mixed
together.
Spread over apples and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until brown.

title: mandarin orange jello salad
directions: Prepare Jell-O; dissolve 1 cup boiling water and 1 cup pineapple juice.
Add all fruit, add sherbet.
Stir until dissolved.
Pour over cheese mixture.
Refrigerate until firm and cut.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Make Jell-O in bowl as directed on package.
Refrigerate. When it starts to set, add other ingredients.
Chill for several hours.
This recipe goes great with turkey or roasted chicken. People who usually will not eat cranberries will enjoy this salad!

title: pork casserole
directions: Wash and drain sauerkraut in a heavy pot.
Fry the chops and sausage until well done.
Set aside, pouring out fat, but don't wash pot.
Add sauerkraut and all other ingredients, stirring well.
Mix in sausage.
Lay chops over the rest in the pot, arranging layers.
Simmer on the top of the stove for 1 hour or more.
(Do not use salt.)

title: santa's whiskers
directions: Cream margarine and sugar, blend in milk and flavoring.
Stir in flour, cherries and nuts.
Form into roll.
Roll in coconut. Wrap and chill overnight.
Slice and bake on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375 degrees for 12 minutes.
Yields 5 dozen.

title: pecan glaze
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Spread on cake.
Top with whole pecans.

title: creamy orange and pineapple salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Add water to juice to make 1 cup.
Heat to boil.
Add boiling liquid to gelatin and cream cheese; beat with beater until smooth.
Cool, stirring occasionally.
Whip cream.
Fold cream, grated carrot and pineapple into cooled gelatin.
Pour into individual molds.
Chill until firm.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: country-fried steak with onions
directions: Pound steak with meat mallet.
Cut into serving pieces.
Heat oil.
Combine flour, salt and pepper.
Cover both sides of steak pieces with flour.
Slowly brown the steak in hot oil, turning once.
Lower the heat; add onion and brown a few minutes.
Add water.
Cover and simmer 1 hour.
Add more water, if needed.

title: olive puffs
directions: Combine the margarine, cheese and flour, using hands if necessary.
Chill dough 15 to 20 minutes.
Mold 1/2 teaspoon dough around olives.
Chill overnight and bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: cheese cake
directions: Set oven at 350°.
Mix together the graham crackers, melted butter and 1 tablespoon sugar.
Mix well and pat into a 9-inch round or spring-form pan.

title: cheesy vegetable casserole
directions: In the vegetables you need approximately 3 to 4 pounds, either frozen or fresh.
Mix and spread all ingredients over vegetables. Place in oven at 350° until vegetables are cooked and cheese is melted.

title: veggie bars
directions: Press rolls out on a cookie sheet with fingers.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Mix the mayonnaise, cream cheese and Hidden Valley together.
Spread on cool dough.
Chop and spread on top the remaining ingredients.
Put in refrigerator just so things stay together overnight.
This recipe is for a small cookie sheet. Enjoy!

title: green congealed salad
directions: Soften cream cheese to room temperature.
Cream the Jell-O and cream cheese together and add boiling water. Dissolve well.
Put mayonnaise in bowl. Add a little of the Jell-O mixture.
Mix well. Add rest of Jell-O mixture.
Add nuts and fruit cocktail. Refrigerate and let "set."

title: fruit cake
directions: Chop fruit and mix in pecans.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt over fruit and nuts.
Mix well.
Mix sugar and eggs until thick.
Pour over mixture of fruit and pecans; mix well.
Line tube pans with waxed paper and grease.
Bake at 275° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Makes 3 cakes.

title: mallow-whipped sweet potatoes
directions: Combine potatoes, 1 cup marshmallows, butter, juice and cinnamon.
Mix well.
Spoon into 1-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with remaining marshmallows and boil until lightly browned.
Makes 6 servings.

title: fettuccini
directions: Saute onion and mushrooms in margarine.
Crumble softened cream cheese over vegetables.
Cook with Parmesan and milk until cream cheese melts.
Pour over fettucini or serve separately. Delicious.

title: congealed cranberry salad
directions: Mix jello with 1 cup boiling water.
When dissolved, add 1 cup cold water.
Mix all other ingredients.
Congeal.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Store in refrigerator in airtight container.
Use for grilling chicken or pork.

title: tortilla soup
directions: Do not drain cans-combine all ingredients and cook for 15 minutes.
Serve over tortilla chips and top with grated cheese.

title: reuben dip
directions: Chop corned beef into small pieces. Drain and chop sauerkraut into small pieces. Mix corned beef, sauerkraut, Swiss cheese and Thousand Island dressing together well. Place in an ungreased casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serve warm.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: claudine's brownies
directions: Mix cocoa, cooking oil and vanilla by hand.
Add remaining ingredients and stir until everything is mixed.
Mixture is thick. Bake at 350° in a 9 x 11-inch greased pan for 30 to 35 minutes. Cool slightly; cut in squares but leave in pan until completely cool.
Great for picnics.
Can frost if you like.

title: zucchini bread
directions: In a large bowl, mash the margarine with the back of a fork. Mix in the sugar.
Add the eggs, water and vanilla and stir until the batter is smooth.
Stir in the zucchini, walnuts and raisins. In a medium size bowl, combine the flours, baking soda, baking powder, salt, cloves, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add the flour mixture to the zucchini mixture and fold the 2 mixtures together gently. Pour the batter into a greased loaf pan.
Bake for about 1 hour at 350°.

title: kenny's mashed taters
directions: Peel and cube potatoes; boil until very soft.
Drain water. Mix milk, butter, parsley, cheese and potatoes with electric beater until well mixed to a creamy texture.

title: stove top swiss steak
directions: Flour and brown steaks.
Add ingredients on top of browned steaks.
Simmer for 1 hour and serve.

title: peach delight
directions: Mix and spread in a 9 X 12 inch baking pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes. Cool.

title: peach delight
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Generously grease and flour 2 round cake pans (8 or 9 x 1/2-inch).

title: lemon-coconut bars
directions: Mix ingredients.
Put in greased and floured jelly roll pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: chocolate velvet cake
directions: Combine chocolate morsels and 1/4 cup water in saucepan.
Stir over low heat until melted and smooth. Remove from heat. Sift flour, soda and salt together. Set aside.
Combine sugar, butter and vanilla in a bowl.
Beat until well blended. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Blend in melted chocolate mixture. Stir in flour mixture alternately with 1 cup water.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 9-inch layer cake pans (you can use a Bundt cake pan, if desired).
Bake in a 375° oven for 30 to 35 minutes (may need longer if using Bundt pan).
Cool.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Peel and slice squash.
Cook in small amount of water with onion, salt and sugar until tender.
Drain.
Mix eggs and soup with margarine.
Add more salt if you like.
Put in casserole and bake in 400° oven for 10 to 15 minutes.
Add cheese and crumbs. Return to oven and brown.

title: cold carrot salad
directions: Cook carrots, drain and set aside.
Cool.
Dice green pepper; slice 3 small onions.

title: shipwreck
directions: Place in layers in casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours with lid on.
Remove lid last 1/2 hour.

title: gourmet potatoes
directions: Peel and boil potatoes until soft on outside, but firm inside. Let cool.
Grate potatoes and onion, mix with other ingredients and place in greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle with crushed cornflakes or bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: seasoned mixed nuts
directions: Melt butter and add onion salt, seasoned salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Stir well.
Add nuts and stir until well coated. Microwave on High, uncovered, for 4 minutes, stirring every minute.
Drain on paper towel and serve warm.

title: watermelon rind pickles
directions: Add lime to enough water to cover rings.
Soak three hours. Rinse thoroughly.
Cook rinds in boiling water 20 to 25 minutes or until tender.

title: sausage and tortellini
directions: Cut sausage, peppers, onions and mushrooms into 1-inch chunks. Saute sausage until they start to turn brown.
Add peppers, onions and mushrooms; cook until onions start to go limp. Transfer to large crock-pot, including any juices that have generated.
Add wine, tomatoes, tomato sauce, spices and minced garlic.
Cook the better part of the day on low.
About 1 hour before serving, raise head and add tortellini.
Sprinkle with cheese to serve.

title: pear turnovers
directions: Roll out the dough to 1/8-inch thickness; cut out four 6-inch circles.
Brush the edges with egg wash.
Slice the pears very thin; add sugar and 2 or 3 turns from the peppermill.
Toss the mixture in a bowl.
Divide the pear mixture in equal amounts and place in center of each dough circle.
Fold the top over the bottom; press the edge and seal.
Brush egg wash over the turnovers and bake at 425° for 20 minutes.
Serve warm with creme fraiche on the side.

title: pizza sauce
directions: Mix well; spread on pizza crust and add your favorite toppings.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Stir milk, lemon juice and Cool Whip together.
Add strawberries and nuts.
Refrigerate for 3 hours before serving.

title: pecan pie
directions: Boil syrup and sugar together for 2 minutes. Beat eggs.
Put butter, vanilla and salt in eggs.
Pour hot syrup over eggs and beat while pouring.
Add nuts.
Pour in pie shell.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: ham and yams
directions: Put butter and onion into a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Place in microwave for 2 minutes on High.
After 1 minute, stir lightly. Blend flour into onion and butter; stir in pineapple juice.
Cook, uncovered, in microwave 1 minute on High (or until thick).
Stir crushed pineapple, brown sugar and ham into sauce.
Place mixture in center of an 8-inch glass dish.
Put sliced yams around outer edge.
Cover with wax paper.
Heat in microwave oven 6 to 8 minutes on High.

title: sante fe rice salad
directions: Place rice in a large bowl.
Cut up all the ingredients.
Add onions, tomato, salsa, beans, peppers, cinnamon and cumin.
Stir gently, but combine well.
Refrigerate about an hour, or a little less, before serving time.
The rice takes on a rosy glow from the salsa, making this an attractive and mildly spicy dish to serve with other southwestern style food.

title: ham barbecue
directions: Heat ham in butter in a large skillet.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer until well blended.

title: make ahead potatoes
directions: Combine cooked potatoes, cream cheese, sour cream and onion powder in large mixing bowl.
Mash potatoes until fluffy.
(Add a small amount of milk if potatoes are too thick.)
Spread in buttered 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Refrigerate until ready to use. To bake, drizzle melted margarine over top and place in 350° oven for one hour.

title: french pudding
directions: Cream butter and powdered sugar.
Add eggs; mix well.
In a well-greased pan, put a layer of vanilla wafer crumbs, a layer of butter mixture, a layer of fruit and nuts, then a layer of whipped cream.
Repeat layers of each.
Sprinkle chopped nuts on top. Chill.

title: grated potato casserole(yields 4 to 6 servings)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 2-quart casserole.
Put all ingredients in blender in order listed:
milk, eggs, salt, pepper, cheese, butter, pepper, onion and potatoes.
Cover and run on high just until potatoes are through blades (don't overblend).
Pour into greased casserole and bake 1 hour.

title: creamy beef dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Chill.
Serve as dip with assorted raw vegetables or hollow out whole rye or pumpernickel bread loaf.

title: swiss steak
directions: Flour
meat and brown on both sides
in
shortening
in electric skillet at 400°.
In saucepan, put all other ingredients and
bring to a boil.
Turn frypan back
to
Pour heated mixture over meat and simmer about 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: russian tea cakes
directions: Mix first three ingredients thoroughly.
Then sift together and add flour and salt.
Mix in nuts.
Chill dough.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased sheet (cookies do not spread). Bake until set, but not brown.

title: old-fashioned blackberry cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Place stick of butter in a 9 x 13-inch flat pan and place in oven to melt.
In the meantime, mix together the dry ingredients.
Stir in milk, beating until smooth.
Remove baking pan from oven and pour in batter.
Spoon fruit and juice evenly over the batter.
Return to oven and bake for 35 to 40 minutes until top is lightly browned.
Serve hot or cold with whipped cream.

title: orange-pineapple-cheese delight
directions: Put drained pineapple, sugar and lemon juice in saucepan over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Bring to boil and stir in jello until dissolved.
Remove from heat.
Add mixed juice.
Chill until it starts to gel.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex pan.
Chill until set.
Cut in squares to serve on a lettuce leaf.

title: broccoli-cauliflower casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and cauliflower in boiling water for 5 minutes; drain.
Melt 1/2 of butter.
Add flour, salt and pepper.
Add milk; cook and stir until bubbly.
Blend in cream cheese.
Combine with vegetables in a 1 1/2-quart casserole; top with cheese. Sprinkle with crumbs tossed with remaining butter.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: tuna noodle soup
directions: Boil bag of egg noodles.
Drain. Mix milk, butter, soup and tuna in a
pan.
Heat on medium heat for 3 minutes or until it is at a slight boil, mixing as it heats. Add mixture to noodles. Serve hot.

title: pumpernickel bread
directions: Mix and cook corn meal and 1/2 cup water.
Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup water.
To the corn meal, add potatoes, molasses, butter, salt, sugar and yeast.
Combine flours.
Add flour to mixture and work dough until it no longer sticks to your hands.
It may take more or less flour.
Divide into thirds.
Place in 3 greased pans. Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 375°.
Best in round pans.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: In heavy saucepan, stir cream and butter until butter melts and cream barely comes to boil. Stir in sugars until dissolved. Reduce heat. Briskly whisk in salt and cocoa.
Remove from heat. Serve immediately or store in glass jar or covered non-plastic container.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown the beef and drain grease.
Add kidney beans and heat. In a large bowl, combine lettuce, tomatoes, cheese and salad dressing.
Stir in the beef and kidney beans.
Add Doritos chips to the salad mixture at the last minute to maintain crispness. Serves as a main course.
Add salsa or sour cream on the side.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut broccoli and cauliflower into bite size pieces; no stems. Fry bacon until crisp; drain fat, cut into small pieces and add to bowl with broccoli and cauliflower.
Add all other ingredients to bowl.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients together; pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan that has been sprayed with nonstick cooking spray.
Bake until done, about 35 to 45 minutes.

title: zesty potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water till tender.
Drain.
Add veggies to potatoes.
Add salt to taste.
Stir in horseradish, vinegar, and mayonnaise.
Cover tightly and chill.
Keep cold. Makes 6 cups.

title: smothered vegetable cheese omelette
directions: In medium nonstick pan, heat 2/3 teaspoon oil. Add mushrooms. Saute 3 minutes. Add peppers. Cook 3 minutes. Add onions, tomato, salsa and cornstarch. (Mix cornstarch with a little water to dissolve it before adding to pan.) Heat 1/3 teaspoon oil in second nonstick skillet.

title: broccoli bake
directions: Cook broccoli and drain; place in baking dish with margarine, cheese and crackers crumbled.
Mix well.
Top with more crackers and cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mexican surprise
directions: Saute chicken and onion in margarine.
Heat soup; add picante sauce, chicken and onion.
Pour over tortillas.
Top with cheese. Bake at 350° until cheese is bubbly.

title: deviled ham spread
directions: Blend all ingredients and spread on crackers.
Broil until cheese is melted.

title: autumn applesauce
directions: In saucepan, combine pineapple and sugar.
Bring to a boil; cook for 3 minutes.
Add jello.
Stir until dissolved.
Add cream cheese.
Stir until completely dissolved; cool.
Fold in apples, nuts and topping.
Pour into a 9-inch square pan.
Chill until firm.
Cut in squares; serve on lettuce.

title: lobster-in-shell soup
directions: Partially thaw frozen lobster.
Split lobster tails in half lengthwise.
Cut in half crosswise to make 8 portions.
In large covered saucepan, cook onion, green pepper and celery in butter or margarine until tender, but not brown.
Add chicken broth, undrained tomatoes, parsley, 1/4 teaspoon salt and dash of pepper. Bring to a boil.
Add cooked pasta.
Reduce heat.
Add lobster and fresh spinach.
Cook about 5 minutes longer or until lobster is done.
Makes 4 main dish servings.

title: marinated shrimp
directions: Boil shrimp in celery tops, pickling spices, salt, onions and bay leaves for 5 minutes.
When cooled, pour marinade of canola oil, vinegar, capers, celery seed and Tabasco over the shrimp and onions.
Refrigerate for 24 hours.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain juice from fruit and reserve 2 cups of juice.
Mix fruit, except bananas.
Heat juice and pudding until thick.
Pour over fruit.
Chill for several hours.
Add bananas just before serving.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Spread cooked broccoli in a shallow baking dish.
Add chicken. Stir milk and soup together and pour over chicken and broccoli. Sprinkle cheese on top and add paprika.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until bubbly.
Serve hot.

title: annie's german endive potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes whole.
Drain and cool.
Peel, cut up in small cubes.
Add bacon and bacon drippings, salt, sugar, onions, pepper and 1 cup endive.
Combine mayonnaise or sour cream, vinegar and milk or water.
Gently stir in potato mixture.
Just before serving, add second cup endive.

title: maple sugar cakes
directions: Mix ingredients together. Bake at 350°. Top with Maple Fudge Frosting.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Cream first 2 ingredients together.
Add pineapple and nuts; mix well.
Fold in Cool Whip, bananas and strawberries.
Mix well and chill.
Can be frozen.

title: baked rice custard pudding
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Heat milk in saucepan until almost boiling.
Remove.
Stir in sugar mixture.
Beat eggs until foamy.
Stir 1/4 hot mix into eggs.
Add remaining.
Stir in rice, raisins and vanilla.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart baking dish, coated with cooking spray.
Sprinkle nutmeg.
Place in pan of water. Bake until knife comes out clean.
After 30 minutes, stir.
Bake approximately 1 hour.

title: soft pretzels
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in large mixing bowl.
Stir in salt, sugar and 2 cups of flour.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in enough remaining flour to make dough easy to handle.
Turn dough onto lightly floured surface; knead until smooth and elastic, about 5 minutes.
Place in greased bowl; turn greased side up. Cover; let rise until double, 45 to 60 minutes.

title: meat loaf patties(my favorite way to fix hamburger)
directions: May use 1/2 cup ketchup for moisture if needed.

title: chicken continental
directions: Saute chicken, mushrooms and garlic in oil for 2 to 3 minutes. Add remaining ingredients except rice and bring to a full boil. Stir in rice; remove from heat.
Cover and let stand for 5 minutes.
Serve with soy sauce or chicken gravy.
Makes 4 servings.

title: greek meat rolls(souzoukakia)
directions: Mix beef, bread, onion, garlic, egg, sugar, salt, cumin, pepper and water until well blended and firm.
With hands moistened in cold water, shape rounded tablespoonfuls of meat mixture into 3-inch long fingerlike rolls.
Coat rolls lightly with flour.

title: guacamole
directions: Peel and pit the avocados; mash them with a fork while blending in lemon juice.
Stir in remaining ingredients.

title: jake louthan's hot rolls
directions: In a large pan, bring sugar, Crisco and milk to a boil and then cool to lukewarm. Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
Add to milk mixture, then add 4 cups flour.
Let set 2 hours or until double in size. Add another 4 cups flour which has been sifted with baking powder, salt and soda.
Next, add only enough to knead and put in a greased bowl in the refrigerator.
Punch dough down when it rises.
Keeps about 1 week. Bake rolls at 425° about 12 minutes.

title: salami
directions: Mix all in a bowl.
Cover and refrigerate.
On the second and third days, remove from the refrigerator, mix well and return to refrigerator.
On the fourth day, form into three long or six short rolls.
Bake on a rack in a pan 6 hours at 150°.
Turn every 1 1/2 hours.
Freezes well.

title: creamy rice pudding(serves 40)
directions: Heat 1 gallon of milk in a large pot, uncovered, on medium heat.
When milk is very hot, add sugar.
Dissolve and stir with a wooden spoon.
Add salt and stir.
When milk comes to a full, foaming boil, add rice, lower heat a little, cover and stir every few minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix butter and sugar until creamy, add eggs one at a time. Add vanilla, flour, baking soda and salt. Mix until incorporated, but careful not to over-mix. Stir in mashed banana and sour cream. Pour into greased bread pan and bake in preheated 350° oven for 50 to 55 minutes, or until toothpick in the center of the loaf comes out clean.

title: holiday punch
directions: Make ice cubes by filling tray approximately 1/2 full of 7-Up. Add a maraschino cherry in each cube.
Freeze.
Add 7-Up to fill tray almost to the top.
Refreeze.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 325° for 30 minutes. Take out and cool.

title: senate navy bean soup
directions: While beans soak, bring ham hocks to boil in 4 quarts water over high heat.
Lower heat and simmer 2 to 3 hours.
In large soup pot, saute onions in 2 tablespoons butter.
Add celery and mashed garlic, stirring.
Add potatoes and 2 cups water from ham hocks.
Cover and cook 15 to 20 minutes.
Add beans, ham hocks, bay leaf and all liquid from beans and ham.
Cover and cook slowly until beans are tender, about 1 hour, adding water if needed. Remove hocks; cut meat from bones in bite size pieces and return to pot.
Salt and pepper to taste. Remove bay leaf.
Add parsley.
