title: sauteed squash with onions and tomatoes
directions: For each serving, allow one squash and one tomato.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix together using hand and make into small balls.
Bake until brown in an ungreased pan about 12 minutes at 375°.
Makes about 40 balls.
May be frozen then baked.
Can be warmed in oven or microwave.

title: meat loaf and gravy
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
On a strip of heavy aluminum foil, mix beef and onion soup mix.
Form into loaf and pour undiluted soup over loaf.
Wrap loosely in foil.
Place on baking sheet.
Bake 1 hour and 20 minutes.
As loaf bakes, it makes its own gravy.

title: friendship soup
directions: Wash beans.
Cover with water and soak overnight.
Drain.
Add 2 quarts of water, ham, onion, garlic, salt and pepper.
Cover and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 2 to 3 hours, until beans are tender.
Add tomatoes and chilies and simmer 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: carrot-zucchini bars
directions: Cream margarine with sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla and orange rind.
Sift together dry ingredients and add to mixture.
Blend in carrots, zucchini and walnuts.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Frost with cream cheese icing.

title: merle lee's p.e.o. punch
directions: Can add sugar, if desired.
Chill before serving.

title: easy tuna casserole
directions: Saute celery.
In large bowl, mix water chestnuts, tuna, soup, sprouts and milk.
Add celery and mix again.
Put in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Put noodles on top and chopped onions on top of noodles.
Bake at 350° until hot, approximately 25 minutes. Very good served over rice.

title: party fish dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill well before serving. Serve with potato chips, assorted crackers or raw vegetables. Make ahead.
Makes 3 cups.

title: jackie's no-fail coconut icing
directions: Mix and place between split layers of Duncan Hines butter cake layers.
Cover sides and top.
Keep refrigerated.

title: apple cider pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift dry ingredients together and set aside.
Combine cider and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients, alternately with liquid.
Mix until well blended.
Bake in 10-inch Bundt or angel food pan, well greased.
Lightly sprinkle sides of pan with sugar.
Bake at 325° for 1
hour and 10 minutes.

title: green enchilada casserole
directions: Place the chicken in a large casserole.
Add remaining ingredients except cheeses and stir well.
Cover with cheese. Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cover the casserole so the cheese doesn't get too hard.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cotton mill mashed potatoes
directions: In the early days of the cotton mill, there was a potato bell which was run 30 minutes before the workers came home for dinner. This was a reminder for the person who was preparing the meat to start cooking the potatoes as they would be home soon.

title: buttered belgian endives
directions: Rub the butter over the bottom of a shallow flameproof casserole or skillet.
Trim off the bottoms and any damaged outer leaves of the endive and cut the heads into diagonal slices about 1-inch thick.
Put them in the pan with salt and pepper to taste, lemon juice and water.
Press a piece of buttered foil on top of the endive and cover with a lid.
Cook over low heat for 7 to 8 minutes or until the endive is tender.
Shake the pan occasionally. Sprinkle with the chopped parsley and serve.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except crackers and melted butter and put in pan.
Crush crackers and put on top.
Pour melted butter on crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: coffee cake
directions: Mix well, except the pie filling,
and spread 1/2 batter in an oblong greased pan (9 x 13-inch).
Add cherry pie filling on top, then add the rest of the batter.

title: mexican dip
directions: Season to taste and brown meat; drain.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Spoon mixture on 9-inch pie plate. Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Stir and continue to bake 5 minutes longer.
Serve with corn chips.

title: antipasto rollups
directions: Mix chopped eggs, tuna and mayonnaise.
Put heaping spoonful on slice of salami.
Roll up.
Stick with toothpick.
Attach cheese and olive by poking in tuna/egg mixture.

title: broccoli and cauliflower with lemon and garlic
directions: Slice tender stems of broccoli in thin rounds and break florets in small pieces.
Rinse broccoli and cauliflower in cold water; drain thoroughly.
Over medium high heat, saute garlic in oil and cook until golden.
Remove garlic and set aside.
Increase heat to high and add vegetables.
Stir-fry 2 minutes.
Add water and mix well.
Cover and cook until vegetables are crisp-tender, about 2 to 3 minutes.
Uncover and cook until remaining liquid evaporates.
Add salt and pepper.
Mix in garlic and lemon juice. Sprinkle with lemon zest.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: Combine chocolate bits, evaporated milk and butter in a small saucepan.
Cook over low heat until mixture is smooth and creamy. Combine other ingredients and gradually stir into chocolate mixture.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake in moderate oven (375°) for 40 minutes or until firm.
Cool pie completely before covering.

title: lentil cheese supper
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.

title: hamburger barley soup
directions: Brown meat and add all ingredients except carrots and potatoes.
Bring to a boil.
Let simmer 45 minutes. Add carrots and cook about 15 or 20 more minutes, then add potatoes and cook another 20 minutes or until vegetables are tender.

title: orange julius
directions: Blend in blender 10 to 15 seconds.
Serves 4.

title: orzo cooked in saffron broth
directions: In a medium saucepan, heat the broth to boiling.
Stir in the orzo and butter.
Cook, covered, over low heat until liquid is absorbed, about 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with scallions; serve at once.

title: escalloped eggplant
directions: In a Pyrex dish, arrange eggplant, onion and tomato slices in layers. Dribble half of the melted margarine over these slices. Sprinkle salt over slices. Cover and bake 20 minutes in a 450° oven. Remove from oven. Sprinkle cheese over dish; pour remaining margarine onto it and sprinkle with cracker crumbs and Parmesan cheese.
Return to oven, uncovered, and bake 10 minutes longer.

title: chinese chicken
directions: Saute onion, celery and oleo.
Add soup, broth, soy sauce, salt, pepper and chestnuts.
Add chicken.
Put in casserole. Sprinkle with noodles and cashews over top of casserole.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: creamy onion soup
directions: Cook sliced onions in margarine 3 or 4 minutes.
Add flour; cook a few minutes.
Add chicken broth, half and half, salt and pepper.
Cook slow until thickened, stirring often.

title: my mother's buns
directions: Scald milk and Crisco and cool.
Beat eggs; add salt, sugar and yeast.
Add cooled milk.
Add 2 cups of flour and beat.
Add 2 cups of flour and beat.
Place in refrigerator for 1 hour.
Shape, rise and bake.

title: sliced orange dip
directions: Blend all of the ingredients in a blender and chill one hour before serving.
Serve with strawberries, apple, melon, orange and pineapple slices.

title: chocolate chip cookie bar(for hungry children)
directions: Cream together first 5 ingredients.
Add flour and soda mix. Fold in chocolate chips.
Spread in a large jelly roll (12 x 17-inch) pan that you have greased.
Bake at 350° for 18 minutes or to touch.
Cool.
Cut in squares.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: caramel corn
directions: Mix together margarine, brown sugar and Karo syrup.
Boil for 5 minutes, stirring constantly. Remove from heat and add baking soda. Stir well.
Pour over popcorn and pecans.
Mix well until evenly coated.
Place on large baking sheet and bake 1 hour at 250°, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: reuben dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and heat until warm.
Serve with crackers.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix sugars, margarine, pumpkin and eggs together.
Mix flour, baking soda, cinnamon and nutmeg together. Add dry mixture to pumpkin mixture.
Mix well.
Drop teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Make the Jell-O, then set aside.
The flavor is your choice. In a large bowl, mix cranberries, juice from orange and sweeten with sugar to your satisfaction.
Add nuts, celery and grapes. Mix well.
Add slightly cooled jello.
Refrigerate until set.

title: round rye and dill dip
directions: Cut off the top and hollow out bread in bite size pieces. Chill bread pieces.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle nuts and coconut on bottom.
Prepare cake mix by directions on box and pour over top of nuts and coconut.
Melt butter and cream cheese together.
Add sugar and pour over cake batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all together and cook 6 hours.
Can use a crock-pot.

title: potato surprise
directions: Thaw hash browns at room temperature for 20 minutes.
Put into a covered 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
In a bowl, combine soup, milk, sour cream and 1 1/2 cups cheese.
Mix with whisk.
Pour over potatoes; sprinkle with the rest of the cheese.
Dot with butter; bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: della's company pie
directions: Mix raisins, nuts and vinegar and let stand.
Combine butter, sugar and eggs and beat until thick.
Beat in spices and salt; stir in raisin mixture.
Turn mixture into unbaked shell and bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: monkey cake
directions: Boil butter and brown sugar.
Cut biscuits in quarters.
Mix white sugar and cinnamon in a covered bowl.
Drop cut biscuits in sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Shake to cover.
Layer nuts and biscuits in a Bundt pan until all are used.
Pour brown sugar mixture over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes and turn out of pan.

title: grandma perkins chocolate chip cookies
directions: Melt butter and add eggs, vanilla, baking soda, salt, whiskey and sugars.
Mix well.
Add the remaining ingredients; mix and refrigerate for 1 hour.
Place dough by teaspoons on cookie sheet and bake until lightly brown at 350°.

title: jello salad
directions: Mix jello with water.
Add orange juice, crushed pineapple along with pineapple juice and mandarin oranges along with its juice to jello mixture.
Mix well and pour into dish.
Let jell for an hour or more.

title: hawaiian meat balls
directions: Mix well.
Make small balls.
Roll in flour.
Saute in shortening to cook.

title: whipping cream pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift flour and add alternately with cream (do not whip cream).
Add vanilla.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Place in cold oven.
Turn oven to 300° and bake 1 hour and 25 minutes.

title: quick tuna patties
directions: Drain water from tuna.
Add crackers, egg, parsley and onion. Mix thoroughly and refrigerate for at least 20 minutes.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: In a large bowl, put frozen peas.
Layer chopped onion, pepper, celery and cheese.
Add lettuce pieces.
Spread mayonnaise on top of lettuce.
Sprinkle sugar over mayonnaise.
Refrigerate overnight.
Toss before serving.
Sprinkle with bacon bits.

title: broccoli cheese casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: almond joy cake
directions: Bake a chocolate cake mix in a 9 x 13-inch pan or larger. While warm, pour 6 to 8 ounces cream of coconut over the top. Punch holes in cake.
Heat 30 marshmallows, 1 cup evaporated milk and 1 cup sugar until melted.
Add the coconut.
Pour over cake while hot.

title: cucumber dip
directions: Place onion in blender; blend on low for 30 to 40 seconds; add cucumber.
Blend on low speed until fine.
Add cottage cheese and salt; blend at medium speed for 1 to 2 minutes.
Chill until serving time.
Serve with vegetables, chips or crackers.

title: cream cheese dip
directions: Rinse dried beef and drain.
Chop beef and onions very fine. Mix all ingredients together and chill 2 hours or overnight. Serve with crackers.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Brown meat.
Add onions and cook until onions are clear.
Stir in seasoning and water; add next 3 ingredients.
Simmer 10 minutes. Spread about 3/4 cup sauce in a 9 x 13 pan.
Top with noodles, sauce and cheese.
Repeat layers.
Bake uncovered 30 minutes at 350°.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Serve with sour cream and black olives.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples in greased 6 x 10-inch baking dish.
Mix together with fork until crumbly and sprinkle over the apples a mixture of the flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and egg.
Pour butter over all.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes in 350° oven. Serve warm with vanilla ice cream.

title: cheese ball
directions: Empty onions into a bowl. Pour sherry over onions to cover good. Put in the refrigerator overnight. Let cream cheese get room temperature. Mix cheese, onions, meat and olives in large bowl together. Form a ball and place on plate in the refrigerator to harden back. Serve with wheat crackers.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix cream cheese, mayonnaise and Worcestershire sauce.
Add shrimp and onion.
Season to taste with Louisiana hot sauce.

title: squash casserolegroves, texas
directions: Pour all ingredients into pyrex dish.
Sprinkle cracker crumbs and bake at 400° for about 30 minutes.
The touch of garlic powder will give it a special taste.

title: black bean pie
directions: Brown onion, pepper and meat. Add olives, green chillies, salsa, black beans and chili powder. (I use about 1 tablespoon.) Line a large Pyrex bowl with 1 pie crust.
Layer with meat mix, tortilla, grated Colby and Jack cheese. End with another pie crust on top. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes and brown on top. Serves 4.

title: french-style potato salad
directions: Wash potatoes, slice, cook in boiling water to cover 12 to 15 minutes.
Drain; cool slightly.
Add wine, toss gently and let stand 10 minutes.
Combine olive oil and next 5 ingredients; stir well.
Pour over potatoes and toss gently.
Add onions and parsley.
Toss gently.
Serve while still warm.

title: easy tuna swiss pie
directions: Pierce pastry and bake 10 minutes at 375°.
In large bowl, toss together next three ingredients and spoon into pastry.
In bowl, stir together remaining ingredients and pour into pastry.
Bake 50 minutes or until knife comes out clean.

title: flan de coco(coconut flan; custard)
directions: Beat eggs. Add all other ingredients and beat well.
Pour in a baking dish (large or individual) with caramel sauce in bottom.

title: cinnamon raisin bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm water.
Stir in 1 3/4 cup warm water, 3 tablespoon sugar, salt, shortening and 3 1/2 cups flour. Beat smooth.
Mix in raisins and flour to handle.

title: pizza fondue
directions: Brown onion and meat in shortening in fondue pot at high. Reduce heat to medium.
Mix cornstarch and seasonings into pizza sauce; add sauce to mixture.
Stir well.
When mixture thickens and bubbles, add cheeses by thirds, stirring well after each addition.

title: ice cream salad
directions: Mix water and jello and cool.
Dissolve jello and ice cream. Mix all together and let chill.

title: triple cheese dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix until thoroughly blended.
Chill several hours before serving.
Serve with fresh vegetable dippers or crackers.
Makes 16 servings.

title: marie's jello salad
directions: Mix jello and water.
Add pineapple and strawberries.
Pour into large glass pan; let set.

title: pepperoni whip
directions: Grind pepperoni and blend thoroughly with cheese spread.
Fold in sour cream, relish and parsley.
Mix well.
Serve with crackers, thin rye bread and potato chips.

title: crabmeat dip
directions: Mix together and serve.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Heat butter in large sauce pan over medium heat.
Add onion and garlic.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Do not brown onions!
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer, stirring occasionally for 1 hour.

title: cherry thumbprint cookies
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients and roll dough into small balls (about 3 dozen), then put thumbprint into center of ball.
Put cherry into thumbprint.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Simmer chicken in 6 cups of water until thoroughly cooked (about 30 minutes).
Reserve broth.
Shred cooled chicken into bite size pieces.
Prepare stuffing according to package directions, using chicken broth instead of water.
Add butter. Combine soups and add to stuffing.
Add chicken and spread mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° until hot and bubbly (about 45 minutes).
Yields 6 servings.

title: seven layer chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken.
Save 1 cup broth.
Shred chicken thighs onto bottom of casserole.
Grate half of the block of cheese over the chicken.
Cook Stove Top stuffing per directions and layer over cheese.

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix ingredients together and chill.
Then form in balls. Place about 1 inch apart on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: meat marinade
directions: Mix well.
Store
in
refrigerator
until ready to use. Cover meat with sauce for several hours or overnight.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix the vanilla pudding with the milk until lumps are gone. Add the sour cream and orange juice concentrate.
Refrigerate for 2 hours.
Serve with sliced fruit of choice.

title: seafoam
directions: Mix sugar, syrup, water and vinegar and cook until it forms a soft ball.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Pour syrup over egg whites in slow stream, beating constantly.
Add vanilla.
When candy is nearly stiff, add pecans.
Using a spoon, beat until firm enough to spoon out on buttered wax paper.

title: "mounds" or "almond joys"
directions: Melt and remove butter from heat.
Add next 4 ingredients and mix well.
Add coconut and roll into balls.
Dip balls in melted chocolate chips and put on waxed paper to set or "thumbprint" almonds onto rolled coconut balls.
Let stand 10 minutes.

title: today's beef roast
directions: Spread open-faced hamburger buns with Miracle Whip, then spread with cottage cheese (small curd).
Spread 1 can tuna over cottage cheese.
Put under broiler until edges are getting brown and mixture is melting together.
You can use Cheez Whiz and cooked, crumbled bacon.

title: peach melba cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to package directions; add dry jello. Spray two 9-inch round cake pans with cooking spry and bake according to package directions. Let cool. Place one cake layer upside down on a platter; spread with 1/3 cup raspberry preserves. Place the second cake layer upside down over the bottom layer and spread the remaining 1/3 cup raspberry preserves over the top. Frost the top and sides with Cool Whip. Top with the peaches and serve. Keep chilled.

title: rice casserole
directions: Melt margarine in baking dish.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Bake at 350 degrees for 40 - 45 minutes.
Stir twice while baking.

title: chicken a la orange
directions: Coat chicken with mixture of flour, 1 teaspoon salt, garlic and paprika.
Saute almonds in butter or margarine until golden in a large frying pan. Remove from pan. Brown chicken in the same pan.
Place chicken in a baking pan.
Stir orange juice, rosemary, thyme and 1/2 teaspoon salt in pan.
Heat to boiling.
Pour over chicken. Cover.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
Sprinkle with almonds.
Serve with rice or wild rice.
Use orange sauce as gravy.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Add all ingredients together except cheese; pour half in a well-greased pan.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Pour in other half. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: amazin' raisin cake
directions: Grease 2 (9-inch) round cake pans.
Mix the first 10 items in a large bowl with mixer at low speed for 2 minutes, scraping sides of bowl frequently.
Batter will be very thick.
With spoon, stir in remaining ingredients; spoon into pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes; remove and cool.
Fill and frost with whipped cream.

title: red lobster cheese garlic biscuits
directions: Combine baking mix, cheese, and milk in a bowl. Mix with spoon until soft dough forms. Beat vigorously for 30 seconds. Drop by spoonfuls onto greased baking sheet. Bake at 450° for 8-10 minutes or until golden brown. Brush hot biscuits with mixture of margarine and garlic powder. Serve immediately.

title: applesauce cookies
directions: Mix together flour, baking powder and baking soda.
Cream shortening, ground cloves, cloves, nutmeg. salt, egg and cinnamon together.
Add to flour mixture.
Add applesauce, raisins and chopped walnuts.
Drop onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake in 400° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: roasted vegetable salad(meatless)
directions: Boil potato cubes for 5 minutes.
Drain.
In a bowl, toss potatoes, peppers, mushrooms, garlic, olive oil and rosemary, until well coated with rosemary and oil.
Spread vegetables on a broiler pan and sprinkle with salt and pepper to taste.
Broil for 10 to 12 minutes, until slightly crisped and browned on edges. Stir once or twice to insure even cooking.
Return to bowl and toss with vinegar.
Serve hot or at room temperature.

title: snowball cookies
directions: Mix margarine, 1/2 cup powdered sugar and vanilla.
Mix in flour, salt and nuts until dough holds together.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
You can put a chocolate chip, walnut or maraschino cherry half in the middle, if you like.
Place about 1 inch apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake until set, but not brown, about 10 to 12 minutes at 400°.
Roll in powdered sugar while warm. Cool, then roll in powdered sugar again.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: orange balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll into balls.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: old-fashion chicken n' dressing
directions: Cook a hen or fryer.
Cover with water.
Add salt.
Add more water as needed until done.
Add chicken bouillon cubes, if desired.
Save broth.
Bone chicken.
If you want, put chicken in your dressing.
Chip into small pieces.

title: daintie meringue cakes
directions: Cream butter and blend in sugar, egg and egg yolk.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to the butter mixture.
Pat dough into a 10 x 10-inch baking pan.
Beat brown sugar into beaten egg whites.
Fold in chocolate bits and nuts. Spread on dough in pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 minutes.
Cut into squares while warm.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: brownies
directions: Cream butter and sugar thoroughly; add vanilla and eggs.
Add combined cocoa and flour; beat well.
Add nutmeats.
Bake in buttered baking pans at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool; cut into squares.
(Use less sugar if brownies are frosted.)

title: crispy chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Put chicken in buttered casserole dish. Cover each cutlet with Swiss cheese.
Add mushrooms or celery. Mix soup and wine.
Pour over chicken and cheese.
Melt butter and combine with stuffing mix.
Top casserole with stuffing.
Bake for 35 to 45 minutes uncovered.

title: miki's potato salad
directions: Cut potatoes in quarters and boil in salted water until done. Add next 6 ingredients to warm potatoes, making sure potatoes are cut in small cubes.
Add mayonnaise and sprinkle with paprika. Garnish with parsley.

title: oyster dressing
directions: Wet French bread and croutons.
Put in bowl and chop pepper, onion and celery in small pieces.
Put in bowl.
Add the eggs and oysters. Mix with hands well.

title: corn fritters
directions: Add egg yolks to corn.
Sift together, flour, baking powder, sugar and salt.
Add to corn mixture.
Beat egg whites stiffly and add to mixture.
Fry in margarine.

title: fried pie dough
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Chill overnight.
Perfect pie crust every time!

title: coconut pie
directions: Pour milk over coconut; set aside.
Cream margarine and sugar in mixing bowl.
Add eggs and beat.
Add coconut mixture and vanilla.
Pour in pie shell.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 minutes or until golden brown.

title: chicken and rice casserole(microwave)
directions: Boil chicken.
When cool, dice.
Mix all ingredients together. Pour into microwave dish; microwave for 25 to 30 minutes (until rice is soft), stirring every 5 minutes.

title: custard pie
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, salt, almond and vanilla.
Stir in scalded milk.
Pour into pie shell.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until knife comes out clean.

title: cranberry salad
directions: In a bowl, dissolve jello in boiling water.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate until sets up.

title: springela
directions: Mix ingredients.
Chill 2 hours.
Roll out using cake flour. Put on wax paper.
Let stand 2 hours.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 350° for 20 minutes.
Watch baking time.
Just let them set slightly brown.
Let stand 2 hours.
Cover with a cloth.

title: barbara's punch
directions: Mix together in punch bowl and serve.

title: mincemeat
directions: Wipe the meat with a cloth and cut in 1-inch cubes.
Cover with boiling water and simmer, covered, about 2 hours or until tender. Remove the meat and measure 1 cup of stock.
Put meat and suet through the food chopper.
Combine apples, raisins, currants, citron, candied orange and lemon rinds, sugar, salt, molasses, beef stock, cider, spices and nuts in a large pot.
Mix well.
Bring the mixture slowly to a boil and simmer slowly about 1 1/2 hours.
Add lemon juice and brandy.
Pack at once into hot, sterilized jars. Seal.
Cool and store in a cool place.
Makes about 5 quarts.
Use as pie filling or relish dish.

title: popcorn delights
directions: Mix sugar, syrup, margarine and butter.
Bring to a boil and boil for 1 minute only.
Remove from stove.
Add vanilla and baking soda.
Pour over popcorn and put into a large baking dish. Bake at 250 degrees for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Sift first 5 ingredients together.
Add remaining ingredients. Mix well (will be thick and lumpy) and pour into greased pan. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Stuff in pepper and wrap in foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: twinkie cake
directions: Split Twinkies and place in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer strawberries on top of Twinkies.
Mix pudding according to directions and place on top of strawberries.
Place Cool Whip on top.
Chill about 1 hour.

title: thai-style marinade
directions: *Use caution with seeds, they give the heat, and can burn your eyes if you touch them after handling the seeds.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients and mix well. Drop from a teaspoon onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Press a crisscross on each cookie with a fork, that has been dipped in water.
Bake for 12 minutes.
Remove from oven and place a Hershey Kiss candy on each cookie.
Cool for 1 minute and remove from cookie sheet.

title: smooth and creamy frosting
directions: Combine pudding mix, sugar and milk in a small bowl.
Beat slowly with rotary beater or lowest speed of electric mixer until well blended, about 1 minute.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spread on cake at once.
Makes 4 cups, enough for 1 (9-inch) cake.

title: western salad
directions: Make salad with onion, tomatoes, lettuce, cheese, dressing, hot sauce, chips and avocado.
Brown beef and add kidney beans, salt and simmer 10 minutes.
Mix with cold salad.

title: loblolly
directions: Mix all ingredients, except tamales, in 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish or pan.
Place tamales on top.
Bake at 350° for about 30 to 45 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: stuffed baked sweet potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes and rub with vegetable oil.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour or until done.
Split potatoes in half lengthwise.
Carefully scoop out pulp, leaving shells intact.
Mash pulp.
Add salt, butter, orange juice concentrate and pineapple to mashed pulp. Mix well.
Stuff potato shell with pulp mixture.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Cut each marshmallow in half.
Place 2 marshmallows (cut side down) on each potato half.
Place potato shells on baking sheet.
Bake at 400° until lightly browned on top.

title: tuna quiche
directions: Sprinkle cheese with flour, toss. Add onions, and tuna and toss well. Stir in milk, mayo, and egg. Pour into pie pan.
Bake at 375° for 40 min.
You can add additional spices, or vegetables. i.e. Broccoli and Swizz Cheese.

title: chili
directions: Adjust V-8 juice, sugar, chili powder, Worcestershire sauce and catsup to taste.

title: chile con queso
directions: Dice and melt cheeses together.
Add cream and stir well.
Add chiles, tomato and garlic powder; stir well.
Heat again slightly. Serve warm with tortilla chips.

title: easy french dressing
directions: Mix cornstarch and dry mustard.
Stir in water gradually. Cook over medium heat until thickened, stirring constantly. Cool.
Add catsup, vinegar, Worcestershire sauce, horseradish, paprika and garlic.
Mix well.
Place in small covered jar.
Store in refrigerator.
Shake well before using.
Makes 21 tablespoons. Per teaspoon:
4.0 calories, 0.0 gr. fat, 0.01 calories from fat.

title: jambalaya
directions: In a large pan, saute onion, green pepper, celery and garlic in the butter until tender but not browned.
Add shrimp and oysters; cook for 5 minutes.
(If ham is used instead of oysters, add the ham when rice is added.)
Add the tomatoes, chicken broth, salt, cayenne and rice; stir and cover.
Cook for 25 to 30 minutes over low heat, or until rice is done.
If mixture becomes too dry, add tomato juice.
Taste for seasonings.

title: hello dolly bars
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 12-inch cake pan and layer ingredients in order listed.
DO NOT STIR!
Bake 20 to 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: neiman-marcus cookies
directions: In a large bowl (I use a soup pot), cream the butter and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla and mix thoroughly.
Add flour, oatmeal, salt, soda and baking powder.
Mix thoroughly.
Add the chocolate, chocolate chips and nuts.
Roll into balls and place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
This makes a lot (15 to 20 dozen.)

title: fried cabbage
directions: Heat wok real hot.
Spray with Pam.
Chop vegetables, add to wok, stir.
After started good, add 1/2 cup water, more or less, depending on amount of vegetables.
Keep turning for 30 or 45 minutes.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Combine the ingredients and mix well.
Pour into an oiled 9 x 13 pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Use 1/2 crumbs to line pan.
Layer the other ingredients in order listed.
Sprinkle the other 1/2 of crumbs on top.
Melt 1 stick of butter or margarine and pour on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbles.
Serves 8.

title: ranger cookies(5 dozen)
directions: Cream butter, brown sugar and granulated sugar.
Add egg and vanilla; beat well.
Sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Stir into creamed mixture.
Stir in cereal, coconut and oatmeal.

title: beans 'n kielbasi
directions: Mix everything together.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: sweet and sour turkey
directions: Toss turkey cubes in soy sauce; roll in egg, then in cornstarch, shaking off any excess cornstarch.
Preheat 1 1/2 cups oil in wok at 375°.
Add turkey in 4 batches, frying until golden brown.
Remove turkey.
Remove all but 1 tablespoon oil from wok. Add onion and bag of vegetables.
Stir-fry 2 to 3 minutes.
Push up side.
Add pineapple; stir-fry 1 minute and push up side. Combine pineapple juice, salad vinegar, brown sugar, oil, soy sauce and pepper.
Add to wok and bring to a boil.
Add cornstarch mixture, stirring until thickened.
Return turkey to wok and combine all ingredients.

title: baked bean casserole
directions: Brown hamburger, bacon and onions.
Add remaining ingredients and bake at 350° until heated through.
Feeds a crowd.
Cut recipe in half and it will fit a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: 7-layer salad
directions: Break lettuce up into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chop onion, green pepper and celery.
Spread over lettuce.
Pour peas over top; spread Hellmann's over peas and sprinkle sugar, crumbled bacon and cheese on top.
Refrigerate overnight for best taste.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Mix orange juice and oatmeal.
Add balance of ingredients, except blueberries, and mix well.
Fold in blueberries.
Pour mixture into 1 dozen muffin cups and sprinkle with mixture of cinnamon and sugar.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Excellent muffins.

title: strawberry angel cake
directions: Heat strawberries and juice.
Put in gelatine while hot; add strawberries.
Refrigerate until thickened, about 10 to 15 minutes.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Cut angel cake in 1/2 and frost layers on top.
Refrigerate until time to serve.

title: creamy cashew gravy
directions: Blend all ingredients until smooth.
Pour into saucepan.
Heat and stir until thickened.
You may add any herb seasoning of your choice.

title: frosted 7-up salad(serves 6)
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water; cool and add 7-Up and chill until partially set.
Drain pineapple (save syrup).
Mix pineapple and banana in Jell-O mixture.
Pour into 8 x 8-inch pan; chill until firm.
Combine 1/2 cup sugar and 1 tablespoon flour; stir in 1 slightly beaten egg and the reserved pineapple juice.
Cook over low heat, stirring, until thick.
Chill.
Add 1/2 cup Cool Whip and whip; spread over Jell-O.

title: cheese cake squares
directions: Blend together the cake mix, melted margarine and 1 beaten egg.
Press into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat cream cheese until soft.
Add other ingredients and blend well.
Pour second mixture over first.
Bake at 325° for 35 or 40 minutes until slightly brown on top.
Cool completely before cutting into squares.
Can top with favorite pie filling, if you wish.

title: corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs; add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Pour into 2 1/2-quart baking dish and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: chili de san miguel
directions: Saute onions.
Brown meats.
Add all ingredients to a 40 quart pot.
Heat slowly, stirring often.
Simmer for at least 3 hours. Do not let it scorch.
Serve with favorite toppings (onions, cheese, crackers or Fritos).

title: crock pot chicken dressing
directions: Melt margarine in large boiler and cook onions and celery for about 10 minutes.
Mix bread crumbs with cornbread crumbs, add cream of chicken soup to celery, onions and chicken broth and bring to a boil.
Pour over bread crumbs, add beaten eggs.
Mix well.
Add salt, poultry seasoning, sage and pepper to taste. Pour into 5 quart crock pot on low for 5 hours or on high setting for 4 hours.

title: sweet pickles
directions: Melt sugar in vinegar.
Drain dill pickles and cut into chunks.
Return
to
jar.
Pour sugar and vinegar mixture over pickles.
Add bag of spices.
Everyday for about 2 weeks, turn jar upside-down
or
over, one day up the next day down.
Very good.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Let crusts thaw at room temperature for 10 minutes.
Cook chicken; cut into small pieces.
Spray bottom of pie plate with cooking oil.
Line bottom of pie plate with pie crust; poke holes with fork.
Mix chicken and all other ingredients in pie shell. Top with other crust; tuck edges under first crust.
Press with fork to seal edges; make slits in top crust.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 8.

title: swiss bliss
directions: Use 9 x 13-inch pan.
Line pan with foil and butter foil.
Cut up steak, sprinkle with onion soup, mushrooms, green pepper, tomatoes and seasonings.
Mix juice, sauce and cornstarch.
Pour over meat and vegetables.
Bake 2 hours at 350°.
Sprinkle with parsley.

title: aunt ina's chicken casserole
directions: Pressure cook whole chicken for 45 minutes.
Tear or cut meat into small pieces.
Place in bottom of casserole dish, 9 x 13-inch size preferred.
Add layer of mushrooms.
Top with undiluted soup. Mix stuffing according to box directions and add to top of casserole.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until stuffing is browned.

title: noodles with cabbage and sausage
directions: Brown sausage and pour off fat.
Add cabbage, apple, water, salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer until cabbge is tender-crisp, about 10 minutes.
Cook macaroni and add to skillet.

title: spinach pinwheels
directions: Mix all ingredients except tortillas.
On each tortilla spread about 1/2 cup of the spinach mixture.
Roll up tightly; wrap in plastic wrap.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours or until firm.
To serve, remove plastic wrap, cut each rolled tortilla into about 10 slices.

title: united states sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into a greased baking dish.

title: hamburger and macaroni
directions: Cook hamburger until loses its pinkness.
Take out and pour off excess grease.
Add uncooked macaroni, pepper and onion.
Cook until macaroni turns yellow.
Return hamburger and add tomato sauce and water.
Simmer for 1/2 hour.

title: hickory nut cake(grandmother's recipe)
directions: Cream sugar and butter together well.
Sift together dry ingredients (flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt).
Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture, alternating with milk.
Add lemon extract.
Fold in nuts, which have been rolled in flour.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into mixture.
Pour into three 8-inch round, greased and floured cake pans.
Bake at 350° approximately 20 minutes or until cake springs back to touch.
Frost.
(See recipe for Divinity Frosting.)

title: split pea, ham and carrot soup
directions: You will need a big pot.

title: spaghetti(serves 5 people)
directions: Grate
and season with salt and pepper, add garlic.
Put meat in cheese and parsley and eggs.
Mix with ginger, then make balls. Fry in oil until brown.
Grate 1 cup cheese for over spaghetti.

title: homemade pizza
directions: Butter pizza pans.
Put bread dough in middle and let rise for 3 hours.
Then spread dough to fit pizza pan.
Add spaghetti sauce, pepperoni and cheese.
Bake at 375° to 400° until crust is brown, about 20 minutes.

title: pizza dip
directions: Beat the first 3 ingredients together well.
Spread in round plastic tray.
Top mixture with the seafood cocktail sauce. Spread the shrimp over the sauce.
Sprinkle the tomato and pepper over shrimp.
Spread the Mozzarella cheese over the tomato and pepper.
Serve with Ritz or your favorite crackers.
Best if done ahead of time.

title: strawberry party cake
directions: Cut pound cake horizontally into 3 layers.
Crush 1 1/2 cups of strawberries, reserving remaining strawberries.
Add sugar to cream cheese, beating until smooth.
Fold in whipped topping, then fold in crushed berries.
Fill and frost cake with cream cheese mixture.
Garnish with reserved berries and chill.

title: lasagna
directions: In a Dutch oven, in a little oil, brown links (sprinkle lightly with garlic salt for flavor).
Drain.
Add soups, sauces and paste.
Mix well, then lightly sprinkle garlic salt and basil over the whole top.
Cover and simmer for 1/2 hour.
Then stir and repeat spices.
Boil noodles and eggs for 15 minutes; rinse and drain.
Peel eggs.
When sauce is ready, remove sausage and slice.

title: jean's strawberry cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl and beat about 2-3 minutes.
Pour into 9-inch cake pans and bake at 350° for about 30-45 minutes.

title: scalloped carrots
directions: Cook carrots in salted water and drain.
Meanwhile, cook onions in butter until soft.
Stir in soup, salt, cheese, pepper and carrots.
Place in 2-quart casserole dish.
Toss bread stuffing with 1/2 cup melted butter.
Spoon over carrots and bake at 350° about 30 minutes or until bubbly and hot.
(I use 2 extra ribs of celery, cut and cooked with carrots because I like celery.)

title: baked spinach
directions: Combine spinach, egg, milk and 1/2 cup cracker crumbs.
Add seasonings and place in a buttered baking dish.
Combine remaining crumbs and butter.
Sprinkle over top and bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes or until brown and firm.
Yields 6 servings.

title: party pizzas i
directions: Mix softened cream cheese with soup.
Add chopped pepperoni. Spread evenly on bread.
Broil 2 to 4 minutes, until brown.
Serve warm.

title: smoked sausage and bean soup
directions: Saute onion in margarine in large pot. Add water, potatoes, sausage, beans and bouillon. Cook for 15 minutes in covered pot (until potatoes are cooked). Add cabbage, tomato paste (Ro-Tel) and vinegar and cook for 10 more minutes.

title: apple cheesecake tart
directions: Press mixture into a pie plate covering bottom and sides.

title: caramel apple cake
directions: Combine oil and sugar in a bowl.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Combine dry ingredients; add to batter and stir well.
Fold in apples, walnuts and vanilla.
Pour in a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until cake is done.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove to a wire rack and cool.

title: louisiana chocolate praline pie
directions: Beat eggs in large bowl until foamy.
Beat in flour, sugar and brown sugar.
Stir in melted butter, chocolate morsels and nuts. Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Serve warm with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: tandoori chicken
directions: Rinse the chicken legs and pat dry.
Mash the ginger together with the allspice, pepper and garlic.
Add the lemon juice to make a paste. Lift skin on chicken and spread 1/2 of the mixture over the chicken flesh.
Brush the remaining paste over the chicken skin.
Barbecue.
Arrange the chicken about 6-inches above hot coals.
Cook, turning frequently, until the meat near the bone is no longer pink when cut with a knife, about 45 minutes.
Transfer chicken to platter and serve hot with white rice and cold yogurt to spoon over the individual servings.

title: dump cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour pie filling in pan and spread over bottom.
Pour pineapple over filling (juice and all). Sprinkle dry cake mix over fruit.
Slice butter over top of cake mix.
Sprinkle nuts over this.
Do not mix.
Bake 1 hour at 350°. Cut into squares and serve with whipped topping or ice cream.

title: chocolate eclair cake(make 1 day ahead)
directions: *Start with 3 cups, only add other 1/4 cup if pudding is extremely thick.

title: grilled jamaican chicken
directions: Place chicken in a dish.
Combine next the lime juice, lemon juice, sweet vermouth, Dijon mustard, jalapeno pepper, garlic, coriander, cumin, thyme, oregano and salt.
Pour over chicken. Cover and marinate in refrigerator 8 hours.
Turn twice.
Remove chicken from marinade.
Place marinade in small saucepan; bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Set aside.

title: ambrosia sherbet
directions: Mix in blender and freeze in small containers.

title: baked salmon
directions: Place each fillet on individual piece of aluminum foil large enough to completely wrap and lightly seal salmon.
Put garlic slices on top of salmon, salt and pepper to taste and a few sprigs of fresh cilantro.
Add a splash of white wine.
Wrap and seal salmon in foil.

title: macho nacho
directions: Spoon chili over chips.
Sprinkle cheese.
Heat till cheese melts and serve.

title: turtle brownies
directions: Melt caramels with 1/2 cup evaporated milk and set aside. Combine cake mix, margarine, 1/3 cup evaporated milk and nuts. Mix. press half of this mixture into 9x13 pan.
Bake 8 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.
Spread semi-sweet chocolate chips over baked mixture.
Spread caramel mixture over chocolate chips.
Crumble other half of cake mixture on top.	Bake 18-20 minutes at 350°.

title: very fancy sweet potatoes(i have heard that this is sometimes called "likker pudding".)
directions: Combine; then fold in 6 stiffly beaten egg whites.
Transfer to 2-quart greased baking dish.
Pour 1/2 cup bourbon over the top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Enough for 8.

title: squash pickles
directions: Mix sugar, vinegar, celery seed, turmeric and mustard seed. Place vegetables in a non-metal container.
Sprinkle salt over top and let stand 3 hours.
Rinse with cold water.
Drain.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti; drain. Cook bell pepper and onion in a small amount of butter or oil until tender, then add to spaghetti with rest of ingredients. Cook until desired thickness.

title: carrot cake
directions: Combine eggs, sugar and oil in a large bowl.
Beat well. Combine flour, salt, soda and cinnamon and add to sugar mixture. Mix well.
Stir in carrots, pecans, pineapple and vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: turkey sloppy joes
directions: Heat the oil in a large pot or Dutch oven over high heat.
Add the onion and green pepper.
Saute for 7 to 8 minutes, stirring frequently, until the pepper is tender and onion begins to brown.

title: rice-broccoli casserole
directions: Butter 2 small or 1 large casserole dish (9 x 13 x 2-inch). Mix all ingredients together; pour into casserole dish(es).
This can be prepared and refrigerated overnight.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: avocado dip
directions: Peel avocado; remove pit and mash. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Chill.
Makes 1 cup.

title: chocolate heath bar dessert(very rich!)
directions: Bake angel food cake.
Tear into bite-size pieces and put in bottom of 9 x 13-inch dish.
Mix large package sugar-free chocolate pudding with skim milk.
Mix well with 8 ounces light Cool Whip. Alternate layers with 1/2 cake topped with 1/2 pudding.
Sprinkle with chopped pecans.
Repeat layers.

title: kirby's peach cobbler
directions: Melt margarine and pour into baking dish.
Mix flour, sugar and milk together and pour on top of margarine.
Then pour in peaches with juice.
Sprinkle with nutmeg and cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until brown.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Heat 7-Up and pour over Jell-O.
Mix cheese with hot water until smooth.
Add cheese and other ingredients together.
Chill.

title: oriental beef steak strips
directions: Cut round steak in strips 1/8-inch thick or thinner and 3 to 4-inches long.* Brown strips in cooking fat. Pour off drippings, measure and add water to make 1 cup. Combine with soy sauce, sugar, pepper and garlic and add to meat. Cover and cook slowly 45 minutes. Using vegetable parer, cut carrots lengthwise into thin strips and cut strips in half. Add carrots, peppers, onions, mushrooms and water chestnuts to meat. Cover and continue cooking 15 minutes. Combine cornstarch and water and use to thicken cooking liquid for gravy. Serve with cooked rice. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: hot pecan chicken salad
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Top with potato chips and 1/4 cup pecans.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve hot.
Garnish with green pepper rings.
Serves 6.

title: cornmeal mush
directions: Bring water to a boil in top of double boiler.
Add salt; stir in cornmeal mixed well with cold water.
Cook; stir constantly until mixture is thick.
Place over boiling water.
Cover; cook for 30 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Pour into loaf pan to cool; slice for fried mush.
Can be used as a cereal.
While still warm, slice thin; fry slices in oil or lard.
When brown, put them on plate and serve with butter and syrup.

title: super nacho
directions: Brown meat with onion and drain lightly.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer:
beans, meat, chilies, cheeses, salsa.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts.
To serve, top with sour cream, avocado dip and black olives.
Serve with corn chips.

title: garlic chicken
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Set aside.
Place chicken skin-side-up in oven-safe pan.
Pour melted butter over chicken; sprinkle whole or chopped garlic cloves on top.
Turn chicken over in butter.
Cover tightly and bake in oven for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Eat with chunks of French bread dipped in garlic butter.

title: salmon bake with pecan crunch coating
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Season salmon with salt and pepper. Place fillets, skin-side down, in a lightly greased 9x13 inch pan. Combine mustard, butter and honey and brush over fillets.
Mix bread crumbs, pecans and parsley.
Spoon mixture evenly over fillets.
Bake 10 minutes or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork.
Garnish with parsley and lemon slices.

title: thai chicken (spicy!)
directions: Rub chicken with salt and pepper.
Saute in frypan in a little oil.
Remove chicken from pan.
Saute the onion in the oil.
Add the remaining ingredients to the pan and mix well.
Return chicken to pan and baste with sauce.
Cover pan and cook over low heat, about one hour or until tender.
Check occasionally and add water, if needed.

title: old-fashioned lemon chess pie
directions: Allow melted margarine to cool.
In a bowl, beat eggs, sugar, corn meal and vinegar.
Add margarine and lemon flavoring and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Add vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add alternating with buttermilk.
Mix well. Add bananas and nuts.
Bake in 2 loaf pans in 350° oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: hot coco pine cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients. Pour into a greased 13 x 9 inch baking pan. Sprinkle brown sugar and pecans over mixture. Bake at 350° for 30-35 minutes.

title: scalloped potatoes and ham
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Peel and slice potatoes thin.
Put in 4 quart greased casserole dish with onion and ham in layer.
Mix flour, milk, salt and pepper.
(Put in a jar and shake.
Make sure there are no lumps.)
Pour over potatoes.
DOT with butter.
Cover and bake 60 to 70 minutes until done.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes. Then put cheese on top and bake uncovered until cheese is melted and bubbly.

title: evoyn's red beans and rice
directions: Pick beans and cover with water. Soak overnight.
Drain beans. Place
in	soup pot with ham hocks, onions, celery and bell pepper.
Cover
with
cold	water.	Cover
pot
and bring beans to a
boil.
Then turn down heat to a simmer.	Let beans simmer 2 1/2 to
hours over low heat, adding more water if necessary, to keep
beans
from
sticking.
Remove ham hocks, onions, celery and
bell peppers.	Remove some beans from the pot and mash
them. Return mashed beans to pot and stir.
(If more beans
need
to be mashed to achieve desired consistency, do so.) Serve hot over cooked rice.
Serves 8.

title: hot christmas fruit
directions: Melt margarine.
Add applesauce and sugar and cook until bubbly.
Drain all fruit and place in medium casserole dish. Pour hot applesauce mixture over fruit and bake 30 minutes at 350°. Sprinkle with cinnamon.

title: gourmet meat loaf
directions: To make filling:
In small frying pan, melt butter and saute onion and mushrooms for 5 minutes, stirring.
Remove from heat and stir in sour cream, mix lightly.
In large bowl, combine remaining ingredients, mix well.
In lightly greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan, place half of meat loaf mixture down the center, make an indentation.
Spoon filling into the indentation.
Place remaining meat loaf mixture over all the filling.
Press top and bottom layers together and bake in 300° oven for 45 minutes.

title: chili dip
directions: Heat on low. Serve with chips.

title: coconut pie(two)
directions: Mix sugar, margarine, eggs and vanilla.
Mix buttermilk and coconut.
Divide into two pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: white christmas mousse(in honor of sep palin, along with greyhound)
directions: Melt the white chocolate with hazelnuts in double boiler, stirring occasionally.
Gradually add warm milk, stirring until smooth; allow to cool.
Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form; gently fold into chocolate mixture (the white chocolate mixture). Whip cream until stiff; fold into white chocolate mixture.
Add lemon juice; stir lightly.
Spoon into 1-quart glass bowl, or 6 individual stemmed dessert glasses.
Chill at least 2 hours; garnish with dark chocolate curls or shavings.
One may also want to place a maraschino cherry on the top to garnish.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Cook the chicken in a quart of water.
Remove the chicken from the liquid and pick the meat from the bones.
Measure the liquid so you will have the amount that the rice box calls for.
Add water if necessary.
Prepare the rice in the same pan that you cooked the chicken in.
Return the chicken pieces to the rice. Add the vegetables and heat through.
This is also good with broccoli.

title: mango cheese crown
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water. Blend both mango juice and fruit in blender until smooth, 1 can at a time. Pour into 1-gallon container. Place 1/2 of cream cheese into blender and add enough of the hot dissolved Jell-O to 3/4 level. Blend until smooth. Add to mango mixture. Repeat with the remaining cream cheese and Jell-O and add to mango. Stir to blend completely. Pour in 1-gallon mold and chill overnight. Unmold onto tray. Line with lettuce and garnish with fresh strawberries and/or kiwi.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Blend oil and sugar; beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add shredded zucchini.
Mix flour, salt, cinnamon, soda and baking powder together.
Add to the first mixture.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until done.
Freezes well.

title: spinach madeleine
directions: Cook spinach according to directions on package.
Drain and reserve liquid.
Melt butter in sauce pan over low heat.
Add flour, stirring until blended and smooth, but not brown.
Add onion and cook until soft, but not brown.
Add liquid slowly, stirring constantly to avoid lumps.
Cook until smooth and thick.
Continue stirring.
Add seasoning and cheese which has been cut into small pieces.
Stir until cheese is melted.
Combine with cooked spinach. Put into a casserole and top with bread crumbs and butter.
Bake at 350 degrees until bread crumbs are light golden brown.

title: german potato salad
directions: Combine celery and onion and cook until done.
Add flour, sugar, water and vinegar.
Cook until thickened.
Add potatoes and crumbled bacon.
Enjoy!

title: five can casserole
directions: Mix together and sprinkle toasted bread crumbs on top.
Cook 30 minutes at 275°.
Let stand until set.

title: no bake strawberry or raspberry torte
directions: Crush graham crackers, saving 1/4 cup for top.
Melt butter or margarine.
Mix butter, graham crackers and sugar.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: sweet n sour franks
directions: Mix jelly and mustard together in a big boiler.
Add franks. Cook for a short time until franks change color.

title: orange delight cake
directions: Beat all together and pour into 3 greased and floured pans. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Let cool before frosting.

title: fried cabbage
directions: Cook bacon until brown.
Remove.
Toss cabbage until tender (10 minutes).
Add lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Put bacon on top.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: any time variety bar
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla and flour.
Beat well.
Spread into ungreased jelly roll pan.
Sprinkle chips and nuts and press down into dough.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: lemon whippersnaps
directions: Grease cookie sheet.
Combine eggs, Cool Whip and cake mix in large bowl.
Stir until well mixed.
Drop by teaspoon in powdered sugar.
Roll to coat.
Place 1 1/2 inches apart on cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes or until light brown.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: pickled eggs
directions: Hard Boil eggs, cool and peel. Drain beets. Use equal amounts of sugar and vinegar stir to dissolve sugar. Add eggs cover with beets. Put in refrigerator. Best in 6-7 days.

title: pasta salad
directions: Mix and add to pasta.
Let set overnight.
Add veggies: broccoli, cauliflower, cucumbers, onion, bell peppers, celery and tomatoes.

title: milky way cake
directions: Melt candy bars and 1 stick (1/2 cup) margarine in saucepan over low heat.
Beat remaining 1 stick (1/2 cup) margarine and sugar in bowl until fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time; beat well after each egg.
Mix flour and baking soda; add alternately with buttermilk.
Stir until smooth.
Add melted candy mixture, mixing well.
Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Pour batter into greased and floured Bundt or 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes or until top springs back when touched lightly.

title: candy strawberries
directions: Roll the ball in the red sugar, then stick the dyed green sliced almonds for the stems.

title: taco party wings
directions: Combine everything except chicken wings in a plastic bag.
Add wings and shake to coat.
Place in a single layer on a greased, shallow baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until tender and brown.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Cream together first 4 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: chocolate oat drop cookies
directions: Combine milk, cocoa, sugar and margarine in saucepan.
Bring to a full rolling boil. Remove from heat immediately.
Add peanut butter, vanilla and oats. Stir to combine. Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper to cool.

title: black walnut fudge
directions: Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Combine sugar, oleo, milk and Karo in large pan.
Put heat on medium.
Stir until sugar is dissolved. Stop stirring; cook until soft ball stage (234° on candy thermometer).
Remove from heat.
Stir in white chocolate chips. Stir well.
Add Marshmallow Creme and stir well.
Add walnuts and vanilla and mix well.
Pour into prepared pan.
Let set to cool. Refrigerate until chilled, then cut into pieces.
Makes 1 1/2 pounds.

title: lefsa
directions: Boil white potatoes with jackets on.
Peel, mash or rice.
Add Crisco, cream, salt and sugar.
Cool overnight.
Mix in flour with hands.
Make into walnut size balls or larger.
Roll thin with lefsa rolling pin (with a sock on).
Put on hot griddle.
Makes 25 to 30.

title: tuna crunch salad
directions: Combine the first five ingredients.
Cover and chill.
Just before serving, add cabbage and half of potato chips.
Toss. Serve on lettuce.
Sprinkle with remaining potato chips and garnish with tomatoes and lemon wedges.

title: delicious spinach salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into jar and refrigerate.
Shake well before using.
Serve with spinach, bean sprouts, water chestnuts, eggs and bacon.
The longer it sits, the better it gets.
(Yield is 1 1/2 cups.)

title: hamburger hash
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a large skillet, cook meat, onions and green pepper until meat is brown and vegetables are tender.
Drain off fat.
Put meat and vegetables in casserole dish (4 quart). Stir in tomatoes, rice, salt, chili powder, 1/2 of the can of tomatoes and tomato juice.
Use last 1/2 to keep rice moist during cooking; add as needed.
Cover and bake 1 hour.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients, then add eggs, cream and milk.
Pour into ice cream churn.
Enjoy!

title: mushroom burgers
directions: Brown beef until almost done.
Drain off fat.
Add salt, pepper and mustard.
Cook about 15 to 20 minutes on low heat.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Melt butter; mix in cocoa and sugar, then milk.
Boil 2 minutes; remove from heat and add vanilla, peanut butter and oatmeal.
Stir together and quickly drop by balls on waxed paper.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Brown and scramble ground beef and diced onion in skillet. Drain fat.
Add tomato sauce.
Stir while mixture simmers.
Place in casserole dish.
Top with mashed potatoes.
Top with cheese. Place in oven and brown lightly.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix pumpkin, sugars, salt, flour, cinnamon and egg together well.
Add milk and mix until smooth.
Place in prepared pie shells and bake 20 minutes at 450°.
Reduce oven to 400° and bake 20 to 25 minutes more, until lightly brown.
Yields 2 pies.

title: potato candy
directions: Cook potato and mash; do not season.
Add butter, vanilla and sugar and roll out thin.
Spread with peanut butter and roll up jelly roll fashion; slice.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Mix first three ingredients.
Combine with rhubarb.
Pour into prepared pie crust, sprinkle with nutmeg and dot with butter. Cover with top crust, making sure to cut slits.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes, lower temperature to 375° and bake for an additional 45 minutes or until rhubarb is tender.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Cook in a cast-iron Dutch oven for 1 1/2 hours on medium heat. Stir frequently.
Best when served next day.
Serve over cooked white or brown rice in bowls.

title: mexican fiesta
directions: Brown ground round; drain.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce, tomato paste, garlic salt, chili powder and Ranch Style beans.
Simmer about 2 hours.
When meat sauce is done, then layer rest of ingredients in any order you want.

title: traditional tourtiere
directions: Bring to boil and cook, stirring constantly, until meat loses red color.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer for 45 minutes or until very tender.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix the instant pudding separate.
Mix the Dream Whip separate.
Combine together with cream cheese.
Mix well.
Then pour over cookies and bananas.

title: real french bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1 cup of water. While yeast softens, sift flour, sugar and salt together in a large bowl.
Stir in the dissolved yeast.
Add just enough of the second cup of water to hold dough together.
Mix until you have a soft rather sticky dough.
Cover with a clean cloth.
Set bowl in a warm spot in kitchen.
Let rise until double in size.

title: oyster cracker hors d'oeuvres
directions: Seal all into a Ziploc bag.
Keep airtight for at least 2 days.
Shake from time to time. When thoroughly marinated, store in glass jars.

title: caramel pie
directions: Beat yolks.
Add sugar, flour and milk; set aside.
Melt and brown 1 cup sugar, then add egg yolks, sugar, flour and milk mixture.
Stir until smooth and creamy.
Add vanilla and butter. Pour into a baked pie shell.
Cover with meringue and brown.
Very good!

title: green bean casserole
directions: Grease baking dish with butter.
Drain beans.
Put in bottom of pan. Shred onion over top of beans.

title: snickerdoodle cookies
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Sift next 4 ingredients together then combine with sugar mixture.
In a small bowl mix 2 teaspoons sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon.

Roll cookie dough into balls about the size of a small walnut, then roll in sugar mixture. Place 2 inches apart on cookie sheet and bake until brown but soft. Cookies will puff up at first but flatten out with crinkled top. Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Have cheeses at room temperature.
Mix cheeses, onion salt, Worcestershire sauce and Accent, if using.
Form into 2 balls. Roll in a mixture of chopped pecans, parsley flakes and paprika. Refrigerate.
May be frozen.

title: popovers
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease muffin pan.
Combine eggs and milk in a bowl.
Add flour and salt and blend until smooth.
Stir in butter.
Fill each cup half full.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: angel pie
directions: Mix and press into pie pan.
Bake in 350° oven until lightly browned, 15 to 20 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Bake and cool pie shell. Combine the peanut butter and powdered sugar with a fork until mixed and crumbly in texture. Spread most of mixture on pie shell. Save rest for topping on meringue.
Combine sugar, milk, butter, cornstarch, salt, egg yolks and vanilla. Cook on low/medium heat until thick.
Stir often. Pour over peanut butter mixture in pie shell. Make meringue with 3 remaining egg whites. Top with crumbly peanut butter mixture. Bake at 325° until meringue is browned.

title: meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In a large bowl, mix bread crumbs, ketchup, onion soup mix and water. Stir in eggs and Worcestershire sauce. Add meat and mix with hands until well blended.

Form into an oblong loaf shape and place in a 13 x 9 baking pan. Pour tomato sauce over loaf; spread evenly. Place bacon strips on top. Bake for approximately 1 1/4 hours. Let stand for 5 minutes after taking it out of the oven.

title: punch for a crowd
directions: Mix in any order you deem best!
All liquids should probably be chilled and the orange juice partially thawed.
Great for receptions, band concerts, and recitals!

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Grease a baking dish.
Chop onion and add mixed vegetables and cheese.
Add mayonnaise and mix together.
Put in baking dish. Crush crackers and add melted margarine on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 375°.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy.
Add oil, zucchini, sugar and vanilla. Mix lightly, but well.
Mix in flour, baking soda, baking powder, salt, cinnamon, raisins and nuts.
Blend well.

title: chinese chicken noodle salad
directions: Break pasta into 5 inch pieces.
Cook in boiling water 2 minutes.
Add snow peas, cook an additional minute.
Drain and rinse under cold, running water.
Drain well.
Combine pasta mixture, chicken and next 3 ingredients in a bowl.
Set aside.

title: cheese dessert
directions: Mix flour, oleo and 1/2 chopped nuts.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool on rack at least 20 minutes.
Blend and whip sugar and cream cheese and fold in 1/2 Cool Whip.
Spread on crust in one direction.
Blend pudding and milk until thick and spread on cheese layer.
Spread on rest of Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with rest of nuts.
Refrigerate for several hours or overnight.

title: coconut pie
directions: Combine
ingredients
together	in mixing bowl and pour into a
9-inch
pie
shell.
Bake at 325° for about 1 hour or until golden brown.

title: strawberry preserves
directions: Place over low heat until sugar is dissolved.
Bring to a boil and boil 15 to 20 minutes.
Make jelly test and skim when necessary.
Pour into a shallow pan and let stand overnight.
Next morning, fill sterilized jars with cool preserves.
Paraffin wax may be added.
Seal.
Makes about 2 1/2 cups.
Recipe may be doubled, if desired.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Blend margarine, flour and sugar together with a pastry cutter or fork.
Sprinkle over peaches.
Bake at 375° until brown.

title: cream of pumpkin soup
directions: In a 6-quart pan, saute onion 10 minutes.
Stir in flour.
Add broth gradually.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce to simmer.
Cover. Cook 10 minutes.

title: norwegian vegetable soup(fersk suppe)
directions: In a large saucepot, bring water, salt, beef and soup bone to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 1 hour.
During cooking, remove foam that forms on top.
After 1 hour, add chopped onions and continue to simmer for 1 hour.
Then add carrots, cabbage, nutmeg, bouillon and pepper.
Simmer another 1/2 hour.
Remove meat and bones and keep meat warm.
Prepare sauce by mixing white sauce with vinegar, sugar and horseradish.
Serve the soup first, then the meat and sauce.
Tastes good with steamed red potatoes sprinkled with parsley.

title: summer potato salad
directions: Boil water in large pot.
Add potatoes and cook 15 to 20 minutes until tender.
Drain.
Place in a bowl.
While potatoes are cooking, combine vinegar, mustard and basil in blender, food processor or by hand.
Add oil.
Blend.
Pour over potatoes.
Add pepper and toss well.

title: strawberry pretzel jello
directions: Mix first three ingredients.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 375° for 10 minutes (do not overbake).
Cool.
Combine cream cheese and sugar with electric mixer.
Stir in Cool whip with spoon.
Spread over pretzel mixture.
Dissolve jello with hot water; blend in strawberries until thawed.
When thickened, spread on top.

title: cookies
directions: Mix all together.
Drop by spoonful on cookie sheet.
Cook 7 minutes at 350°.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Shake dressing together just before serving; add almonds, orange and dressing to lettuce mixture.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Cream together butter, oil and sugar.
Add beaten eggs, vanilla and sour cream.
Sift together dry ingredients and add to egg mixture.
Add zucchini, chocolate chips and pecans (nuts). Bake in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan or Bundt pan at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
May be iced on top with whipped cream.

title: chicken oporto(good housekeeping illustrated cookbook)
directions: In a 12-inch skillet over medium-high heat in hot butter, cook mushrooms 5 minutes.
Remove with slotted spoon and set aside in bowl.
On wax paper, combine flour, salt, pepper and nutmeg; use to coat chicken breasts.
In same skillet in remaining butter over medium-high heat, cook chicken breasts until browned on all sides. Stir in cream, Port wine and mushrooms.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 15 minutes or until chicken is fork-tender.

title: snickers cheese cake
directions: Mix all ingredients, except crust.
Spoon into the graham cracker crust in a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Refrigerate for 2 hours.

title: classy cukes
directions: Sprinkle cucumbers with salt and refrigerate for 3 hours. Rinse in cold water and squeeze out liquid.

title: raisin bread
directions: Melt butter in water; bring to boil. Add raisins and soda. Let stand overnight. Next morning, beat eggs and vanilla. Add to first part, then add sugar, flour, cinnamon, salt and nuts. Mix well. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: kahlua
directions: Mix water, sugar and instant coffee.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer for 3 hours.
Remove from heat and cool.
When cool, add vodka and vanilla.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Peel
potatoes	and
cut into cubes.
Cook potatoes and onions until potatoes are tender.
Brown meat and drain, then mix
with potatoes
and
onions.
Add mixed vegetables, salt, pepper,
soda and
sugar	(to taste).
Simmer on low heat for approximately 1 hour.
Yields 2 to 3 gallons.

title: fudge pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into greased pie plate. Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: beefy cheese ball
directions: Combine cream cheese, mixing at medium speed until well blended. Add onion, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Mix well. Chill for several hours. Shape into a ball. Roll in shredded beef.

title: fruit punch
directions: Put water, tea bags and spices into a small saucepan.
Bring to a boil, lower heat and barely simmer about 1 hour.
Cool. Strain into punch bowl and add the frozen concentrates and chilled juices.

title: oven baked macaroni and cheese
directions: You also need 1 medium size oblong glass baking dish or pan.

title: impossible cheeseburger pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Lightly grease casserole dish.
Crumble and cook beef and onion over medium heat until brown; drain.
Stir in salt and pepper.
Spread beef mixture in dish.
Spread cheese evenly over beef.
Beat milk, Bisquick and eggs until smooth, 15 seconds in blender or 1 minute with hand mixer.
Pour evenly over beef and cheese.
Bake until golden brown and knife inserted in center comes out clean (about 30 minutes).
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: mexi-casserole
directions: Brown first four ingredients and set aside.
Mix next three ingredients and pour over meat mixture; set aside.
Start with a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex pan.
Layer in this order: pinto beans, corn chips, refried beans and corn chips.
Mix together the cream cheese and sour cream with 1 teaspoon of garlic powder and spread on top to make the next layer.
Now pour the meat sauce you have reserved on top of this.
Melt the milk and Velveeta in microwave and pour over top.
Then add the Mozzarella cheese as the last layer.
Place this in 350° oven and bake 30 minutes.

title: mom's homemade vegie soup
directions: Cover with water, bring to boil and cook slow until meat is done.
Remove bone; cut meat.
Then add mixed vegies, limas and egg noodles.
Bring to boil, then let simmer until done.
Remove bay leaf.

title: two-toned appetizer
directions: Fill glasses 3/4 full with chilled pineapple juice.
Tip glass slowly and pour tomato juice down the side of glass until full. Serve chilled at once.

title: banana butter
directions: Mash bananas thoroughly.
Measure 4 cups into 6 or 8-quart pan.
Stir in lemon juice.
Add fruit protector, if desired. Prepare jars for canning.
Measure sugar into separate bowl.
Stir pectin into fruit in saucepan.
Add margarine.
Place over high heat; bring to a full rolling boil and boil 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; skim off foam with metal spoon. Ladle quickly into jars, filling to within 1/8-inch of top.
Put tops on tightly.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes until done.

title: blueberry pudding cake
directions: Place blueberries in 8 x 8-inch pan.
Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Shake cinnamon over top.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Cream together sugar, softened butter, egg, vanilla and salt. Beat until smooth and creamy.
Spread mixture in baked pie shell; chill.
Combine whipped topping, pineapple, pecans, cherries and milk until blended.
Spread over chilled filling.
Chill pie until ready to serve.

title: chocolate chip chiffon cake(dam family birthday cake)
directions: Measure flour, baking powder, sugar and salt in a bowl.
Make a well and add oil, egg yolks, water and vanilla.
Beat with a spoon until smooth.
In a separate bowl, whip egg whites and cream of tartar until very stiff.
Do not underbeat.
Pour egg yolk/flour mixture over whipped egg whites.
Gently fold with rubber spatula until just blended.
Do not stir.
Fold in shaved chocolate.
Pour immediately into ungreased pan and bake.
Tube pan, 10 x 4-inch at 325° for 55 minutes, then 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Oblong, 9 x 3-inch at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until top springs back when lightly touched.
Immediately turn finished cake upside down, placing tube part over neck of funnel or bottle, or resting edge of oblong pan on edges of two other pans.
Let hang, free of table, until cold.
Loosen from sides and tube with spatula.
Turn over and place on cake plate.
Frost cake with Buttercream Frosting (recipe follows).

title: nanaw's soup
directions: Brown ground meat.
Drain grease and place in a large stew pot.
Add several cups of water. Stir in the chili and the other cans of vegetables.
Peel and cut the carrots and potatoes. Add them to the soup. Simmer for 2 or 3 hours over low heat until the potatoes and carrots are tender.
Serve with cornbread or crackers.

title: party meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients together except for the meatballs. Put meatballs in a casserole dish. Pour mixture over the meatballs. Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour.

title: sugarless bars
directions: Cut up fruit and boil with 1 cup water.
Add margarine and cool.
Combine ingredients and add fruit mixture.
Put in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 or 30 minutes.

title: twenty minute cake
directions: Bring first 4 ingredients to a boil; remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: punch
directions: Mix ingredients together and chill before serving.
Serves approximately 25 people.

title: southwest chicken casserole
directions: Boil the chicken, saving the broth.
Let chicken cool; skin and debone.
Shred the chicken into strips or chunks.
Cut up the green onions.
Add the onions to 2 cups of the boiling broth.
Add the 2 cans of soup, stirring until thick.
Put the Doritos in a baking dish, pouring the mixture over.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: lazy daisy cake
directions: Combine eggs, sugar and vanilla; beat well until thick.
Add sifted ingredients.
Heat milk and butter to boiling point and add to above mixture. Bake in buttered 8 x 8-inch pan at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes until done.

title: piggie pudding
directions: Mix flour, butter and chopped pecans.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool.

title: black bean soup
directions: Soak beans overnight in cold water.
I usually don't have things planned that far in advance, so I pre-cook the beans in cold water.
Bring to a boil approximately 20 minutes.
Drain. Heat oil in stock pot and saute onions, celery, garlic, carrots, cumin, oregano and basil until tender.
Add water, beans and tomato sauce.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and cook approximately 2 hours.
Serve with French bread and a dollop of sour cream can be put in the middle of each serving.

title: cream cheese icing
directions: Beat cheese and butter and gradually add powdered sugar. Add vanilla and chopped nuts, if desired.

title: warm brownie cups
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Place a baking pan half full of water in oven.
Bring a saucepan of water to barely simmering.
Place chocolate and butter in a heatproof bowl.
Place over water and stir until almost melted.
Remove bowl from heat and let cool, stirring occasionally.
Sift together, twice, all dry ingredients except sugar.
Set aside.

title: ramsey mcmuffins(breakfast or luncheon)
directions: In medium bowl, break down (smash) the croutons so they are almost crumblike.
Add enough water to moisten so it is doughlike. Spray 12 muffin cup tin with Pam.
Divide crouton mixture among the 12 cups; press croutons into the bottom 1/3 of each cup. Divide bacon among the cups, adding that layer next.
Now, crack 1 egg into each cup, breaking the yolk.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper to taste.
Top with shredded cheese, mounding over each egg.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes (until egg looks solid under melted cheese).
Serves 12.

title: brandi's fudge
directions: Cook until a soft ball forms.
Then pour into an 8 x 8-inch greased pan with margarine.
Let cool.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger until done.
Drain.
Mix soup and sauce together.
Put meat in Pyrex dish and layer, ending with cheese. Pour soup mixture over each "layer."
Cook at 350° until hot.

title: easy-breezy bread pudding
directions: Crumble bread in 9 x 13 greased pan.
Spread fruit evenly over crumbled bread.
Set aside.
In a separate bowl, mix butter, eggs and sugar with a hand mixer until creamy.
In a medium saucepan, combine milk and vanilla.
Cook until warm but not boiling.
Pour warmed milk into butter, egg and sugar mixture. Beat until all lumps are dissolved.
Pour mixture over bread and fruit.
Bake for approximately 1-1/2 hours at 350 degrees until firm in the middle.

title: easter potato bake
directions: Note:
It is important to boil the potatoes a day before preparing and leave them in the refrigerator overnight.

title: dilled pork scaloppini
directions: Cut pork crosswise into 12 slices; flatten to 1/4-inch thickness. Dust with flour. Combine egg and water; dip pork into mixture, then coat with crumbs. In large skillet, saute pork in butter, about 3 minutes per side. Keep pork warm while preparing sauce.

title: pretzels
directions: Thaw frozen bread dough until it handles easily.
Cut into 12 pieces the long way, then roll into long snake.
Grease pan lightly.
Shape anyway you want.
Place pretzels on pan and brush with egg yolk and sprinkle with rock salt on top.
Bake 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve hot or cold.

title: fruit salad dressing
directions: Boil the ingredients together until thickened.
Pour hot (not boiling) over fruit in bowl.
Refrigerate when cool.

title: cheesy ham and egg brunch
directions: Prepare shells according to package directions.
Meanwhile, in a medium bowl, combine eggs, 1/4 cup soup and ham.
In a 10-inch skillet, over medium heat, heat margarine.
Add egg mixture and cook until eggs are set, stirring often.
In a 1-quart saucepan, combine remaining soup and milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring often, until heated through.
Evenly divide egg mixture among pastry shells.
Spoon soup mixture over eggs.

title: barbecued brisket
directions: Rub the brisket with liquid hickory smoke.
Sprinkle with garlic salt and meat tenderizer.
Pierce meat with fork in a number of places.
Wrap in foil and let stand several hours or overnight.
