title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place 2 coffee measuring spoons of this in a cup and add hot water.

title: mexican salad
directions: Put vegetables into large salad bowl.
Toss in beans and cheese.
Just before serving, toss in crushed Fritos and pour on dressing.

title: spinach balls
directions: Put all ingredients in large bowl and mix well.
Roll into balls about 1-inch.
Bake at 350° until browned (about 10 minutes).
May freeze for later use.
If seasoned bread crumbs are used, do not add additional spices.

title: corn relish
directions: Combine in a bowl.
Pour mixture over vegetables.
Bring to boil; simmer 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Cover and store in refrigerator.
Keeps about 2 to 3 weeks.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: chocolate malt shoppe pie
directions: Combine crumbs and butter or margarine.
Press into a 9-inch pie pan.
Freeze while preparing filling.

title: super baked beans
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Pour into casserole dish with all 2 cans of baked beans and mix together.
This is where you can add the mustard and brown sugar to taste.
Top with bacon and cook in oven at 350° until bacon is done.
This is great when you have a barbecue and company.

title: date pudding
directions: Mix boiling water and brown sugar and let stand.
Mix together flour, sugar, vanilla, baking powder, milk, salt, dates and nuts. Put in large greased baking bowl.
Pour water and brown sugar over the top.
Do not mix.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 1 hour 10 minutes.

title: oven barbecued steak
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cut steak into 10 equal portions.
Pour oil in skillet and heat.
Brown steak on each side for 1 to 2 minutes.
Transfer to baking dish.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer over low heat for 10 minutes.
Pour over steak in baking dish and bake, covered, for 1 1/2 to 2 hours, until very tender.

title: 24 hour cranberry salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients. Cover. Chill overnight.
Add remaining ingredients. Mix well and chill for 30 minutes.

title: mexican dip
directions: Spread cheese on bottom of an 8 x 8 or 9 x 9-inch pan.
Mix salsa and beans together. Spread over cream cheese.
Chop the green chilies and spread over top.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 20 to 30 minutes (until hot and bubbly).
Serve with nacho chips.

title: baked fish
directions: Freeze fish, preferably trout, separately. Hold fish under hot water faucet just long enough to loosen skin. Then remove skin.

title: burger and macs
directions: Brown meat, then add other ingredients. Salt and pepper to taste.
Top with grated Cheddar cheese and bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: quick sherbet punch
directions: Just before serving, spoon sherbet into punch bowl.
Slowly pour chilled ginger ale over sherbet.
Add fruit cocktail, stirring gently.
Serve immediately.
Yield:
4 1/2 quarts.

title: mexican bean dip
directions: Spread refried beans in bottom of casserole dish.
Combine sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning mix; spread over refried beans.
Layer remaining ingredients.
Can be served hot or cold with nacho chips.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken and debone.
Mix together soup and sour cream. Add chicken and put in casserole dish.
Melt butter and pour on top.
Crumble crackers and put on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: candyland
directions: Mix crushed cookies and melted butter.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Let cool.

title: jeanette's ham
directions: Wash ham.
Cut ham to fit crock-pot.
Pour water in pot (may need to use a little more, depending on size).
Let cook all night or until done on medium to high.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add egg and molasses.
Sift dry ingredients and add.
Roll into balls; dip tips in sugar and place on a cookie sheet.
Do not flatten.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan.
Stir in flour until smooth.
Stir in juice of one can of asparagus slowly until smooth.
Cook until thick.
Add cheese and stir until melted.
Spread crushed crackers thickly on bottom of greased, 8 x 8-inch casserole dish. Alternate layers of asparagus and cheese sauce, finishing with a thin layer of crackers on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Roll thin.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Chopped nuts and raisins may be added.

title: asparagus and rice
directions: Saute onion in oil.
Add mushrooms until wet.
Add asparagus until hot.
Add chicken broth and rice; boil.
Cover and remove from heat until liquid is absorbed.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Chop and mix broccoli, onion and bacon.
Add cheese.

title: cabbage strudel
directions: Shred cabbage (about 9 cups).
Toss with salt.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Squeeze out water.
Cook cabbage with onion 1/2 at a time in hot oil.
Remove from heat.
Add pepper.
On pastry cloth stack 4 sheets of dough, brushing each with melted margarine and 1 tablespoon bread crumbs.
Spoon 1/2 cabbage down long side of dough 4 inches from edge.
Fold edge of dough over cabbage and roll up jelly roll fashion.
Place seam-side down in greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan.
Brush top with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Slice into 2-inch pieces.

title: english toffee bars
directions: Mix butter, sugar, vanilla and salt.
Add flour and mix well. Press dough into ungreased 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch pan.
Bake at 300° for 35 minutes. Remove from oven and arrange chocolate bars on top of hot dough.
When melted, spread over dough.
Sprinkle with ground nuts. Cut when cool into bars.

title: vegetable lasagna
directions: Spoon out enough spaghetti sauce to cover bottom of a 13 x 9-inch glass pan.
Shred zucchini and onion; sprinkle in pan. Layer uncooked spaghetti noodles on top and alternate sauce, vegetables and cheese until pan is layered to top.
Sprinkle the Mozzarella cheese on top and completely wrap the glass pan in plastic wrap.
Microwave on High for 15 minutes.
Turn pan and microwave 12 more minutes.
Let sit covered for a few minutes. Serve and enjoy!

title: ice cream in a bag
directions: Place ice in a large ziploc freezer bag.

title: apricot pineapple salad
directions: Mix jello and sugar with hot water.
Stir in cream cheese and baby food.
Stir in pineapple.
Fold in 8 ounces Cool Whip.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan and keep in refrigerator.

title: seven layer magic cookie bars
directions: Melt margarine and sprinkle in graham cracker crumbs and press into buttered 8 x 8 pan. Layer coconut, chips, and nuts over crust in order listed. Drizzle condensed milk over top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. If glass pan is used, bake at 325°. Let cool, cut into bars and store in air tight container.

title: peanut butter temptations
directions: Cream butter, peanut butter and sugar.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture.
Heat oven to 375°.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Place in 1 1/2-inch ungreased muffin pans.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Immediately after baking, press peanut butter cup into center of each ball until just the top shows.
Let cool 10 minutes and carefully remove from pans.
Let cool.
Makes 40 cookies.

title: crab stuffed mushrooms
directions: Place picked crab in a mixing bowl. Add finely minced onion and green pepper to crab meat along with other ingredients except mushrooms. Be careful when folding ingredients together to preserve lump texture of crab.
Wash mushrooms and remove stems. Stuff caps with crab mixture and place in refrigerator for at least 2 hours.
Bake in 350° oven until mushrooms are tender (about 10 minutes). Brown off under broiler and serve immediately.

title: crisp oriental salad
directions: Make dressing of mayonnaise and soy sauce.
Pour over other ingredients and mix until vegetables are coated.
Chill before serving.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Boil until clear and thick the water, cornstarch and sugar. Remove from heat and stir in gelatin until dissolved.
Cool completely.
Stir into glaze thawed strawberries and juice.
Set aside.

title: crab bisque
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan, saute mushrooms, onions and garlic in butter for 5 minutes.
Blend in flour and add stock, stirring until smooth while over medium heat 10 minutes.
Flake crab meat and remove cartilage.
Add crab meat and remaining ingredients and bring to a light boil, reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes.
Serve hot with crackers.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Mix persimmon pulp and eggs together; beat until well-mixed.

title: bottled hell
directions: Puree jalapenos, them measure.
Puree onions and mix in saucepan.
Add vinegar and ketchup.
Simmer, uncovered, for 15 minutes.
Store in refrigerator.

title: see's fudge($5,000 recipe)
directions: Bring milk and sugar to a boil, stirring constantly to soft ball stage.
Add chocolate chips and butter; stir well.
Add Marshmallow Whip, nuts, salt and vanilla; mix well.
Pour into pans.

title: ribbon salad
directions: Dissolve lime Jell-O in 2 C. hot water.
Add 2 C. cold water; pour into 14 x 10 x 2-inch pan.
Chill until partly set.

title: triple-chocolate cherry bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Grease bottom and sides of jelly roll pan, 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch, with shortening; lightly flour. Mix cake mix, pie filling, eggs and chocolate chips in large bowl with spoon. Pour into pan. Bake 20 to 30 minutes. Cool completely, about 1 hour. Frost with frosting.

title: hidden valley ranch oyster crackers
directions: Combine Ranch mix and oil. Add spices. Pour over crackers. Stir to coat. Place in warm oven for 15 to 20 minutes. Store in airtight container.

title: coconut chews
directions: Melt butter in a
saucepan.
Add
sugar
and stir until dissolved.
Cool these ingredients
slightly.
Beat in egg and vanilla, sifted flour, baking
powder
and
salt.
Add coconut and mix thoroughly.
Pour batter
into
greased 8 x 8-inch pan and bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Cut into bars.

title: beans supreme
directions: Fry bacon and onions.
Add baked beans, lima beans, kidney beans, catsup and brown sugar.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: fettucine primavera
directions: In skillet, over medium-high heat, cook broccoli, zucchini, green pepper, onion and basil in butter until vegetables are tender.
Stir in cut tomatoes and mushrooms.

title: easy mexican casserole
directions: Cook hamburger, onion and garlic salt until brown.
Add chili.
Mix in green chili peppers.
In a casserole dish, layer chips, meat mixture and cheese.
Repeat until all used.
Save some cheese for topping.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts.
Cooking time should be 30 minutes.
(You can put casserole in the microwave to melt cheese, if you prefer to do so.)
Serves 4.

title: banana dessert
directions: Mix 1 1/2 cups of graham cracker crumbs with 1/4 cup sugar and 1/3 cup melted margarine.
Press this mixture into bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan firmly and chill it.
Beat 8 ounces of cream cheese with 1/4 cup of sugar and 2 tablespoons milk until smooth.
Fold in 1 3/4 cups Cool Whip and spread over crust.
Slice bananas in an even layer over cream cheese mixture.
Mix instant pudding according to directions.
Pour pudding over bananas.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Just before serving, add Cool Whip and slice bananas on top.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Sprinkle 1/2 cup pecans in greased and floured 10-inch tube pan; set aside.

title: cold lemon chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large skillet, melt margarine over medium heat.
Add chicken breasts and cook, turning once, until light brown, about 4 minutes a side.
Transfer chicken to an 8-inch square baking dish.
Add wine to pan, bring to a boil, scraping bottom of pan with a wooden spoon.
Stir in 2 tablespoons lemon juice and salt.
Pour mixture over chicken.
Cover baking dish with foil and bake for 15 minutes, basting occasionally.
Let chicken cool to room temperature.

title: nancy's pork chop casserole
directions: Cook rice as directed.
Pour uncooked rice in pan; add water. Then place pork chops on top.
Add mushroom soup over pork chops. Bakes in 2 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: roasted red potatoes with skin on
directions: Scrub potatoes; dry. Combine olive oil with rosemary and pepper. Roll potatoes in mixture until well coated. Bake at 400 degrees on an oiled sheet pan until they are tender. Pierce with a toothpick. Tiny yellow squash may be cooked with the same method.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain all of the canned fruit except for the pineapple.
Place fruit, except bananas, in a large mixing bowl and sprinkle with the pudding and Tang.
Gently stir to mix.
The pudding and Tang, along with the juice from the pineapple, will create a delicious sauce.
Refrigerate for several hours.
Just before serving, slice the bananas and mix in.

title: taco pie
directions: Press biscuits into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Brown turkey.
Add onions, bell peppers and the remaining ingredients, except cheese; mix well.
Pour 1/2 of the turkey mixture on semi-baked crust. Sprinkle with 1/2 the cheese.
Add remaining turkey; top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and line a 9 x 13-inch pan with wax paper.
Pour batter into pan, which has been made by mixing together the first 5 ingredients.
Sprinkle the cake mix over batter; pat down lightly.
Sprinkle the chopped pecans over cake mix.
Melt the margarine; pour over cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes; cool for short time.
Turn upside down into another 9 x 13-inch pan.
After cool, top with topping.

title: dijon chicken
directions: Lightly sprinkle chicken with salt, pepper and garlic powder. Combine sour cream and mustard in shallow dish, mixing well.
Dip each chicken breast into mustard mixture and dredge in bread crumbs.
Arrange chicken in a single layer in a baking pan.
Bake at 375° for 50 minutes or until tender.
Serves 6.

title: kahlua delight
directions: Bake chocolate cake according to directions on the box. Prepare a large box of jello chocolate pudding.

Chop Skor or Heath candy bars into small pieces (approximately 4 bars). Break cake into pieces and layer 1/2 of the cake into a bowl and pour Kahlua over cake to moisten; add a layer of pudding, a layer of Cool Whip and a layer of candy (use amount according to your taste). Repeat layers and chill to set.

title: pan coating
directions: Mix the ingredients well to a paste.
Spread a thin coating on bottom of pans.
This does not need to be refrigerated.

title: scalloped potatoes and summer sausage casserole
directions: In a deep casserole dish, put potatoes and 1 1/2 cups of milk. Mix scalloped potatoes and cheese sauce in.
Add butter and sliced sausage.
Mix in chopped onion and chopped pintatoes.
Stir everything together.
Put in oven at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: chicken and broccoli dish
directions: Cook chicken and cut into pieces.
Cook broccoli until almost tender. Cook Rice-A-Roni according to package directions.
Mix the milk with the soup.
Layer cooked Rice-A-Roni in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Next, layer chicken, then broccoli.
Pour soup mixture over all.
Top with grated Cheddar cheese. Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until starts to bubble.

title: pig picking cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Pour batter into 3 cake pans (greased and floured), 9-inch layer pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool.
Frost with frosting.

title: cream cheese cupcakes
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed. Fill cupcake cups half full. Blend cream cheese, egg, sugar, and chocolate chips. Spoon about 1 tsp. on top of cake batter in cup. Bake until top springs back.

title: no-bake cookies
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, milk and butter in a pan.
Bring to a boil.
Boil for 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat. Add oats, peanut butter and vanilla.
Stir well.
Drop on wax paper to make cookie the size desired.

title: grandmama's bread pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until done.
Serve with vanilla ice cream or whipped topping.

title: taco dip
directions: Brown meat and onions.
Add beans, tomato sauce and taco mix. Bring to boil.
Spread in oblong baking dish and cover with 1/2 grated cheese.
Spread sour cream over cheese.
Top with remaining cheese.
Heat in oven at 375° for 15 minutes or until slightly brown.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: people chow
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients in a large saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until melted and smooth.
Add cereal, stirring to coat.
Place half of the powdered sugar in a large paper bag.
Add cereal mixture and remaining half of the powdered sugar.
Gently shake to coat.
Pour mixture onto 2 cookie sheets.
Let dry.
Separate large pieces, if necessary.
Yields 12 cups.

title: coconut cake
directions: In large bowl, blend eggs, sugar, vanilla, butter and milk. Slowly add flour.
Mix 20 minutes until batter is smooth.
Flour 3 round cake pans.
Pour batter in pans and place in preheated oven. Bake 30 minutes.
Let cool.

title: finger salad or vegetable pizza
directions: In large bowl, combine first 3 ingredients.
Stir until dissolved.
Cool to lukewarm.
Sprinkle yeast into 1/4 cup very warm water.
Let stand a few minutes, then stir until dissolved. Add yeast and egg to butter mixture.
Then add flour and salt; mix well.
Pour on well-greased sheet cake pan and press evenly. Fingers need to be very greasy.
Bake at 325° until done, just golden brown.
Cool.
Add the dressing mix to sour cream and spread on dough.
Top with vegetables and cheese.
Cut in pieces and serve.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Wash and stem berries. Soften cream cheese with milk and spread in bottom of pie shell.
Place one-half of the best berries in pie shell.
Heat remaining berries in water.
When berries are soft, add to sugar mixture of cornstarch and salt. Return to heat and cook until thick.
Add food coloring.
Pour over berries in pie shell.
Chill.
Top with whipped cream before serving.

title: basic dessert crepes
directions: In bowl, combine flour, milk, eggs, sugar, oil and salt.
Beat with rotary beater until blended.
Heat a lightly greased 6-inch skillet.
Remove from heat.
Spoon in 2 tablespoons batter. Lif and tilt skillet to spread batter.
Return to heat. Brown on one side.
Invert pan over paper toweling.
Remove crepe.
Repeat to make 16 to 18 crepes, greasing skillet as needed.

title: fudge piediagonal, iowa
directions: Melt chocolate and butter together.
Let cool.
Combine sugar, eggs, flour, salt and vanilla.
Add the chocolate mixture.
Pour into greased pie pan.
Bake until set on the outside, but still soft in the center.
DO NOT OVERBAKE!

title: cranberry bread
directions: Sift together first 5 ingredients.
Add rest of ingredients. Mix well and put in well-greased loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour (very small pans for 45 minutes).

title: al's wondermous chili
directions: Brown ground beef, drain.
Add the onion, celery and garlic to the meat; cook until the onion and celery are tender.

Add the tomatoes, tomato sauce, tomato paste, chilies, cumin, chili powder, oregano, bay leaves, salt, pepper, Worcestershire sauce, seasoned salt and enough of the 2 tablespoons of brown sugar to desired sweetness.
Bring to a boil.
Add kidney beans, reduce heat and simmer on low for 1 1/2 hours.

title: aunt lizzie's chocolate chews
directions: Mix ingredients and bake in a heavily greased 9 x 9-inch pan for 30 to 35 minutes in a 350° oven.
Cool and turn out on to a sheet of wax paper covered with powdered sugar.
Cut into squares while still a little warm.

title: hot berry-brandy punch
directions: In blender or food processor, puree raspberries.
Strain; discard seeds and pulp.
In a Dutch oven, combine raspberry puree and remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil, stirring until sugar dissolves.
Serve warm.

title: sherbet salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
Add sherbet and stir until dissolved.
Put in fruits.
Pour into bowl and chill.

title: steam bread pudding
directions: Put a cup of brown sugar into top of double boiler.
(Make sure there is water in the bottom pot.)
Butter 4 slices of bread on both sides and cut into cubes.
Place on top of brown sugar. Beat 3 eggs and add 2 cups of milk and 1 teaspoon of vanilla and mix well.
Pour over bread.
Do not stir.
Cook until a knife comes out clean for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: ninth street house california chicken salad
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Cool to room temperature.
In a bowl, stir the butter, mayonnaise, parsley, curry powder, garlic, marjoram, salt and pepper.
In a large bowl, combine chicken, grapes and almonds.
Arrange this mixture on lettuce leaf.
Pour the dressing on top and sprinkle paprika.

title: spanish rice
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and pepper.
Drain off grease.
Mash up tomatoes.
Add to meat mixture, then add water and rice.
Simmer about 20 minutes until rice is done.

title: lime pie
directions: Combine egg yolks and milk; mix well.
Add 3 ounces of lime juice slowly.
Add whipped cream.
Mix well.
Pour into crust. Chill.
Garnish with lime slices.
Serve chilled.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix and press into pan.

title: baked vegetable omelet
directions: Layer Monterey Jack cheese, broccoli, tomatoes and Cheddar in an ungreased 8-inch square baking dish.
Beat together remaining ingredients until smooth; pour over cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes, or until egg mixture is set.
Let stand for 10 minutes before cutting.
Serves six.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put muffin mix in last.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch greased pan and bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: baked fish with mushrooms
directions: Thaw fish, if frozen.
Arrange fish in a baking dish, turning thin edges under.
Sprinkle with salt.
Cook mushrooms, onion and tarragon in margarine until tender.
Spoon over fish.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake, covered, in a 450° oven for 6 to 10 minutes, or until fish flakes easily with a fork.
Makes 4 servings.

title: oyster crackers
directions: Mix all except crackers.
Pour over crackers.

title: crusty oven fried chicken
directions: Combine cracker crumbs, sesame seed, salt and pepper.
Dip chicken pieces in butter (melted), then in crumb mixture.
Place on foil lined 13 x 9 x 2-inch and 9 x 9 x 2-inch pans.
Bake 1 hour at 375°.

title: florida white fruit cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar. Add the eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Add the vanilla and lemon extract.
Sift together the flour and baking powder. Combine the cherries, pineapple and pecans. Put flour mixture over this.
Mix and place in cold oven.
Turn oven to 250° and bake for 2 1/2 hours.

title: zucchini fritters
directions: Combine everything but the oil.
Heat oil to 375° and drop batter by tablespoonfuls into oil.
Turn once.
Cook until golden. Drain on paper towels.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix well; serve cold.
May add boiled chopped eggs, celery and green peppers.

title: quick rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients except flour and cool.
Mix in enough flour to make a soft dough.
Put in icebox for 1 hour. Roll and cut out.
Put in pan.
Baste with a little butter and let rise. Bake.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Layer the first 4 ingredients in a casserole or small roaster. Sprinkle with seasoned salt. Mix soup with a little water and pour over top. Bake covered at 350° for 1-1/2 hours.

title: crock-pot beef stew
directions: Mix 3 soups together and put in crock-pot. Add meat and cook on medium 1 hour. Add all vegetables except peas and cook 3 to 4 hours. Add peas last, right before serving, just to heat through. Serve over rice or noodles. Serves 6 to 8.

title: zucchini bars
directions: Peel zucchini and remove seed.
Slice as for apple pie.
Cook in lemon juice about 10 minutes until tender.
Do not overcook. Add sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Simmer 3 minutes.
Add 1/2 cup Crushed Mix to thicken.

title: chicken continental
directions: Combine rice, soups and milk; pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Place chicken on top of this mixture.
Sprinkle onion soup over chicken.
Cover and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: * fudge cookies *
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and boil for 1 minute.
Blend in vanilla, oats and peanut butter.
Spoon out on wax paper to cool. Yields approximately 60.

title: * broiled beefettes *
directions: Combine ground beef, onion soup mix and milk.
Blend thoroughly (shake package of soup to blend ingredients before measuring).
Combine wheat germ and baking powder.
Add this mixture to meat, along with salt and pepper to taste.
Shape mixture into 4 to 6 patties.
Broil in oven or over charcoal.

title: all natural bran muffins
directions: Cream honey and butter until light and mixed well.
Add eggs and beat again.
Add vanilla and dry ingredients and beat until well blended.
Bake in 350° oven approximately 15 to 20 minutes.

title: country vanilla ice cream
directions: Add sugar to beaten eggs.
Beat until mixture is stiff.
Add remaining ingredients.
Freeze it.

title: china pie
directions: Saute onion in frypan with butter; add Vegeburger and mash. Warm it up.
Turn into a greased casserole dish.
Top with green beans.
Top with tomato soup.
Top with mashed potatoes.
Cook in a 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes, until it bubbles on the side.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients and pour into 3-quart casserole dish. Pour 1 stick melted butter over potatoes.
Melt 2nd stick and mix with corn flakes.
Sprinkle over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: out of this world salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water. Add cream cheese and stir until dissolved. Cool.
Add pineapple, sugar, vanilla and pecans. Stir. Add Seven-Up, stir well and chill until set.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: annie's caramel corn
directions: Boil margarine, brown sugar and corn syrup.
After mixture comes to a full boil, add salt, soda and vanilla.
Pour over 7 quarts of popped corn.
Put in large pan and mix well.
Cook in 200° oven for 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: Lightly grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread pineapple with juice over bottom of pan, then spread over that the cherry pie filling.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over the pie filling and sprinkle with nuts.
Slice margarine evenly over all and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: easy chicken breasts
directions: Pour Salsa sauce over chicken in 9x13 pan. Bake at 350° for 45-50 minutes.

title: galliano
directions: Boil water with sugar; cool.
Then add vanilla extract, anise extract and lemon or lime juice.
Then add vodka.
Put mixture in blender and add yellow food coloring.

title: brownies
directions: Cream together margarine, sugar and eggs.
Add chocolate syrup, flour, nuts and vanilla.
Spread in 10 x 15-inch pan.
Bake at
350° for 30 minutes.
Cool.

title: celebration punch
directions: Combine tea powder and water and stir until tea is thoroughly dissolved.
Add concentrates and cranberry cocktail.
Blend well. Just before serving, pour over ice in a punch bowl and add ginger ale.
Makes 4 gallons or 100 (5 ounce) servings.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Heat green beans and mushrooms in saucepan. Drain.
Add cream of mushroom soup and 1 cup cheese.
Mix well. Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until bubbly.

title: deer roast
directions: Place hams and water in a crock-pot.
Combine the other ingredients with the roast.
Cook overnight.
To thicken gravy, mix water and cornstarch and add to gravy.
Serve with rice.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix in the order given.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes or until firm in a 350° oven.

title: lomi salmon
directions: Combine ingredients, mash salmon and put in refrigerator with 4 ice cubes on top.
Chill 1 hour or longer.
Stir before serving. Serve chilled.

title: mexican dip
directions: Layer cream cheese, chili and cheese, keeping cheese on top in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° until brown, about 10 minutes. Serve with chips.

title: dill meatballs
directions: Mix hamburger, rice, egg, parsley, onion, dill weed, salt and pepper.
Roll into meatballs; brown in frying pan.
Add tomato juice, water and butter.
Simmer for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: pickled beans
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients, layer alternately with salt in jar; weight down.
Cover with cold water.
Let stand for 1 week and pack in sterilized jars.
Pressure 5 minutes at 10 pounds.

title: banana berry cooler
directions: Place all ingredients in a blender.
Blend on high for 30 seconds or until smooth.
For extra refreshing drink, add 1/2 cup ice and blend well.
Makes 2 (8-ounce) servings.

title: ole barbecue bake
directions: Cook meat and onion; drain off fat.
Mix barbecue sauce and meat and spread in ovenproof dish.
Mix eggs and sour cream together.
Spread sour cream mixture over meat, then spread corn chips over sour cream mixture.
Cook 30 to 40 minutes at 350°, then sprinkle cheese and cook 5 minutes longer.

title: mexican chicken with rice
directions: Sprinkle chicken with salt, paprika and pepper.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes.
Combine 2 to 3 packages bouillon, oregano, bay leaves, peas, onion and rice in baking dish.
Top with chicken. Cover with foil.
Bake until liquid is absorbed and chicken is done at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain.
Add soup, tomato sauce and green chiles.
Put some in pan; cover with chips.
Top with layer of American cheese.
Cover and bake at 350° until melted.
May add more layers to make thicker.
I usually double layers.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Fry hamburger and onion, together.
Add macaroni and spaghetti sauce; mix together.
Layer.

title: potato bake
directions: Slice potatoes thin, with or without peeling.
Melt 1/2 stick margarine in approximately 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Layer potatoes, salt, pepper and diced onion.
Cover with 1/4 Velveeta cheese and bake, uncovered, for 45 minutes at 350° or until tender.

title: steak casserole
directions: Add all ingredients in order given in a casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sugar-free raspberry pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into two crust pie and bake.

title: chicken with peppers and tomatoes
directions: Brown chicken in oil about 5 minutes.
Remove chicken and set aside.
Add garlic, tomato and yellow pepper; saute until pepper is tender, about 5 minutes.
Add chicken, basil and wine.
Cover and simmer until chicken is tender, about 20 minutes.
Season with salt and pepper.
Remove chicken, etc., from skillet and keep warm.
Cook liquids down over high heat until half the amount; spoon over chicken.
Serve over rice.

title: hot dog relish
directions: Grind vegetables together (onion, cabbage, tomatoes and peppers).
Let stand overnight.
Drain.
Combine all ingredients and heat to boiling.
Simmer until tender.
Put in jars.
Seal. Enjoy!

title: cowboy stew
directions: In a large pot, put a small bit of oil and saute garlic, onion, bell pepper and meat.
Add chili powder and sugar.
Add tomatoes and two cans of water.
Mash tomatoes until they are in small pieces.
Add rest of vegetables.
Bring to a boil and then simmer until vegetables are tender.
Makes a large pot of stew.

title: watermelon star salad
directions: Cut watermelon slice into 5 wedges.
Cut rind from wedge. Arrange wedges on salad greens in circle with points outward to resemble star.
Spoon cottage cheese into center of watermelon star.
Sprinkle with blueberries. Serve with 1-2-3 Fruit Dressing.

title: buttermilk
directions: Mix and let stand 5 minutes.

title: poo's pizza pie
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Stir in sugar, salt and oil. Add flour and beat vigorously about 20 strokes.
Let rest 10 to 15 minutes.
Spread on greased pizza pan.
Bake at 450° for 8 minutes.
Add favorite sauce and toppings.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes more.

title: richard's caso
directions: Place first three ingredients in blender or food processor. Blend well.
Chop onions and garlic.
Saute in hot oil or margarine.
Mix in Ro-Tel mixture and simmer about 15 minutes to reduce liquid.
Gradually add Velveeta.
Serve warm or cold with tortilla chips or raw vegetables.

title: creamy cheese pie(great diet breakfast)
directions: Mix all ingredients in a blender until smooth.
Pour in pans sprayed with "Pam."
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Cool.
Cut into 8ths.
One sections equals breakfast protein.

title: dorian's stuff your face stuffing
directions: After fixing stuffing according to directions on the box, mix the rest of the ingredients together in a casserole dish and bake uncovered at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: hamburger helper venetian noodles
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a small saucepan, heat oil; add onion, mushrooms, garlic and oregano.
Cook over low heat, stirring occasionally, until onion is soft.
Stir in tomato sauce and pepper.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

Grease cookie sheet with margarine. Take casings off sausages and break up into pieces and cook with a little salt and a couple tablespoons of water to prevent sticking. When cooked, let the sausage cool for a couple of minutes. Meanwhile, roll out dough onto a floured countertop.
Roll the dough about the size of a pizza.
Try not to roll the dough too thin.
Sprinkle the crumbled sausage on the dough, leaving about a 2-inch edge all around.
Spread broccoli on top of sausage. Sprinkle the Mozzarella cheese on top of broccoli, then sprinkle with oregano.

title: cherry mini-cheese cakes
directions: Beat all ingredients except wafers together until light and fluffy.
Crush a few wafers very fine.
Butter small muffin pans generously; dust with the wafer crumbs.
Put a vanilla wafer in the bottom of each cup.
Fill cups 3/4 full with cream cheese mixture.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until lightly brown at 375°; cool.
Top with 1 tablespoon of cherry pie filling, then whipped cream.

title: famous oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix well; bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: grandma's gingerbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: snowballs
directions: Mix pecans, pineapple and butter together.
Stack vanilla wafers in 4's with pineapple mixture between.
Place in freezer. When cold or frozen, cover with whipped cream and roll in coconut.

title: cherry salad
directions: Drain juice from pineapple.
Bring juice and water to a boil. Add jello to hot liquid and mix.
Add cherry pie filling and cola. Let partially congeal before adding pineapple.
Chill until firm.

title: easy whole wheat rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in a large bowl.
Add shortening, eggs, sugar and salt.
Beat together in mixer or stir real well. Gradually stir in enough of both flours to create a soft dough. Turn out.
Knead until smooth.
Place in a well-greased bowl. Cover and let rise in warm place until doubled.
Punch dough down. Roll out to thickness desired.
Cut with biscuit cutter.
Place on greased cookie sheet about 2-inches apart.
Cover; let rise in warm place about 30 minutes.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Brush top with melted butter, if desired.
I always butter mine with real butter as soon as they come out of oven.
Makes lots, about 4 dozen.

title: company casserole
directions: Brown meat in large skillet.
Add onions, peppers, salt and pepper.
Add soups and noodles; heat thoroughly.
Place in large greased baking dish (9 x 14 x 2-inches).
Sprinkle with bread or cracker crumbs and add grated Parmesan cheese.
Bake 45 minutes at 325°.
Serves 16.

title: turtle candy cake
directions: Combine cake mix, melted butter
and 1/2 cup evaporated milk. Pour 3/4 of batter into
9	x 13-inch well-greased pan. Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Combine
caramels
with
the 1/3 cup evaporated	milk and melt.	Pour
over
partially
cooked cake. The pour chocolate chips
over
caramel and pour pecans over chocolate chips.
Top with spoonfuls of remaining batter. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: goulash
directions: Brown hamburger meat (drain), then add tomatoes and catsup. Boil noodles and mix all together.
Add salt and pepper.
Boil for about 10 minutes.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Egg, bread and fry "cut up" chicken pieces; set aside.
Slice green peppers and onions.
(Hint:
To help eliminate frying time, I place in separate bowls with some water, cover and microwave each until softened, not mushy!)

title: frosty lime punch
directions: Mix limeade, lemonade, water and lemon juice.
Chill.
Spoon in sherbet.
Pour Sprite down side of bowl.
Mix gently.
Garnish with fruit slices.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Brown hamburger, onion, celery, salt, pepper, garlic salt and onion salt.
Add flour and vinegar.
Layer hamburger mix, zucchini, tomatoes and Cheddar cheese in casserole.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes, covered, 30 minutes uncovered.

title: rosemary potatoes
directions: In a large skillet, cook and stir the garlic and rosemary in the olive oil for 1 to 2 minutes over medium heat.
Add potatoes, salt and pepper.
Cook for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally. Reduce the heat to medium-low and cook about 20 minutes more, turning often, until the potatoes are brown and crisp.
Garnish with the rosemary sprigs, if desired.
Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: cinnamon logs
directions: Cream together the first 4 ingredients. Add the flour and mix well. Chill. Roll into strips 1/2-inch diameter.
Tine with fork. Cut on slant about 1 to 1 1/2-inches long or form balls with 1/2 rounded teaspoonful dough. Flatten with thumb. Bake in a 300° oven for 20 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet.
Roll logs in powdered sugar while warm or put dot of icing or a chocolate chip in indent make by thumb.

title: baked apple french toast
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spray 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer pan with sliced bread, double deep.
Place eggs in batter bowl and beat lightly.
Add 1/4 cup sugar, milk and vanilla.
Pour half liquid over bread.
Peel, core and slice apples; place on top of bread. Pour remaining egg mixture over bread.

title: honey mustard chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 425 degrees.
Place the chicken breasts on a 10 x 15 inch rimmed cookie sheet that has been coated with nonstick cooking spray.
In a small bowl, combine the remaining ingredients; mix well.
Spread the mixture evenly over the chicken breasts.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes, or until topping is golden and no pink remains in the chicken.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Melt margarine in oblong baking dish. Pour into mixture and bake until bubbly and brown in 325° oven, about 1 hour.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Put chicken (torn up) in bottom of pan.
Pour gravy on top of chicken.
Mix stuffing by directions on box; put on top of gravy. Cover with aluminum foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until done and cut into small pieces.
Prepare rice according to package.
Drain water chestnuts and green beans. Combine all ingredients in casserole dish.
Mix well.
Cook 45 minutes at 350°.

title: cooked fruit salad
directions: Mix together the Tang, vanilla pudding and 1 cup of the pineapple juice; if there isn't enough liquid to make a cup, use water
or juice from fresh orange juice.
Cook the pudding mixture until it becomes clear and slightly thickened.
Add the pudding mixture to the fruit and let stand for 1 hour or overnight.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Place pieces of chicken in a skillet; add salt and pepper to taste.
Pour barbecue sauce and 7-Up over chicken.
Simmer on top of stove for at least one hour.
Happy eating.

title: easy beef stroganoff
directions: Saute meat and onion; add soup, water and sour cream.
Cook noodles as directed; drain noodles and layer with meat mixture in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts.

title: chocolate candy
directions: In microwave, melt chips and shortening until smooth.
Remove from microwave; stir in raisins and nuts.

title: bertha's skillet(easy for children and teens)
directions: Brown meat; saute onion in large casserole dish.
Drain. Sprinkle dry noodles over meat.
Add dry seasonings, then pour tomatoes, sauce and very little water over noodles.
Stir only slightly; meat, noodles and sauce should remain layered.
Bring mixture to a boil.
Reduce to low heat, cover and let simmer for 20 minutes, or until water is absorbed.
Do not stir.
Let sit for about 10 to 15 minutes before serving.

title: sour cream cake
directions: Grease and flour a 10-inch tube pan.
Heat oven to 300°. Separate eggs while cold.
Warm yolks and whites to room temperature.
In large bowl, cream together butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Sift flour 3 times.
Mix baking soda into sour cream.
Add flour and sour cream to butter mixture alternately.
Add almond and vanilla extract.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold into batter.
Pour into pan and bake for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours or until cake tester comes out clean.

title: chocolate mousse cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare and bake cake mix according to package directions for two 9-inch layers.
Remove from pans; cool thoroughly.
In large bowl, beat sweetened condensed milk and melted chocolate until well blended.
Gradually beat in water, then dry pudding mix until smooth.
Chill at least 30 minutes. Beat until smooth.
Fold in whipped cream.
Chill at least 1 hour. Place 1 cake layer on plate; top with 1 1/2 cups mousse mixture. Place other layer on top; spread top with remaining mousse mixture or cover entire cake with mousse.
Chill.
Store covered in refrigerator.

title: squash dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Pour into an oiled oblong dish.
Pour 1/4 pound of butter over top of mixture.
Bake at 425° or until brown.

title: hard candy(double batch)
directions: Boil to 300°.
Take off heat and divide in different dishes. Add color and flavors.
Pour on cookie sheet covered with powdered sugar.
Cut with scissors while still warm.
(For 4 cups, use 1 gram of oil flavoring.)

title: oven-fried fish fillets
directions: Preheat oven to 500° (very hot).
If frozen fish is used, thaw it enough to separate pieces.
Dip fish into well-seasoned French dressing, then into bread crumbs.
Arrange on an oiled baking pan or on an ovenproof platter.
Pour any remaining French dressing over fish.
Bake for 10-12 minutes or until the fish flakes easily when tested with a fork.
Makes 4 servings, 4 oz. each.

title: eggless cake
directions: Sift or mix together all dry ingredients.
Place in oblong ungreased baking pan (9 x 13-inch).
Make 3 vertical groves.
Mix Crisco, vinegar and vanilla; pour in groves.
Pour water over everything and mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until cake is done.

title: frozen fruit chunks
directions: Combine all but cherries.
Use enough red food coloring to tint pink. Cut cherries in half or chop.
Fold cherries into mixture.
Spread into lightly oiled Pyrex dish (13 1/2 x 8 3/4 x 1 3/4-inch).
Freeze until firm.
Cut into chunks with sharp knife. Serve on lettuce or in sherbet dish or eat like a popsicle.

title: salad supreme
directions: Prepare jello according to package directions.
Add drained pineapple (reserve juice).
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup nuts.
Chill until congealed.
Mix Cool Whip and cream cheese.
Spread on congealed jello.
Chill.
Add enough water to pineapple juice to make 1 cup.
Combine lemon juice, sugar, flour and eggs.
Add to pineapple juice and cook over medium heat until thick.
Chill. When mixture is cool, spread over cream cheese mixture.
Sprinkle nuts on top. Yields 10 to 15 servings.

title: ham dip
directions: Soften cream cheese and stir. Then add 3 packages of ham, onions, Worcestershire sauce and Accent.
Form into ball and roll in remaining ham or put all ham into the mixture.
Serve without being in ball form.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies(microwave)
directions: Combine sugar
and
cocoa
in a large bowl.
Add butter and milk.
Microwave on High for 4 minutes; stir at half time. Add vanilla,
then
add
oats and peanut butter.
Stir.
Pour into a buttered dish until firm.

title: cherry cobbler
directions: Make a batter of flour, sugar, salt, baking powder and milk. Melt margarine in an 8 or 9-inch square or round pan.
Pour batter over melted butter.
Do not stir.
Over top of batter, pour fruit. Sprinkle with desired spice.
Bake for one hour at 350°.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix ingredients together and let stand for about 1/2 hour before serving.
Serve with raw vegetables.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Save 1/4 cup cheese to sprinkle on top.
Cook spaghetti until tender; drain.
Mix other ingredients; cook in greased casserole dish at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: auntie ann's swiss braided bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water and sugar.
In a saucepan, melt butter, add milk until warm, add beaten eggs.
In a large bowl, put flour and salt, make a well and dump in yeast and milk mixture. Stir well, knead and return to a greased bowl to raise.
Place in oven preheated to 120° (turned off) for a half hour to rise. Return dough to counter, divide into 4 pieces and braid, one end will be larger than the other, brush with an egg yolk.
Return to oven again at 120° for 10 minutes, then turn up to 425° and bake 30 to 40 minutes.

title: grandmother's cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add the juice plus enough water to equal 2 cups.
Add remaining ingredients and pour into 1 large mold or 12 individual molds.
Refrigerate until set.
Yield: 10 to 12 servings.

title: australian meat pie
directions: Heat the oven to 350°.
Brown the ground beef; drain.
Add the catsup, salt, milk and bread crumbs.
Spoon this mixture into the pie shell.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Mix the Worcestershire sauce and cheese.
Spread this over the meat mixture.
Return the pie to the oven until the cheese melts.

title: baked chicken salad(serves 12 to 15)
directions: Cook chicken until tender and easily removed from bone.
Chop chicken and vegetables.
Combine all ingredients, except noodles, and pour into large baking dish.
Bake, covered, for 35 to 40 minutes.
Uncover and sprinkle noodles over top.
Return to oven for about 15 minutes, leaving cover off.

title: oriental tomato-cucumber salad
directions: Core and dice tomatoes.
Peel and halve cucumber lengthwise. Scoop out seeds using a spoon and slice.
Mix sesame oil, soy sauce, red pepper and sugar.
Add cucumber, tomatoes and onions; toss gently.
Sprinkle with sesame seed.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: hot pineapple side dish
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 1/4 cup juice.
Set aside.
In medium bowl combine sugar and flour.
Add the oleo and 1 cup of cheese and mix well.
Stir in pineapple.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle crushed crackers on top and drizzle with reserved juice.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until bubbly around edges.
Remove and sprinkle with remaining cheese.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix crumbs and melt butter.
Press into bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat powdered sugar, vanilla and butter together for 10 minutes.
Add eggs, continue to beat.
Spread over crumbs layer. Peel bananas and cut in half lengthwise.
Place over creamed layer.
Drain pineapple; spoon over bananas.
Cover with cool whip.
Sprinkle pecans and add cherries.
Chill for 2 hours.

title: blueberry icebox pie
directions: Mix Cool Whip, milk and lemon juice with mixer.
Fold in berries and nuts.
Fill pie crusts and chill.

title: asparagus soup
directions: Cut off tough ends of asparagus and discard.
Boil remainder in salted water until done (about 20 minutes).
Pour contents in blender.
Add butter and cream; blend for 2 minutes.
No flour is needed, as blending thickens soup.
Reheat and serve.
Sprinkle top with black pepper.

title: brazilian snow
directions: Grind coffee in a small nut grinder as finely as possible. Sprinkle about half of coffee over ice cream.
Scoop up ice cream one scoop at a time.
Try to mix without over handling ice cream. As you finish one layer of ice cream, sprinkle coffee over the top until all coffee and ice cream are in the serving dishes.
Garnish with whipped cream and sprinkle with coffee and cherries.
Serve at once.
Serves 4.

title: split pea soup
directions: Rinse peas and drain.
Combine all ingredients in soup kettle, cover and simmer 2 hours or until peas are tender.
Remove ham bone from soup, cut off meat and return meat to soup.
Mash peas slightly, if desired.
Makes 8 servings.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Chop onion and crush Ritz crackers fine.
Chop mushroom stems; save caps.
Mix all ingredients together.
Stuff mushroom caps; place under broiler for 5 to 8 minutes.

title: easy fruit dip
directions: Cheese and topping should be at room temperature.
Mix together.
Serve with sliced fruit.
Apples are very good with this dip.

title: cheesy potato soup
directions: Dice potatoes, onion and celery fine and place in large pan. Cover with chicken broth.
Bring to a boil.
Turn down heat; cook until vegetables are tender.
Remove from heat; mash vegetables slightly.
Melt butter; add flour and blend well.
Add milk and bring to boil.
Cook until slightly thickened.
Place vegetables back on heat; add thickened milk.
Blend well; add cheese.
Cook until slightly thickened.
If too thick, add more milk.
Simmer 10 minutes.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Unroll
crescent
rolls and place in greased pizza pan. Mix cooked sausage and hash browns and place on top of dough. Sprinkle with
cheese.
Mix eggs with milk and pour over meat mixture. Bake
at
for
to
minutes.
Yield:
8 slices.

title: herbed cornish hens
directions: Rub hens with oil.
Combine oil, salt, pepper, poultry seasoning and cayenne; stir well.
Coat hens with seasoning mixture and refrigerate 3 to 4 hours.
Place hens in 2 (13 x 9-inch) baking pans.
Sprinkle hens with lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, parsley flakes and celery.
Place 1 green pepper ring and 1 slice onion on each hen; secure with a toothpick.
Pour enough wine into pans to cover bottom.

title: broccoli italian style
directions: Wash broccoli.
Look over carefully. Trim stalks.
Remove all large coarse leaves.
Cut stalks and flowerets into large pieces. Heat oil in a large skillet.
Add garlic, onion and chili powder. Stir and heat until onion is soft.
Remove garlic and discard. Add broccoli, water and salt.
Cover skillet. Cook 12 to 15 minutes or until just tender.
Serve immediately.
Makes 4 servings.

title: creamsicle pie
directions: In pie crust, layer vanilla ice cream, thin layer of orange sherbet and another layer of vanilla ice cream.
Put whipped cream on edge.
Top with pineapple when served.

title: lemon muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In large mixing bowl, mix flour, sugar, lemon peel, baking powder, soda and salt.
Make a "well" in the center.
In a medium container, whisk together yogurt, butter, egg and lemon juice.
Add this mixture to the "well" and stir until just blended.
Batter will be lumpy.
Spoon into muffin cups, filling 3/4 full.
Bake until tester comes out clean, about 20 minutes.
Meanwhile, prepare glaze.

title: butter roll
directions: Roll out your biscuit dough to 1/2 inch thick.
Layer it in a baking dish with butter and sugar. When dish is about half full, finish by pouring the milk and vanilla over it.
Bake at 400° until brown.
Remember this will rise, don't fill your pan to full.

title: chicken francaise
directions: Mix lemon juice, wine, water, margarine, chicken base, pepper and garlic in a 2-quart saucepan and heat. Add cornstarch. Put aside. Cut up chicken cutlets into 2 ounce pieces. Dip chicken pieces in flour. Turn in beaten eggs. Heat corn oil in pan. Cook chicken approximately 3 minutes on each side until light brown. Drain oil and add sauce you put aside. Simmer for approximately 5 minutes. Makes 2 servings.

title: succotash
directions: Clean
and wash beans.	Cover beans with water and soak overnight.	Drain.	Place
beans,
pork, salt and enough water to cover
ingredients	in a 12-inch Dutch oven.
Cook with lid on. Place 8
coals on top and 8 coals on the bottom for 1 1/2 hours. Add water if needed.
Add corn.
Stir and cook for 1/2 hour more. Replenish coals as needed.

title: chicken continental
directions: Saute onion in butter; put in bottom of casserole (do not stir into other ingredients).
Mix chicken, soups, water chestnuts, mushrooms, tortillas and onion; spread half of this mixture into casserole dish over butter and onion.
Spread half of shredded cheese over it; add rest of mixture and spread remaining cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: scotch broth(for soup)
directions: Put bones, water and salt in a large saucepan. Bring to a boil; skim water. Add bay leaf, cloves, sprigs of parsley and chopped onion. Simmer 2 to 2 1/2 hours until meat is done. Take out the meat and cut into small pieces when cool. Strain the stock; add barley. When barley is half done or tender, add carrots, celery, turnip and diced onions. Cook until the vegetables are tender. Add meat; skim off fat. Simmer a few minutes more. Add chopped parsley.

title: ranch oyster crackers
directions: Empty crackers into large container and sprinkle with all dry ingredients and toss.
Pour corn oil on crackers and toss frequently for 12 hours before use.

title: nestle's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a small bowl combine flour, soda and salt.
Set aside. In a large bowl combine shortening, sugar and vanilla.
Beat until creamy.
Beat in eggs.
Gradually add flour mixture and mix well.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.

title: apple cream cheese coffee cake
directions: Cut cream cheese and margarine into baking mix.
Stir in milk. Turn dough onto cloth covered surface well dusted with baking mix; gently roll in baking mix to coat.
Knead lightly 8 to 10 times.
Roll into rectangle, 12 x 8-inches; place on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Spread Cream Cheese Filling down center of rectangle.
Make cuts, 2 1/2-inches long at 1-inch intervals on 12-inch sides of rectangle.
Fold strips ove filling, overlapping. Mix sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle over top.
Cover and refrigerate up to 24 hours.

title: chocolate crunch cake
directions: Mix together flour, sugar and pecans.
Melt margarine and pour over flour mixture.
Press into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Press as flat as you can on bottom and sides of pan.
Bake until light brown in preheated oven at 350°.

title: frozen mud
directions: Mix all ingredients together until firm.
Put into cupcake cups or whatever.
Freeze for at least 3 hours before serving.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Melt margarine and pour over crushed crackers; set aside. Thaw broccoli in microwave. Mix soup and cheese in saucepan over medium heat. Put broccoli in baking dish. Pour cheese mixture over broccoli. Top with buttered cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: chicken pie
directions: Place chicken in casserole dish.
Add eggs.
Mix broth and soup.
Pour over chicken.
Melt margarine.
Add flour and milk and mix.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 375° until crust is brown. Batter will form crust.
tags: cream of chicken soup or cream of celery soup

title: chicken-almond supreme
directions: Melt butter; add flour or cornstarch and stir until smooth. Add broth; mix well.
Blend in half of the cheese and all other ingredients except bread crumbs.
Spread half of the bread crumbs in bottom of pan.
Put chicken mixture in pan next and sprinkle top with paprika and celery salt.
Spread the remaining cheese on top and top with remaining bread crumbs.
Bake 30 minutes at 350° in a 9 x 13-inch pan or until bubbly.
Serve on hot rice.

title: watergate salad
directions: Put Cool Whip in bowl.
Sprinkle with pudding mix. Add pineapple, including juice, marshmallows and nuts.
Mix well and refrigerate overnight.

title: tuna noodle
directions: Combine soup and water.
Add 1 cup noodles, drained tuna, cooked celery and cooked onion.
Place in a dish and sprinkle remaining noodles over top.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: percolator punch
directions: Combine all of the above into an electric percolator, or in a large saucepan, and simmer 10 minutes.

title: cajun cabbage
directions: Blend and cook cabbage, vinegar, oil and sugar until done. Add Ro-Tel and cook an additional 5 minutes.

title: easy cherry cheese pie
directions: In a large bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in milk until smooth.
Stir in lemon juice and vanilla.
Pour into crust.
Chill 3 hours or until set.
Top with pie filling before serving.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: pumpkin dessert
directions: Mix ingredients.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: vegetable cheese soup
directions: In a large saucepan, melt margarine to coat pan and saute chopped onions. Add milk and chopped pieces of cheese and warm to melt on medium heat.
Add precooked (slightly) broccoli and cauliflower.
Add celery, zucchini and garlic salt.
Warm until done and vegetables are desired texture.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Add Cheese Nips to cover top.
Cook another 15 minutes.

title: wild rice, sausage and oyster dressing
directions: Cook rice according to package directions; drain.
Place in bowl.
Drain oysters, reserving liquid.
Chop oysters and add to rice.
Fry sausage until brown.
Break into small pieces.
Drain off fat.
Mix with rice and oysters.
Melt butter in skillet and stir-fry carrots, celery and onion.
Cook for 10 minutes on low heat.
Stir in mushrooms and oyster liquid.
Cook 10 to 15 minutes.
Add to rice mixture.
Stir in cornbread stuffing, nuts, eggs and salt and pepper to taste.

title: banana punch
directions: Boil 6 cups of water with 4 cups of sugar.
Let cool.
Mix all other ingredients with boiled sugar water and freeze.
Pour ginger ale over to serve.

title: spaghetti pork chops
directions: Brown chops in a large skillet.
On top of each pork chop, place 1 tablespoon brown sugar and 1 tablespoon vinegar.
Add spaghetti and tomatoes.
Cover and simmer until spaghetti is done. Very good.

title: diabetic lemon pie
directions: Mix milk and pudding with mixer; add Crystal Lite and then Cool Whip.
Pour into 2 graham cracker pie crusts or 2 regular pie crusts already browned.

title: clam dip
directions: Let cream cheese stand at room temperature for 1 hour.
In a bowl, mix cream cheese and all other ingredients together; mix well.
If dip is too thick, add a little clam juice until smooth. Chill for 1/2 hour.

title: creamed tomatoes
directions: Cook tomatoes until tender. Add salt and sugar.
Mix flour, milk and sour cream. Whisk it.

title: sad cake
directions: Mix throughly and bake at 350° about 30 minutes.

title: sweet and sour sauce
directions: Combine cornstarch and pineapple juice until dissolved well. Bring water, vinegar and sugar to a boil.
Add first ingredients into hot liquid and cook until it is thick as desired.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: corn salad
directions: Chill and drain before serving.
Can be made 1 or 2 days ahead.

title: carottes glacees avec raisins(glazed carrots with grapes)
directions: In a saucepan with a cover, boil the carrots slowly in the stock, sugar, pepper and butter for 30 to 40 minutes until the carrots are tender and the liquid has reduced to a syrupy glaze. Correct seasoning and add the splash of cognac.
Reheat just before serving; gently toss the grapes in with the carrots, rolling them delicately in the pan to coat them with syrup.
Turn into a hot vegetable dish and sprinkle with parsley.
Serve immediately.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: elegant meringue
directions: Beat egg whites and salt until stiff.
Add Marshmallow Creme. Continue to beat until stiff peaks form.
Spread on pie and brown.

title: poodle cake
directions: Mix above ingredients and bake in 350°
oven until golden brown in a 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: yellow squash souffle
directions: Wash squash, brushing skins.
Slice and cook until tender. Drain very well, rinsing water out of squash.
Blend squash, cream cheese, first amount of butter and salt.
Place in buttered pan. Top with cracker crumbs and top with remaining butter.
Bake 30 minutes uncovered at 350°.
Serves 7.

title: country candied yams
directions: Place water, yams and all other ingredients in a pan.
Cover and bring to a boil.
Lower fire and simmer until done and liquid thickens.
Pour yams in casserole dish.
Place in oven, uncovered, and cook for 1 hour at 350°.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Combine sugar and cocoa in a bowl; mix well. Add butter and eggs; beat well. Stir in milk and beat all ingredients until well blended. Pour into pie shell and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until set.

title: best dessert ever
directions: Crust - mix flour, oleo, and pecans and press into pie pan. Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes. Cool Completely. Mix, cream cheese, sugar, and mix well. Fold in cool whip. Spread on crust. Mix chocolate pudding, vanilla pudding and milk. Spread on top of cream cheese mixture. Top with remaining cool whip.

title: crunchy chicken casserole
directions: Remove chicken from bones and cut into bite size pieces.
Put chicken in casserole.
Combine soups and sour cream; pour over chicken.

title: old fashioned chocolate cobbler
directions: Heat oven to 350 degrees.

Mix flour, sugar, 2 Tbsp. cocoa, baking powder and salt in ungreased 2 quart pan (9 x 9 inch pan). In a small bowl mix milk, butter and vanilla; add to flour mixture and stir with fork until mixed and smooth.
Stir in nuts and spread the dough evenly in the pan.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and 1/4 cup cocoa.
Pour hot water over batter;
DO NOT STIR.

title: dessert for twenty or death by chocolate
directions: Bake cake as directed in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cut into 1-inch squares when cool.
Mix pudding with milk.
Chop up the Heath bars in a blender.
Night before serving, layer cake, pudding, Cool Whip and Heath bars; repeat.
You should be able to make three layers. Use a Tupperware cake server upside down or a punch bowl to layer it in.
This recipe can be cut in half.
A yellow cake mix and vanilla pudding or other variations may be used instead.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients; put in crust.
Cover with crust.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Take from oven; cut hole the size of a quarter.
Pour in mixture of remaining ingredients and all of top which you cut out.
Bake another 5 minutes or until brown.

title: oatmeal raisin spice cookies
directions: Sift flour,
baking powder, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg into a bowl.
Add shortening, brown sugar, eggs and half of the milk. Beat until smooth.
Add rest of milk, raisins and oats.
Drop by spoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes. Makes 3 to 4 dozen.

title: coffee roast
directions: *Leftover coffee can be used to substitute the instant coffee and water, as long as there is 4 cups liquid.

title: peppy stuffed peppers
directions: Cut green peppers in half.
Remove seeds and wash peppers. Lightly mix ground beef, rice, onion, salt, pepper and 1/2 can Hunt's tomato sauce.
Fill pepper halves, arrange in baking dish. Pour remaining tomato sauce over peppers.
Cover tightly and bake at 350°
for 1 hour or until peppers are tender.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: squash supreme
directions: *Zucchini may be substituted.

title: egg pancakes
directions: Beat eggs.
Add milk and vanilla.
Add liquid ingredients to dry ingredients; beat until smooth.
Heat and lightly butter a skillet.
Drop batter into 3-inch circles.
Brown on both sides. Serve with butter, syrup, applesauce or fruit of choice.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Slice tomatoes 1/4-inch thick.
Let set in salad dressing about 5 minutes.
Roll in flour and fry until brown (Fry Baby works great).
No need for salt if salad dressing is used. Slightly turned tomatoes are wonderful cooked this way.

title: mock toffee squares
directions: Melt sugar and butter. Boil 3 minutes. Layer saltine crackers on foil-lined cookie sheet. Pour sugar mixture over crackers and bake at 400° for 5 minutes. Sprinkle chocolate chips over hot crackers and spread with spatula. Press chopped nuts into chocolate. Cool in fridge and break into pieces.

title: baked chicken parmesan(low-fat and low cholesterol)
directions: In a paper bag, put seasoning, cheese, parsley and crumbs. Coat chicken by shaking.
Oil a roasting pan and pour in the water.
Arrange chicken pieces.
Sprinkle chicken with oil and margarine.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 30 minutes.
Pour wine over chicken.
Lower heat to 325° and cover pan with foil.
Bake 15 minutes longer.
Remove foil and bake at 350° 10 minutes longer.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Flake crab meat; mix softened cream cheese and mayonnaise. Add crab meat and blend.
Put mixture in a 9 x 9-inch Pyrex dish. Sprinkle with paprika and dill seed.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serve with crackers.

title: apricot cake
directions: Mix oil and sugar.
Break eggs, one at a time.
Sift flour with salt and soda.
Beat well.
Bake at 350°.
Test in 30 minutes.

title: chicken breasts italian(low-fat)
directions: Dip chicken breasts in milk, then in remaining ingredients. Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: garfield's easy lasagne
directions: Brown beef; drain off excess fat.
Add sauce and water. Simmer for 10 minutes.
Combine remaining ingredients except for the lasagne.
Pour 1 cup of sauce on the bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Layer 3 pieces of uncooked lasagne over sauce. Cover with about 1 1/2 cups of sauce.
Spread half of cheese filling over sauce.
Repeat layers of lasagne, sauce and cheese filling.
Top with layer of lasagne and remaining sauce.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake at 350° for 60 minutes.
Remove foil and bake for 10 more minutes.
Cool for 10 minutes and serve.

title: mama's fruit cake
directions: Mix the first 9 ingredients as any cake, then add gradually the raisins, citron, nuts and currants.

title: shrimp, spinach and basil pizza bianca
directions: Place crust on sprayed cookie sheet.
Combine cornstarch, milk and garlic in a small pan.
Whisk, bringing to a boil.
Cook 1 minute; add salt and pepper.
Spread on crust.
Heat a nonstick skillet coated with Pam over medium heat.
Saute shrimp three minutes.
Add mushrooms.
Saute 2 minutes.
Stir in spinach and cook until spinach wilts.
Drain.
Spoon mixture over sauce. Sprinkle with oregano and basil.
Top with cheeses.
Bake at 425° for 8 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: meat loaf pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine first 7 ingredients gently.
Put into 9-inch pie plate, forming shell around edge.
Then combine next 4 ingredients with 1/2 cup cheese.
Fill meat shell and cover with foil.
Bake 25 minutes; uncover and sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake uncovered another 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Sauce:
Mix first 5 ingredients in a 2-quart saucepan; heat for 15 minutes.
Put aside.

title: caramelized tomatoes
directions: Cut tomatoes from blossom and take out pulp.
Place in a baking pan.
Remove crust from bread and cube.
Combine with tomato pulp, melted brown sugar, butter, salt and pepper.
Fill shells with mixture.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Garnish with parsley.

title: peanut butter-chocolate squares(reese's cups)
directions: Melt peanut butter and butter in microwave on High until smooth; add sugar and graham cracker crumbs and mix.
Mixture will be crumbly.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan.

title: chocolate plunge
directions: In medium saucepan, stir corn syrup and cream.
Bring to a boil over medium heat.
Remove from heat.
Add chocolate; stir until completely melted.
Serve warm as a fondue dip for fruits.

title: swiss vegetable medley
directions: Combine vegetables, soup, 1/2 cup cheese, sour cream, pepper, pimiento and 1/2 can French fried onions.
Pour into a 1-quart casserole.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and onions.
Bake, uncovered, for 5 minutes longer.
Makes 6 servings.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Melt butter in baking dish.
Mix flour, brown sugar and pecans.
Pour into butter and bake 15 minutes in 350° oven.
Cool well.
Mix sugar, cream cheese, Cool Whip and vanilla.
Pour over crust and add blueberry pie filling.

title: fresh peach pie
directions: Bring jello, cornstarch, white sugar and water to boil.
Cool slightly and pour over fruit.
Top with whipped cream when cooled.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix together hamburger, egg, Rice Krispies, onion flakes, salt and pepper.
Roll mixture into walnut-size balls and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Combine and mix butter, sugar and peanut butter until creamy. Roll in small balls.
Chill for 1 hour.
Melt chocolate chips and paraffin on heat in double boiler.
Dip chilled peanut butter balls in chocolate mixture.
Place on buttered wax paper until hardened.
Store in fridge.

title: hershey pie
directions: Put marshmallows, milk and Hershey bars in double boiler. Heat and blend together.
Cool.
Fold in heavy whipped cream. Pour into shell and refrigerate.

title: fettucini toss
directions: Prepare pasta and cheese according to package directions, stirring in remaining ingredients during last minute of cooking. Remove from heat.
Cover; let stand 2 minutes.

title: oriental beef(serves 10)
directions: Brown onion and beef.
Pour off fat.
Add soup, soy sauce and water.
Cook slowly about 10 minutes. Add green pepper, celery, pimentos and chestnuts.
Cook until vegetables are still crunchy.
Add sour cream, mushrooms and noodles and put in a buttered 3-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with almonds. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.
May be frozen.

title: rhubarb strawberry rolls
directions: Mix rhubarb, strawberries and cup of sugar in an 8 x 10-inch pan. Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Cut in the butter or oil. Add the milk and knead for several minutes. Roll out and dot with butter. Roll up the sheet of dough and slice. Place slices on fruit mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: corn muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients and
pour
into well-greased muffin tins. Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 375°.

title: molded banana
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add cold water and cool to room temperature.
Slice 1/2 banana into individual molds.
Pour gelatin over fruit and stir.
Chill until set.
Yield:
2 servings. Carbohydrate 8 g, protein 2 g, fat 0 g, calories 40.
One serving = 1 fruit exchange.

title: baked cardamom applesauce
directions: Layer sliced apples in ungreased baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over apples.
Bake uncovered for 1 hour at 375°.
Mash warm apples.
Makes 5 to 6 cups.

title: fresh fruit frappe
directions: Mix all ingredients, except ice.
Fill blender half full of mixture; add crushed ice to fill to top.
Cover and blend on high speed until uniform consistency.
Repeat with remaining mixture. Serve immediately.
Garnish with fruit, if desired.
Makes 4 servings.

title: baked fish
directions: Cover fillets with 1/2-inch milk in baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 12 minutes.
Drain off milk.
Spread fillets with butter and lemon juice.
Sprinkle generously with seasoned salt.
Broil for 5 minutes.

title: easy christmas candy
directions: In double boiler, melt chocolate chips and butterscotch chips. Remove from heat and stir in noodles and nuts.
Drop by spoon onto wax paper on cookie sheet.
Refrigerate until set.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: pizza porcupine patties
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Set aside 8 ounces tomato sauce.
Mix remaining sauce, ground beef, rice, chilies, salt, garlic salt and oregano.
Makes 6 patties (1/2-inch thick).
Place in baking pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Do not grease pan.
Cook uncovered for 15 minutes.
Remove from oven and drain.
Dissolve bouillon in boiling water and stir in remaining tomato sauce.
Pour mixture over patties.
Cover and bake for 35 minutes.
Cover patties with surrounding sauce.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Cook until cheese has melted.

title: harvest herb vegetables
directions: Peel vegetables; cut into large (1-inch) chunks.
Combine vegetables in a 2-quart baking dish.
Drizzle melted butter over vegetables; toss to coat.
Sprinkle the Harvest Herb Blend and salt evenly over vegetables; toss to evenly distribute spice mixture.
Cover and bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes or until tender.
Makes 4 servings.

title: poverty cake
directions: Boil the first 6 ingredients together for 3 minutes; cool. When cool, add dry ingredients.
Beat about 200 strokes, until mixture is bubbly.
Bake in greased and floured loaf pan in hot oven (375° to 400°) for 1 hour, then reduce heat until cake is done, about 15 minutes.
This may vary.

title: country-style rotini
directions: Cook rotini according to package directions. Heat olive oil in large skillet over medium heat. Saute ham, peppers and mushrooms for 2 minutes. Add garlic, salt and pepper and cook for about 4 minutes. Add chicken broth and simmer mixture for 2 minutes. Add hot rotini and mix well. Add spinach and cook until the spinach is wilted. Add Parmesan cheese. Blend well and serve. Serves 6 to 8.

title: key lime pie
directions: Mix condensed milk with softened Cool Whip.
Add Key lime juice slowly while mixing.	When thoroughly mixed pour in graham cracker crust.
Refrigerate for 2 hours and serve.

title: irish tea scones
directions: Rub the butter into the flour; add the baking powder, salt and sugar and mix well.
Beat the egg and add to the milk.
Mix the liquid into the dry ingredients to make a manageable dough, neither too firm nor too slack.
Turn onto a floured board; roll to 1-inch thick and cut into rounds with a pastry cutter.
Arrange on a lightly floured baking sheet and bake at 420° until risen and brown, approximately 15 minutes.
Yields 18 scones.

title: potato cucumber salad
directions: Bring a large pot of water to boil.
Scrub potatoes, then cut into 1-inch cubes and boil 15 to 20 minutes.
Peel and seed cucumber and cut into 1-inch cubes.
Blanch cucumber 1 minute in saucepan; remove.
Blanch garlic 4
minutes; drain and remove from pan.
Drain potatoes and cucumber; combine in large bowl.

title: goya lenten sauce for spaghetti
directions: Heat oil
in heavy skillet or pot.
Add chopped vegetables and simmer
for
minutes.	Stir
often
to keep from browning. Add
seasonings, tomatoes and tomato paste.
Simmer over low heat, uncovered, for 1 hour or until well thickened. Add Ragu sauce and bring to low boil and turn off.

title: chinese cabbage salad
directions: Chop cabbage by hand.
Chop onion.
Combine in bowl.
Mix next 4 ingredients and pour over cabbage and onion, along with seasoning packet from the noodles.
Twenty minutes before serving, add almonds, sunflower kernels and raw crumbled noodles.
Good for a week in fridge.

title: dumplings to freeze
directions: Mix flour, salt and margarine well.
Beat egg; pour into 1-cup measure and finish filling cup with milk.
Add egg mixture to flour and margarine.
Work well.

title: fried pie dough
directions: Mix well.
Cover and store in refrigerator overnight.
Make fruit pie.
Fry in deep fat.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat and onion in skillet. Drain. Mix salt, pepper and soup with hamburger mixture. Pour into dish. Slice cheese and layer over meat mixture. Layer Tots over cheese. Cook at 325° for 1 hour.

title: icebox pickles
directions: Mix cucumbers, onions, peppers and salt.
Cover and refrigerate for 2 hours.
Drain well, then add sugar, vinegar and celery seed.
Pickles will keep indefinitely if kept in refrigerator.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Remove chicken from bone.
Melt margarine and mix with stuffing in separate bowl.
Combine soups and broth.
(Add broth, slowly stirring in.)

title: easy cheesy chicken
directions: Place chicken breasts in a well-greased pan.
Place a slice of Swiss cheese on each piece.
Mix chicken soup with water and pour over chicken.
Sprinkle stuffing over top; then drizzle melted butter over top.
Bake, uncovered, for 55 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: sausage gravy
directions: Crumble pork sausage into large frypan.
Cook over medium heat.
May add chopped onions if you like.
Drain off all but 2 tablespoons grease.
Stir in flour, stirring constantly until bubbles and turns light brown.
Stir in milk plus water.
Add salt and black pepper.
Cook until thickened.
Good to stir in dash of Texas Pete or Worcestershire sauce.
Serve over hot biscuits, broken in half.

title: double crust for 8-inch pie
directions: Mix flour and salt in a bowl.
Cut Crisco into flour with a pastry blender, 2 knives or a fork until the pieces are the size of peas.

title: chili cheese dip
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In a 9 x 9 pan, spread cream cheese on the bottom. Spread chili on top of the cream cheese. Sprinkle cheese on top. Bake until cheese melts. Serve with Fritos Scoops.

title: party chicken
directions: Wrap each chicken breast with a slice of bacon.
Arrange dried beef in ungreased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Place chicken on dried beef. Combine soup and sour cream.
Pour over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, at 275° for 3 hours.

title: quick deep-dish cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in 4-quart baking dish at 350° in moderate oven. After margarine is melted, mix in separate bowl, sugar, flour and milk.
Pour mixture into baking dish, then place fruit and syrup into baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve warm with whipped cream.
Other fruit can be used, as well as canned pie filling.

title: homemade macaroni and cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 375.
Cook macaroni according to directions on box.
Drain and set aside.
Grate cheeses together.
Scald milk, butter, salt and pepper.
Bring to boil and immediately remove from heat.
Mix macaroni, cheeses and milk mixture together.
Save 1/2 cup of cheese mixture to put on top.
Bake at 350 for 20 min. or until lightly browned.

title: white bread or rolls
directions: In a large bowl, mix together all ingredients except flour. Let stand until yeast begins to work.
Stir in thoroughly, a little at a time, the flour.
Cover and allow dough to rise until double.
After second rising, turn dough onto floured board or counter top and knead until all air bubbles are gone.
Form dough into bread or rolls.
Cover with a cloth and let rise until almost double.
Bake rolls at 425°, loaves of bread at 400°.
Brush tops of rolls with melted margarine as they come from the oven.
Cover either bread or rolls with a cloth until cool.
Makes 3 to 4 dozen rolls or 2 loaves of bread.

title: broiled marinated fish steaks
directions: In large, shallow, non-metallic dish, with whisk, combine broth, oil, lemon juice, mustard and pepper.
Add fish, turning to coat.
Cover; refrigerate for 1 hour, turning fish occasionally.
Remove fish from marinade.

title: avocado crab cutlets
directions: Remove spines from crab meat; melt butter and blend in flour. Add salt, pepper and milk; cook until thickened and add avocado and crab meat.
Mix well.
Shape into cutlets; roll in crumbs, then egg and again in crumbs.
Fry in deep hot fat, 360°, until browned, 2 to 4 minutes or add a little milk; place in casserole and cover with buttered crumbs.
Brown in 350° oven.

title: christmas salad
directions: Drain pineapple and apricots together; save liquid.
Drain mixed fruit separately; discard liquid.
Mix the pudding with drained juice; add liquid gradually.
Stir until smooth.
Fold pudding into drained fruit and banana slices.
Refrigerate.
