title: red ribbon meat loaf
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese according to package directions. Set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Mix well.

title: chinese pickled beets
directions: Place sugar, cornstarch, cloves, oil, salt and vanilla in large, shallow skittle; mix well.
Add beets and 1 1/2 cups beet liquid; cook over medium heat for 3 minutes, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Serve hot or cold.
Keep well in glass jar in refrigerator.
Delicious served on a mound of cottage cheese. Serves 10 to 12.

title: pork roast(crockery cooking)
directions: Always boil your pork before cooking in a recipe.
Boil pork for 1/2 hour; remove to crock-pot (low).
Add chicken broth mixed with 2 tablespoons flour.
Add rosemary, lemon pepper and salt to broth.
Pour over pork.
Cover and cook 6 to 8 hours spooning gravy over meat for flavor every so often.
Serve with potatoes (sweet or white) or noodles.

title: impossible taco pie
directions: Brown beef and onion. Add taco mix. Beat with mixer the eggs, milk and Bisquick for one minute. Spread beef and onion in pie plate. Cover with chilies. Pour liquid over and bake at 400° for 25 minutes. Remove and cover with 1 cup grated cheese and thinly sliced tomato (optional). Bake an additional 5 to 10 minutes.

title: zoie's favorite eggplant
directions: Slice eggplant in 1/4-inch pieces. Lay flat to cover the bottom of a roasting pan. Drizzle with olive oil and garlic salt. Roast in a 475° oven until eggplant begins to appear translucent (about 5 to 10 minutes).

title: pork tenderloin roll
directions: Mix garlic, onions and oil.
Marinate pork in mixture for 1 1/2 hours at room temperature, covered.
Grill on top shelf at high temperature for 25 to 30 minutes.
While meat is grilling, baste 3 or 4 times with a mixture of the last 4 ingredients. Remove meat from grill and immediately cover with foil.
Rest 15 minutes.
Garnish with more parsley, chives, green onions and salt and pepper.
Slice and serve.

title: squash crouquettes
directions: Cook squash and onion in small amount of salted water.
Drain and mash.
Add egg, butter, cheese and 1/2 cup cracker crumbs. Mix well.
Shape into balls and roll in remaining crumbs.
Fry in deep fat until golden brown.

title: teriyaki sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Use as a marinade for chicken or beef.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream butter, slowly beat in sugar and salt.
Add eggs, one at a time, beat briskly.
Blend entire mixture.
Pour into pie crust. Bake 10 minutes at 450°, then reduce heat to 350° for 30 minutes.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in baking dish. Stir in flour, sugar and milk in another bowl, then pour in margarine. Pour in baking dish. Add fruit in the center of baking dish. Don't stir in fruit, just pour in middle of batter mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: spicy corn combo
directions: In medium saucepan, combine all ingredients.
Heat thoroughly. Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: norwegian apple pie
directions: Beat together egg, sugar, vanilla, salt and baking powder until smooth and fluffy.
Stir in the remaining ingredients. Spread into a greased 8-inch pie pan and bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: venetian salad
directions: Combine undrained mushrooms, oil, vinegar and seasonings. Pour over Brussels sprouts, carrots and onion.
Cover and marinate several hours.
Just before serving, drain; toss vegetables with salad greens.
Serve topped with hard-cooked eggs and salami. Makes 6 servings.
tags: bite size pieces mixed salad greens

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Add several strips of bacon on top. Bake at 300° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: jam cake
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar and oil.
Mix well.
Sift all dry ingredients together.
Add half dry mixture to eggs, sugar and oil; beat well.
Mix in buttermilk.
Add remaining ingredients. Add jam; mix well. Fold in pecans.
Pour into two 8-inch greased and floured pans.
Bake at 350° until cake springs back when touched.

title: spicy nuts
directions: Combine egg whites and water.
Add nuts and coat thoroughly. In a separate bowl, combine sugar, pumpkin pie spice, salt and pepper.
Add to nuts.
Toss until well coated.
Spread mixture on a lightly oiled baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Remove and break into clusters.
Serves 12.

title: caramel crackers
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
In a greased, large shallow pan, combine crackers and nuts.
In a saucepan, boil for 5 minutes over medium heat, the following:
margarine, corn syrup and brown sugar. Remove from heat and add the vanilla and soda.
Blend well.
Pour the entire mixture over crackers and nuts.
Coat well.
Bake 45 minutes, stirring every 15 minutes.
Pour onto wax paper and break apart.
After cool, store in airtight container.

title: chocolate surprise cake
directions: Make pudding according to package directions.
Let cool for a few minutes but do not let it get thick and set.
Mix cake mix into pudding mix (do not follow directions on cake mix box).
Mix well with a spoon, not with an electric mixer.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips all over cake, then sprinkle pecans over the chips. Put into oven and bake according to directions on cake mix box.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix and store in jar.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Mix and bring to a boil the oleo, cocoa and milk. Remove from heat.
Add powdered sugar, pecans and vanilla. Spread on cake.

title: marinade for game or beef
directions: With a fork, combine the oil and wine. Add the cloves and shallots (both finely chopped), the peppercorns (crushed), bay leaf, chopped oregano, sweet basil and salt to taste.
Mix thoroughly to blend the ingredients.

title: quick pork polynesian
directions: Saute cutlets in oil.
Add remaining ingredients; simmer, covered, for 1 hour.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Blend peanut butter and powdered sugar together; spread 2/3 of this in baked pie shell.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Melt butter in bottom of baking dish. Stir in 1/2 of dressing mix with broth & onion.
Spread over bottom of dish. Pour mushroom soup over this. Layer chicken with dressing mix on top. Last layer cream of chicken soup. Bake at 350° until brown.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Combine spaghetti, eggs, Parmesan cheese and milk.
Put half this mixture in a large greased baking dish.
Layer half the Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat with another layer of spaghetti and Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 5 to 20 minutes.
Cool 5 to 10 minutes.
Cut in squares and serve with spaghetti sauce.

title: barbecue beef for a crowd
directions: Put beef in crock-pot and add all ingredients.
Cover and cook for several hours, until tender.
Can be cooked in oven at 300° for 6 hours.
Shred and serve on buns.
Freezes well.

title: ice cream topping cake
directions: Bake the cake mix as directed on box.
When done, take out and poke holes in cake. Mix Eagle Brand milk and topping together. Pour on top of cake and let cool. Put whipped topping on top.
Add nuts or sliver a candy bar and sprinkle on top.

title: perfect apple pie
directions: Peel and slice apples (Jonathan or Granny Smith).
Sprinkle lemon juice over apples.
Mix sugar, flour, salt and cinnamon and stir into apples.
Spoon apple mixture into 9-inch pie crust.
Top with second crust.
Seal edges and cut vents in top crust.
Brush top crust with water and sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 425° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: mom's sour cream cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter together.
Add egg yolks, 2 at a time. Blend soda with sour cream.
Add sour cream and flour alternately to butter and sugar.
Beat mixture for 3 minutes.
Whip egg whites until stiff.
Fold into batter and beat for 3 minutes.
Pour into a greased and floured tube or Bundt pan.
Bake for 60 to 70 minutes at 325°.
Remove from pan immediately and carefully.
When cool, sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: friendship egg custard pies
directions: In a large mixing bowl, slowly mix eggs (don't let them foam). Sift together flour, sugar and salt.
Add to eggs slowly.
Add milk, vanilla and butter.
Pour into two 9-inch pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Grease and flour tube pan.
Sift flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Cream margarine, sugar, eggs (one at a time) and vanilla.
Add sour cream, alternating with dry ingredients.
Fill pan with half of dough.
Sprinkle half of cinnamon/sugar mixture over dough.
Pour remaining dough in pan.
Top with remaining cinnamon and sugar mixture.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: hot vegetable casserole
directions: Cook and drain vegetables.
Add celery.
Mix mayonnaise and milk.
Pour over vegetables.
Layer vegetables, chestnuts and cheese slices.
Mix butter with crackers.
Top casserole with this mixture.
Bake at 350° until hot and bubbly.

title: lazy cucu pickles
directions: Place cucumbers, onion, bell pepper and salt in a large bowl. Refrigerate for 2 hours (do not drain).
Whisk together vinegar, sugar and celery seed.
Pour over cucumber mixture and store in refrigerator.
Makes about 10 cups.

title: oatmeal chocolate morsel cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients; stir well.
It will be thick.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart on a lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned. (Do not overcook.)
Makes 6 dozen.

title: my favorite sugar cookies
directions: In a bowl, cream the sugar and butter.
Add egg and vanilla. Mix thoroughly.
In a different bowl, mix dry ingredients together, then add to creamed mixture.
Divide dough in half. Refrigerate a couple of hours.
Roll out to desired thickness. Bake at 350° for 7 to 8 minutes or until light golden brown.

title: jello pie
directions: Bring to a boil and let cool.
Beat in 1 egg.
Whip 1 cup evaporated milk.
Pour into first mixture and mix well.
Pour into pie pan lined in bottom and on sides with vanilla wafers.
Chill.

title: easy hot mexican dip
directions: Melt over stove or in microwave.
Serve with Tostitos.

title: molasses oat bread
directions: Combine 3 cups flour, oats, brown sugar, yeast and salt.
In saucepan, combine milk, water, shortening and molasses.
Cook over low heat until warm, stirring to melt shortening.

Add molasses mixture with eggs to flour mixture. Beat at low speed for 1/2 minute, scraping bowl constantly. Beat 3 minutes at high speed. By hand, stir in enough of remaining flour to make a soft dough. Turn out on lightly floured surface and knead until smooth, 4 to 5 minutes. Place in greased bowl, turning once to grease surface. Cover and let rise until double in size, about 1 1/2 hours. Punch down; turn out on lightly floured surface. Divide dough in half. Shape each into loaf. Brush with a little water. Roll in oats. Place in 2 greased loaf pans. Cover and let rise until double, about 1 hour. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes. Makes 2 loaves.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients in microwave bowl.
Microwave for 10 minutes.
Stir one time.
Pour in baked pie shell. Beat 3 egg whites until stiff.
Add 2 tablespoons sugar and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Place on pie and place in 400° oven until brown.

title: holiday punch
directions: Let ice cream and sherbet soften a little before stirring liquids in.
Mix well before serving.

title: jam cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs and spices.
Sift flour slowly.
Add flour, soda and buttermilk and jam.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cabbage and tomatoes
directions: Cut cabbage and tomatoes.
Put into kettle.
Cover with water, salt, pepper and oleo.
Boil 20 minutes.
Fry hamburg and onion. Cool, then add to hamburg, egg and rice.
Mix and put into peppers. Simmer 1 hour.

title: lazy apple pie
directions: Fill ungreased 9-inch plate two-thirds full with prepared apples.
Combine 1 tablespoon sugar with cinnamon and sprinkle over apples.
Mix together 1 cup sugar, flour, butter, egg and salt. Pour over mixture the apples and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: In 2-quart casserole dish, layer potatoes, 1/2 of onions and 1 cup of cranberries.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and drizzle with 1/2 of honey.
Top with remaining cranberries and honey.
Cover and bake at 400° for 35 minutes.
Gently stir casserole.
Top with remaining onions.
Bake, uncovered, 1 to 3 minutes longer or until golden brown.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: spicy baked chicken
directions: Spray bottom of 13 x 9 inch baking pan. Wash chicken and place in pan. Brush chicken with olive oil, then sprinkle with all seasonings (to your taste). Add 1/2 cup water or wine in pan to prevent chicken from sticking. Bake in a 375° oven for 30 minutes. If not done bake another 15 minutes or until brown.

title: formula scramble
directions: Break eggs into bowl.
Beat until foamy.
Add formula, salt and paprika until blended.
Melt butter in skillet over low heat. Pour in egg mixture.
Stir until eggs are thick but soft.
Serve at once on warm plate.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Add milk and grated cheese to sausage.
Gradually add Bisquick until well mixed.
Roll into small balls (dampen hands and mixture is easier to roll).
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes or until desired doneness.

title: supreme meat loaf
directions: Combine ground beef, onion and green peppers in an 8 x 8-inch casserole.
Spread the mushroom soup on meat.
Bake at 375° for about an hour.

title: english toffee(tastes like a heath bar)
directions: Melt butter in heavy pan
and
put in sugar.
Cook over medium heat, stir, stir, stir until sugar is melted.
After it starts to melt, put in
1 1/2 cups chopped pecans.
Stir until pulls away from pan;
then
put
in
cream
of
tartar, really stir.
Take off when
it
turns
pinkish-tan,
put
on greased cookie sheet. Pour package of
morsels on top of hot mixture, then sprinkle 1/2 cup chopped
pecans on top.
Cool, slice and enjoy.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Cube cream cheese and add 7-Up, pineapple and 4 to 5 drops of food coloring; mix well and pour in mold.
Chill until firm.

title: trail drive beans
directions: Wash beans and soak overnight in cold water; drain 2 1/2 cups water and bring to a boil.
Turn down and simmer 1 hour.
Render salt pork in skillet; add beef and brown.
Drain.
Add to beans with remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer for 2 hours, adding hot water as needed.

title: orange salad
directions: Put cottage cheese in bowl.
Sprinkle orange jello over cottage cheese; mix well.
Mix Cool Whip with cottage cheese and orange jello.
Mix in orange segments.
Put remainder of orange segments on top of salad.

title: stuffed shells - cheese filled
directions: Cook shells according to package directions and drain.
Cool on wax paper to keep from sticking.
Combine cheese, eggs, parsley, oregano, salt and pepper.
Fill each shell with 2 tablespoons of mixture.

title: maduros fritos
directions: Cut plantains into quarters.
Fry in hot, melted butter at medium heat until golden brown and soft.
A sweet that goes with the meat.

title: zucchini nibbles
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Spread in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cut into small squares to serve. May be served either hot or cold.
Yields 25 servings.

title: orange-date cake
directions: Mix together shortening and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time. Add, alternating dry ingredients with buttermilk.
Then add orange rind, dates and nuts.
Grease and flour long cake pan.
Bake in 325° oven for 30 minutes or until tested done.
While cake is still hot pour 1 cup orange juice mixed with 1 cup sugar over it.

title: "mom's" macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni; drain.
Boil together the sugar, flour, water and vinegar; stir and cool.
When cool, add mayo and mustard.
Mix in macaroni, celery, onions, cheese, tomatoes, carrot and eggs.

title: liz's red beans
directions: Lightly brown garlic and onion in oil.
Add green pepper; cook on low to saute.
Add tomato sauce and simmer 15 minutes.
Add beans and taste.
Add hot sauce now, if needed.
Perfect with my Paella!

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix together mayonnaise, vinegar and sugar.
Put bacon into mixture.
Mix all ingredients together and toss.
You may mix all ingredients except the mayonnaise mixture the night before. Serves 10.

title: chocolate heath bar trifle
directions: You will need a trifle dish.

title: kringle sticks
directions: Mix Nucoa, flour and sour cream as pie crust.
Chill 1 hour or more.
Divide dough into 4 parts.
Roll each part on floured board into 6 x 12-inch strips.
Put 1/4 of filling down center of strip.
Bring sides over filling overlapping them.
Place on cookie sheet, two to a pan.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
While still warm, frost with powdered sugar, vanilla and a little milk.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Drain pineapple, add enough water to make two cups.
Put in boiler and get hot.
Add jello and dissolve.
Let stand until warm. Add cheese spread and pineapple, put in refrigerator.
When almost congealed, stir in salad dressing.
Use more salad dressing, if desired.

title: angel rolls(negligible cholesterol per roll)
directions: Dissolve milk powder in milk.
Stir sugar and oil into water. When sugar is dissolved, add milk.
Stir in until lukewarm.
Pour out a small part of this mixture and add yeast to this.
Stir in the "egg substitute" and set aside for 20 minutes.
Mix the salt into the flour.
Pour in the liquid mixture.
Blend until batter becomes a smooth paste.
Cover with a damp cloth and set to rise in a warm place until doubled in bulk.
Half fill oiled muffin pans and again let rise until doubled in bulk.
Bake at 400° in a preheated oven for about 20 minutes or until done.

title: rhubarb-strawberry jam(freezer)
directions: Put rhubarb in pan; pour sugar over rhubarb.
Let set overnight.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Melt oleo and peanut butter over low heat, stirring often. Remove from heat.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Add milk, small amounts at a time, to get good kneading consistency.
Pat out in buttered 9 x 9-inch pan.
Cool.
Cut into blocks.

title: frog eye salad
directions: In saucepan, put sugar, flour and salt. Stir in juice and egg and cook over medium heat; stir until thickened.
Add lemon juice. Set aside and cool. Cook pepe separately. Cover. Place in refrigerator until cooled. Mix all ingredients together and cool.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Blend oil, sugar and eggs.
Add flour with soda, baking powder, salt, cinnamon and vanilla.
Fold in zucchini and nuts. Mix well, but do not beat.
Bake in 2 or 3 loaf pans at 325° for 1 hour.

title: baked beef barbecue
directions: Cut beef into small cubes.
Place in roaster or Dutch oven. Combine rest of ingredients in saucepan; bring to a boil and pour over meat.
Cover, simmer in 300° oven for 6 hours or until meat is tender enough to pull apart with a fork.
Pull all meat apart and simmer for 15 minutes.
Any leftover barbecue may be stored in refrigerator for several days or frozen indefinitely.
Serves 20.

title: dolly's catfish stew
directions: Combine butts meat and onion together in bottom of large pot. Add a little grease to saute.
Add tomatoes, deboned fish and spices and let cook on low for awhile.
If you use red peppers, remember to remove them before serving.
They get hotter and hotter.
Can be frozen for later use also.

title: chicken marsala
directions: Rub chicken with lemon.
Brown garlic in butter and rosemary. Flour and season chicken.
Add to butter and brown for 2 minutes on each side on high heat.
Add wine.
Cover, reduce heat to medium and cook for 5 minutes.
Add mushrooms.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni in salty water as directed on box.
Drain in colander.
Put back in pot.
Add butter, whipped eggs and milk. Stir in cheese.
Place in greased casserole and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until liquid is firm, but not dry.

title: lettuce salad
directions: Fry bacon crisp and drain.
Cut up head of lettuce in bottom of bowl.
Cut head of cauliflower over lettuce, then add chopped onion.
Spread salad dressing over mixture to seal.
Next, spread Parmesan cheese over salad dressing, then sugar.
Crumble bacon on top and cover with lid.
Let set at least 6 hours or overnight in refrigerator.

title: sesame chicken wings
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in large mixing bowl; mix well. Dip chicken in half and half; dredge in crumb mixture.
Arrange coated wings in three 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pans.
Pour melted butter evenly over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: italian sauce chicken
directions: Place chicken in casserole dish.
Mix Italian sauce (dressing) and lemon juice.
Pour over chicken; melt butter and pour over chicken, then salt and pepper.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: lime mold salad(good with ham)
directions: Drain and heat pineapple juice; dissolve jello in hot juice. Add pineapple and sour cream.
Pour into (fancy!) mold and refrigerate.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in baking dish.

title: d-light jello salad
directions: Mix dry jello and water together. Chill until almost set. Whip until fluffy and fold in the Cool Whip. Then add all the other ingredients. Refrigerate for about 1 hour. Ready to serve.

title: mother goose popcorn(microwave)
directions: Melt butter.
Add all ingredients except popcorn and soda. Microwave on High for 3 minutes; add soda.
Spray inside of paper grocery bag with Pam; put popcorn in bag.
Pour sauce over popcorn and shake to mix.
Put bag in microwave and cook on High for 1 1/2 minutes; shake bag.
Microwave for 1 minute; shake again. Microwave 30 seconds; shake.
Microwave 30 seconds; shake, then pour on wax paper.
Cool and eat!

title: peach festival cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in casserole.
Add peaches. Sprinkle with 1/4 cup sugar.
Combine remaining sugar, flour, baking powder, salt and nutmeg.
Stir in milk and vanilla.
Pour batter over peaches; bake for 30 minutes or until golden brown. Serve vanilla ice cream over cobbler.

title: opera bars
directions: Blend flour, sugar and butter.
Pat into cookie pan.
Bake for 15 minutes in 350° oven.
Beat eggs and combine with remaining ingredients.
Spread over top of baked mixture.
Bake for 30 minutes at 300°.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: vidalia onion pie
directions: Melt 1/4 cup butter and mix with crackers.
Press into 9-inch pie pan.
Saute onions in 2 tablespoons butter until tender, then place them in the crumb shell.
Combine milk, eggs, salt and pepper and pour over onions.
Sprinkle with cheese and paprika. Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: frozen lemonade pie
directions: Mix ingredients together and pour into graham cracker pie crust.
Refrigerate several hours until set before serving.
You may wish to add a bit of red food coloring if the lemonade is not "pink" enough.

title: tuna ball
directions: Soften cream cheese, then mix in tuna and other ingredients. Make into ball if desired.
Serve with crackers.

title: hamburger crunch
directions: Brown meat and onions together; drain.
Add soups, warm water, rice, soy sauce, salt and pepper.
Heat thoroughly and pour into a casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Add chow mein noodles, and bake an additional 10 minutes, uncovered.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all together and drop by spoonfuls into hot grease.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients in order given.
Bake in a black iron skillet at 350° for about an hour, or until golden brown.

title: lumpia
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Mix all vegetables with meat.
Cook 5 minutes over medium heat.
Add soy sauce; stir.
Add egg yolks, stir well.
Separate lumpia wrappers carefully.
Use 1 to 2 tablespoons of meat mix in wrapper.
Fold wrapper and roll.
Seal with egg white at edge of wrapper.
Deep fry until golden brown. Drain on end.
Turn to other end and drain a second time.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: In a 3-quart oblong baking dish, combine soup, milk, thyme and pepper.
Stir in vegetables and chicken.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until mixture begins to bubble.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together until well blended.
Pour into well greased and floured Bundt pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour. Cool on wire rack for 45 minutes before inverting onto plate.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix
soup
mix, sour cream and mayonnaise.
Add drained chopped
spinach
and
water chestnuts; blend well.
Chill for several hours or overnight.
Delicious with crackers, cubes of French bread or crudites.

title: cheese soup
directions: Brown onion in butter.
Blend in flour and seasoning. Gradually stir in milk and broth.
Bring to a boil and boil 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Add cheese.
Cook slowly, stirring constantly until cheese melts.

title: anna maude's currant sauce
directions: Blend the cornstarch with 1/2 cup apple cider until smooth. Pour into a small saucepan.
Add all remaining ingredients, except butter and salt.
Heat, stirring constantly, over moderate heat. Bring to a boil; cook until thickened and clear and no raw taste remains.
Add butter and salt.

title: christmas holly leaves
directions: Melt together marshmallows and butter; add 1 1/2 teaspoons green food coloring.
Pour over 3 cups cornflakes.
Drop by spoonful on waxed paper and add red cinnamon candies to look like holly.
(Very pretty addition to a plate of cookies.)

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix all ingredients.
In a casserole dish sprayed with Pam, bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: strawberry delight salad
directions: Mix cottage cheese and dry jello together.
Stir in pineapple. Gently fold in Cool Whip.
Garnish with nuts and refrigerate.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Cook hamburger, onion and bell pepper until brown. Add ground mustard, tomato sauce, ketchup and chili powder.
Cook on low for at least 2 hours. Pour over spaghetti noodles.

title: snowballs
directions: Mix and cook, stirring, sugar, butter, dates and egg.
When melted, add cereals and nuts.
Form into balls and roll in coconut.

title: chocolate covered cherries and nuts
directions: Cream the butter and sugar together, adding milk in small amounts.
Add salt and vanilla.
Drain cherries.
Roll cherries in cream mixture to cover each cherry well.
Add nuts to what is left of mixture and roll in oblong rolls.
Melt chocolate and paraffin over boiling water.
Dip cherry and nut rolls, one at a time, in melted chocolate.
Place on wax paper to cool.

title: cherry dream squares
directions: In large bowl, combine cake mix, 6 Tbsp. margarine and 1 c. oats.
Mix until crumbly.
Reserve 1 cup of crumbs for topping. To remaining crumbs, add egg and mix well.
Press into a greased 13 inch x 9 inch pan.
Pour cherry pie filling over crust.
To reserved 1 cup of crumbs, add 1/4 c. oats, 2 Tbsp. margarine, nuts and brown sugar.
Blend and sprinkle over cherry mixture.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 - 35 minutes.
Cool.

title: oat burgers
directions: Boil everything together except oatmeal and nuts.
Remove from heat.
Mix oats and nuts, then sprinkle a little at a time into boiling mixture.
Let stand until most of the liquid is absorbed. Stir lightly until just mixed.
Drop by spoonfuls on oiled cookie sheet; press flat.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: sweet red pepper pasta
directions: Heat oil in skillet.
Saute garlic and peppers about 15 minutes.
Meanwhile, cook pasta.
Drain and transfer back into pot.
Add chicken bouillon to pasta; simmer until most of bouillon has been absorbed.
Stir in garlic, oil and pepper mixture and toss.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Serves 2 as a main dish or 4 to 6 as a side dish.

title: party punch
directions: *If using sugar-free Kool-Aid, no sugar needed.
If using regular Kool-Aid, sweeten just as you would regular Kool-Aid.

title: jalapeno pepper jelly
directions: Put peppers and vinegar into blender.
Blend well.
Add this mixture to sugar in a large pan.
Cook slowly to a rolling boil. Skim.
Boil gently on low flame for 3 to 5 minutes.
Add Certo and coloring.
Return to a boil and pour into jars.
Makes 6 to 8 jars.

title: spinach dip and hawaiian bread
directions: Cook spinach according to package directions. Drain. Mix all ingredients and chill. Serve with Hawaiian bread. Pull out the middle of bread and put dip in, using bread as a serving bowl for the dip.

title: chicken in soup
directions: Mix celery soup, mushroom soup and onion soup together and pour over the chicken.
Cover and cook 1 hour at 325°, then uncover and cook 1 hour at 325°.

title: lori's firecracker chili
directions: In large kettle, brown cubed round steak in oil with 1 medium chopped onion, 1 clove minced garlic, cumin and 1 teaspoon chili powder.
Add 2 cups water.
Bring to boil, reduce heat and cook down until liquid is almost gone.
Set aside.

title: angel cake supreme
directions: Sift together flour and powdered sugar.
Set aside.
Beat egg whites until stiff, but not dry, soft peaks.
Turn mixer on low and add sugar & flour mixture.
Add 1 cup sugar and mix well. Pour into angel food cake pan and bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour or until done.

title: savory cauliflower
directions: Microwave directions.
Cut cone shaped wedges out of cauliflower core.
Place cauliflower and water in 1 1/2 quart microwave proof casserole.
Cook on high for 9 minutes.
Turn over halfway.
Drain.
Mix mayonnaise, onion, mustard and salt.
Spoon sauce over cauliflower.
Lay cheese slices on top.
Cook uncovered till cheese melts.
Sprinkle with paprika and let stand 2 minutes before serving.
Serves 6.

title: strawberry jam
directions: Mix berries with sugar. Cook rapidly until thick (about 20 minutes). Add lemon juice a few minutes before cooking is complete. Pour into sterilized Kerr jars to within 1/4-inch of top. Put on cap. Screw band firmly tight. Process in boiling water bath 10 minutes. Yield: 5 (8 ounce) jars.

title: cream of potato soup
directions: Place all vegetables, butter and seasoning in heavy saucepan. Add just enough water to barely cover vegetables. Cover and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and cook until vegetables are very tender.

title: creamy banana pudding
directions: In large bowl, combine sweetened condensed milk and water. Add pudding mix; beat well.
Chill 5 minutes.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: Mix cereal with sugar, flour, soda and salt.
Add eggs, shortening and milk.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Batter will keep up to 6 weeks in refrigerator.

title: chocolate crackers
directions: Line a cookie sheet with foil and butter well.
Place a single layer of saltine crackers on the foil.
In a saucepan, boil for 2 minutes the butter and sugar; do not stir while cooking.
Pour over crackers and bake 4 minutes in a 400° oven.
Remove and sprinkle with milk chocolate chips.
When chocolate is soft, spread around evenly.
This will taste something like chocolate butter brickle.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Combine brown sugar, flour and salt in top of double boiler; add milk and yolks, mixing thoroughly.
Place over rapidly boiling water and cook 10 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from boiling water.
Add butter and vanilla.
Cool.
Turn into pie shell.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Spray baking pan with Pam.
Line bottom of pan with chicken. Sprinkle chopped onion and mushrooms over chicken.
Pour undiluted soups over top.
Place stuffing on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese.
Put half of batter into a 9 x 13-inch well-greased baking dish.
Sprinkle on cheese.
Add rest of batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cherry pie sweet and sour for shrimp or chicken
directions: Heat together the cherry pie filling and pineapple chunks with juice.
Stir-fry green pepper, onion, shrimp or chicken; add to cherry-pineapple mixture.
Serve with rice or noodles.

title: feta cheese ball
directions: Place garlic in work bowl and pulse/chop until finely minced. Add scallions to bowl and pulse for 3 seconds.
Add remaining ingredients, except the salt, and combine and process for about 20 seconds, stopping once and scraping down the side of bowl.
Add salt to taste and adjust other seasonings.
Refrigerate.

title: mint brownies
directions: Follow box directions and bake in a jelly roll pan or cookie sheet, 15 1/2 x 10 x 1-inch.

title: homemade tartar sauce
directions: Place all ingredients in blender and blend until smooth, not too long.
Keeps in refrigerator 2 weeks or longer.

title: marshmallow cream fudge
directions: In medium saucepan, combine margarine, marshmallow, sugar, evaporated milk and salt; bring to full boil, stirring constantly over moderate heat.
Boil 5 minutes, stirring constantly over moderate heat.
Remove from the heat.
Stir in chocolate chips until melted and smooth.
Stir in vanilla and nuts or peppermint extract, if desired.
Pour into greased 8-inch square pan; cool off, then chill several hours before cutting into squares, which may be individually wrapped in plastic wrap.

title: crab meat dip
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Add sour cream and drained crabmeat. Stir together.
Add a pinch of salt.
Place on a nice serving platter in a mound.
Starting on top of mound, pour the cocktail sauce on top, letting it flow over the sides itself.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Just before serving, place Triscuits or your favorite crackers around the edges of plate.

title: potato cream casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients with frozen hash brown potatoes, using half of grated cheese.
Blend well, making sure potatoes remain frozen.

title: cherry cream crescents
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat cream cheese, sugar and egg yolk. Separate roll dough into 16 triangles. Place on lightly greased baking sheets. Spread 1 tablespoon cream cheese mixture near the edge of the short side of each triangle. Top with 1 tablespoon pie filling. Fold the long point of the triangle over the filling and tuck under dough. Lightly beat the egg white and brush over rolls. Bake at 350° 15-20 minutes or until golden brown. To serve, sprinkle the top with confectioners sugar and garnish with cherries left from the pie filling.

title: crab hors d'oeuvre
directions: Blend cream cheese (softened) with lemon juice, onion, mayonnaise and Worcestershire sauce.
Shape into flat round shallow dish or plate.
Top with chili sauce. Just before serving, top with layer of crab and one of parsley.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Preheat oven to 325°. Cream butter, oil and sugar; blend in vanilla, eggs and buttermilk. Combine dry ingredients; stir into creamed mixture with zucchini. Pour into prepared pan.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips and nuts.

title: quick cherry pudding
directions: Turn syrup into measuring cup.
If very sweet, add 2 teaspoons lemon juice.
Add flavorings and mix well.
Follow directions on pudding box to finish pudding.
Mix everything together.
Serve topped with cherries.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: hamburger-rice dish
directions: Brown hamburger and add diced onion. Mix with rest of ingredients. Put in baking dish.
Bake for 2 hours at 350°.

title: fresh green onion butter
directions: Combine all ingredients in small mixing bowl, blending well. Serve with hot bread or baked potatoes.
Makes 3/4 cup.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix melted butter, sugar and eggs together. Add corn meal, vinegar and vanilla. Stir well, but do not overbeat. Pour in unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: brown sugar coffee cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar and salt.
Cut in butter until like fine meal.
Spread 2 1/2 cups of the mixture evenly in the bottom of a greased 7 x 11 x 2-inch baking pan.
Blend soda and nutmeg into remaining flour-sugar-butter mixture.
Combine egg and sour cream. Stir into flour mixture until just blended.
Spoon over crumb mixture in pan.
Sprinkle nuts on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Check for doneness.

title: cookie-dunk pudding
directions: Pour milk into medium bowl.
Add pudding mix.
Beat with wire whisk until well blended, 1 to 2 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes. Spoon half of the pudding into 4 dessert dishes.
Stand 4 to 6 cookies in each dish of pudding, placing them along sides of dish. Top with remaining pudding.
Serve immediately or refrigerate until ready to serve.
Garnish with additional cookies.
Makes 4 servings.
